title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in 8 x 8 x 2-inch microwavable dish.
May sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine flour, oats, brown sugar and cinnamon in mixing bowl.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly. Sprinkle over apples.
Cook on full power for 12 to 14 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: bean burrito bake(serves 8)
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain. Combine beans, baking mix and water in bowl; mix well.
Spread over bottom and halfway up side of greased 10-inch pie plate. Layer ground beef, avocado, salsa and cheese in prepared pie plate.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Cut into wedges; top with sour cream.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Fry celery and onion in oleo until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in casserole at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Grind or crush cookies until fairly fine.
Set aside.
Mix together in a large bowl pudding and milk.
In separate bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar and oleo until smooth and creamy.
Add Cool Whip to pudding and mix well.
Add cream cheese mixture and mix well.

title: baked squash
directions: Wash and cut up squash; boil until tender.
Drain thoroughly and mash.
Add all ingredients, except 1/4 cup margarine and bread crumbs.
Pour mixture in baking dish.
Melt 1/4 cup margarine and pour over mixture.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until brown on top only.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Bake cake by directions on box.
Pour in 2 (9-inch) layer cake pans.
When cake is done, slice into crossways.
Mix sugar and sour cream.
Add coconut.
Spread between layers and on top.

title: carrot-coconut cake(makes 12 servings)
directions: In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and cinnamon; set aside.
In medium bowl, with electric mixer at medium speed, beat margarine, sugar and eggs until creamy.
Alternately stir in milk and flour mixture until blended.
Mix in carrots, coconut, walnuts and pineapple with juice until blended.
Spread into 2 greased 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans; cool completely on wire racks. Frost cake with Coconut Cream Cheese Frosting.
Garnish with coconut and carrot flowers, if desired.

title: california hamburgers
directions: Mix ingredients, except buns, together and spread on open-faced hamburger buns.
Place on cookie sheet and broil until cheese is melted.

title: stuffed zucchini halves
directions: Cut ends off and slice the squash lengthwise.
Hollow seeds out with spoon.
Mix in hamburger with all other ingredients except tomato sauce.
Stuff zucchini halves with mixture.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and pour tomato sauce over them.
(Grated cheese is a tasty change.) Return to oven uncovered for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs; add milk (put flour and nutmeg in a little bit of the milk and dissolve before adding), sugar and vanilla. Strain into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then 350° until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: easy pork chops one pan dinner in 30 minutes
directions: Season pork chops on both sides and brown in frying pan. Cover pork chops with mushroom soup.
Layer sliced potatoes and broccoli (or vegetable of choice) on top of soup and chops.
Cover and lower heat to simmer.
Dinner is done in 30 minutes.
Place chops, potatoes and vegetable on platter.
Add a little water to pan and whisk, then pour sauce on top.
Don't forget to save soup label for Mrs.
McEwan.

title: chocolate-nut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line a 13 x 9-inch baking pan with aluminum foil, extending foil over ends of pan; grease foil. Process graham cracker crumbs and butter in a food processor until well blended.
Press into bottom of prepared pan.
Melt 1/2 cup chocolate chips and stir into sweetened condensed milk.
Pour chocolate mixture over crumb mixture, spreading evenly.
Sprinkle peanut butter chips, remaining 1 cup chocolate chips, coconut and walnuts over chocolate mixture.
Press down chip mixture lightly with a fork.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool completely in a pan on a wire rack.
Lift from pan using ends of foil.
Cut into bars.
Store in an airtight container.
Yield: about 2 1/2 dozen bars.

title: marinated garden tomatoes
directions: Place tomatoes and onion in a shallow serving dish.
In another bowl, combine all remaining ingredients.
Pour over tomatoes.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours or over night. Serves 10.

title: layered salad
directions: Place one layer, in a Pyrex dish, of spinach, sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Crumble on bacon.
Next, add eggs.
Place on a layer of lettuce, salt and pepper to taste.
Add peas, then onions.
Cover with mayonnaise, seal at edge with mayonnaise.
Top with cheese.
Cover tightly with Saran Wrap and refrigerate several hours.

title: potato soup
directions: Place potatoes and onions in a large pot with enough water to cover vegetables at least 2 inches. Cook until potatoes are well done.
Drain off liquid. Reserve. Mash potatoes and onions thoroughly.
Add reserved potato water plus 1 or 2 cups more water.
Stir well. Add carrots, garlic powder, salt and pepper. Simmer until carrots are tender.
Garnish with parsley and add to soup. Serves 6 to 8.

title: dried beef cure
directions: Mix salt, sugar and saltpeter together, mashing all lumps. Divide in 3 portions.
Cut pieces of meat lengthwise with grain so that slices will be crosswise.
These pieces are best if not more than 5 pounds.
Place meat in a large container and rub thoroughly with one portion of the salt mixture.
Follow the same procedure the second and third days.
Turn several times a day and let stand for 7 days.
Then hang in a warm place to drip.
When dripping stops, rub with hickory smoke wash.
Hang in cool place for 6 weeks before slicing.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, onion, 1/2 shredded beef and seasonings. Shape into balls.
Roll in remaining beef.
Chill overnight.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs with 1 stick margarine.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan or Pyrex dish.
Place in refrigerator.

title: mother's tea cakes
directions: Mix well and roll out.
Cut cookies.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: cheese cake
directions: Prepare crust; press in bottom of 9 or 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: butterscotch cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt in saucepan. Gradually stir in water and milk. Add butter.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and boils.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Stir at least half of hot mixture into eggs slowly, then blend with rest of mixture in saucepan.
Boil 1 minute more, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: freeze slaw
directions: Slice or grind the vegetables to desired thinness. Bring to a boil the remaining ingredients and pour over the vegetables.
Put in freezer containers and freeze.
Remove from freezer and let thaw as needed.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage until brown, stirring often.
Drain.
Roll out crescent rolls.
Mix other ingredients, add beaten eggs.
Pour mixture over dough.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: honey dressing
directions: Mix
dry
ingredients.
Add honey, vinegar, lemon juice and onion.
Pour
oil into mixture slowly, beating constantly with rotary or electric beater.
Chill well before serving.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Mix soup, milk, salt, pepper and onion.
In a greased dish layer 1/2 potatoes, soup mixture and 1/2 of sausage.
Repeat.
Cover and bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: lemon sherbet
directions: Grate rind and squeeze lemons.
Mix with sugar.
Add beaten yolk and milk.
Stir well and freeze to mush.
When at mushy stage, add stiffly beaten egg white.
Pour into ice cube tray and freeze.
Makes 1 full tray.

title: best ever bean dip
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Soften cream cheese.
In a large bowl, combine cream cheese, refried beans and taco seasoning.
Mix well. Add chilies, onion, sour cream and salsa.
Mix well after each addition.
Pour into medium baking dish and bake 45 minutes. Remove from oven.
Add cheese to top.
Return to oven and bake an additional 30 minutes.
Serve with tostado chips.

title: cold broccoli salad
directions: For dressing, mix mayonnaise, sugar, and vinegar.
Set in refrigerator to chill.
Layer broccoli, onions, cheese and bacon. Let salad set in refrigerator.
When ready to serve, pour dressing over salad.
Toss to coat and serve.

title: scalloped potatoes with cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Rub an 11 x 7-inch baking dish with cut sides of garlic halves; discard garlic. Coat dish with cooking spray. Arrange half of potatoes in dish and drizzle with half of the butter. Sprinkle with half of salt and half of pepper and top with half of cheese. Repeat the layers. Bring milk to a boil over low heat in a small saucepan; pour over potato mixture. Bake for 40 minutes or until tender. Yields 7 servings.

title: sweet pickled carrots
directions: Slice carrots thick.
Cook in boiling, salted water just until tender, 7 to 8 minutes; drain.
In a large kettle, place remaining ingredients and simmer 20 minutes.
Pack carrots in hot jars. Cover with vinegar mixture.
Process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.
Makes 6 pints.
Carrots may be cut into lengthwise pieces.
Baby carrots may be used.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mash the avocados with a fork.
Add the lemon juice; blend well.
Add remaining ingredients; combine thoroughly.
Serve with warm tostados or king size corn chips.
Yields about 3 cups.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients and then add remainder and mix with electric mixer.
Bake at 350° for approximately one hour.
This usually makes 2 large and one small loaf.

title: nutmeg sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.	Add eggs and beat well.	Add dry ingredients and milk.
Mix well.
Chill 2 hours.
Roll out and cut.
Bake at 325° for about 8 minutes. Decorate with your favorite frosting.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Mix well and refrigerate 24 hours.
Garnish with cherries, if desired.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Skin chicken and roll in flour and salt mixture.
Brown in cooking oil and turn over.
Combine lemonade, 1/2 cup water, brown sugar, catsup and vinegar; pour over chicken in skillet.
Cover and cook over low heat for 30 minutes.
Remove chicken to serving plate and keep warm.
Combine cornstarch and 1 tablespoon water. Gradually add to lemonade mixture, stirring until smooth and cook until thick.
Spoon over chicken.
Serve with rice and green salad.
Great company dish.

title: light rolls
directions: Scald milk; add yeast cake in lukewarm milk.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour, shortening
and
egg
white beaten stiff, then add remaining flour and salt.
Cover
and
let rise one hour, then use just enough flour
to
make out rolls and let rise another hour. Bake in medium oven.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package.
Mix Uncle Ken's and Good Seasons together.
Toss pasta and seasonings.
Sprinkle Parmesan over pasta.
Put pasta on top of vegetables.

title: "the famous peanut butter cookies"
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Take teaspoon of batter and roll into ball.
Put on cookie sheet.
Press with fork dipped in sugar, twice.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 2 to 3 dozen.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in pan. Do not stir.
Mix 1 cup sugar, flour, baking powder, milk and salt together.
Pour over oleo. Do not stir. Pour fruit and juice on top. Do not stir.
Sprinkle with 3/4 cup sugar on
top. Do not stir. Bake at 350°
in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour.

title: beef rouladen
directions: Cut each steak in half and pound to tenderize.
Spread each piece with mustard, salt and pepper.
Place bacon, onion and dill pickle on top.
Roll each steak and secure with a toothpick.
Heat oil in a Dutch oven and brown meat on all sides.
Turn heat down and simmer about 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Combine 2 tablespoons flour with 1/4 cup water.
Add to pan and simmer.
Add sour cream and heat thoroughly.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown beef, bell pepper and onions.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and let simmer 1 hour.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and spread in large size dish. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Mix the next 3 ingredients and pour over first mixture when cooled.
Mix pudding mix and milk; pour over second layer.
Spread Cool Whip over and sprinkle nuts (if desired).
Refrigerate several hours.

title: chicken with cream sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash chicken breasts and place in a baking pan or dish.
Sprinkle onions, garlic powder and Bac*O bits over the top of the chicken breasts.
Drop a spoonful of soup on top and between each piece.
Cover pan with foil or lid.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.
The soup will mix with the juices from the chicken to make a smooth tasty sauce.
Serve with rice, noodles or mashed potatoes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: barbecue rice and beans
directions: Cook and stir onion and pepper in hot oil in saucepan until tender.
Stir in beans, water, barbecue sauce, bouillon cube and garlic powder.
Bring to boil.
Stir in rice and cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fajita rice
directions: Prepare rice as directed on package, omitting margarine and salt.
Heat oil in a large skillet on medium-high heat.
Add meat, onion and garlic.
Cook and stir until meat is browned.
Add peppers.
Cook and stir until tender-crisp.
Stir in water, soy sauce and hot pepper sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat. Stir in lime juice.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked stuffed lobster pie
directions: Place lobster in buttered baking dish.
Mix ingredients, using enough butter to moisten well.
Season with a few drops of either garlic or onion juice.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with lemon wedges.

title: glorified angel cake
directions: Bake or buy angel food cake the day before you want to serve it.
Slice cake across in three layers.
Cook lemon pudding as directed on box, then cool.
Whip cream and mix with cooled pudding.
Spread on each layer, spread and sides on top. Refrigerate cake until ready to serve.

title: three bean salad
directions: Chop green peppers.
Drain beans.
Mix green pepper and beans. Mix sugar, vinegar, salad oil, salt and pepper.
Pour over vegetables and mix well.
Cover and chill.

title: chocolate chip peanut butter cake
directions: Generously grease bottom only of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In large bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, peanut butter and butter or margarine.
Reserve 1 cup.
Add baking powder, soda, milk, vanilla and eggs to remaining crumb mixture.
Blend at low speed until moistened, beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Pour batter into pan. Sprinkle with 1 cup reserved crumbs.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: butter tarts
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Line 24 medium tart tins with pastry. Beat eggs slightly, then beat in sugar, corn syrup, vinegar, vanilla and butter.
Stir in fruit and nuts.
Fill tart shells two-thirds full with mixture; cook about 20 minutes or until set. Cool for a few minutes in pans, then lift out and cool on racks.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine 1 ounce of milk, margarine and cake mix in bowl; mix well.
Spread 1/2 of the mixture into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan and bake for 6 minutes.
Melt caramels and remaining milk in saucepan over low/medium heat.
Layer chocolate chips, coconut flakes and nuts, then drizzle caramel over the top of baked 1/2 of cake mixture.
Spread remaining 1/2 of mixture over the top and bake for 17 to 22 minutes.
(Practice has shown 18 minutes makes a perfect brownie.)

title: turkey and stuffing casserole
directions: Into medium bowl stir together eggs, turkey, gravy and pepper. Turn into well-greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch (2-quart) baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese.
top with stuffing.
Cover.
Bake in 325° oven 25 minutes or until heated through.
Sprinkle with parsley. Let stand 5 minutes.
Serve with turkey gravy.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: walnut bourbon balls(no bake cookies)
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Add corn syrup and bourbon. Mix well.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: curry dip for raw vegetables
directions: Mix in a medium bowl until blended.
Can be made ahead of time.
Refrigerate.
Serve with assorted raw vegetables.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Beat together cream cheese and 1/2 cup sugar until creamy. Blend in 4 1/2 ounces Cool Whip.
Pour in 9-inch graham cracker crust.
Top with cherry pie filling or whatever topping you like. Chill 2 hours.

title: mandarin orange cake and icing
directions: Mix and bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan for approximately 35 minutes.

title: caramel crispy treats
directions: Microwave caramels, margarine and water in qt. container on High for 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes, until smooth, stirring every minute.

title: butter tart square
directions: Mix together and press into 8 x 8-inch ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add cream cheese chunks, applesauce and Cranfruit, mixing well. Add chopped pecans; mix well. Place in 9 x 13 baking dish and chill. Serve with turkey and dressing on holidays.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening. Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour, salt, vanilla and milk. When well blended, stir in nuts. Bake 1 hour, 15 minutes at 350°.

title: face paint
directions: In each cup of the muffin tin, mix 1 teaspoon cornstarch, 1/2 teaspoon water, 1/2 teaspoon cold cream and a couple of drops of food coloring, a different color for each cup.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Mix eggs, shortening and buttermilk. Mix all ingredients together. Store covered in refrigerator. When ready to use, fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 60 muffins.

title: carolina burgers
directions: Grill hamburgers.
Top with mustard, chili, onions and slaw for a genuine Carolina Burger!

title: creamed ham and peas
directions: Melt the butter and mix in the flour, being careful not to burn the mixture.
Add milk and stir constantly, until thickened. Remove from heat and stir in baking powder.
Add ham and peas to the white sauce.
Season as desired.
Reheat and serve with baked potatoes or hot mashed potatoes.
This is also good over toast.

title: asian rice
directions: Cook rice 40 minutes or until done.
Let set 15 minutes.
Add meat and cook together 20 minutes.
Add cabbage.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add salt to taste.
Add peppers; mix and done.

title: sherry beef
directions: Mix all together.
Bake, uncovered, for 3 hours at 325°. Serve over noodles.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together and put in a greased pan. On top of mixture, spread 2 cups corn flakes and 1/4 cup melted butter. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: old fashion sugar cream pie
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch and milk until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Drain pickles.
Make syrup of vinegar, spices and sugars. Bring to a boil and simmer about 5 minutes.
Add pickles and allow to come to a boil.
Let stand 24 hours before putting in jars. Keep in refrigerator.

title: taco pizza dip
directions: Mix sour cream, cream cheese and taco seasoning together; spread on a foil-lined pizza pan. Add toppings. Serve as nacho dip. Keep refrigerated.

title: cabbage lover's special
directions: Put oil in Dutch oven; let it get hot, then add bacon to oil. Brown bacon, then add cabbage, onions and bell peppers.
Add about 1/4 cup of water, then add the Ro-Tel.
Continue to stir and let simmer until vegetables are tender,
as desired.
Add garlic salt to taste.

title: easy fruit dessert
directions: Drain fruit; mix together being careful not to mash.
Add nuts and marshmallows to taste.
Mix Cool Whip and chill.
(I chill cans of fruit first.)

title: no-knead oatmeal bread
directions: Soften yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
In a large bowl, combine the boiling water, the rolled oats, molasses, shortening and salt. Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in 2 cups of the flour.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in softened yeast.
Beat well.
Add remaining flour, 2 cups at a time, mixing well after each addition to make a moderately stiff dough.
Beat vigorously until smooth, about 10 minutes.
Grease top lightly.
Cover tightly.
Place in refrigerator at least 2 hours or overnight.
Turn out on well-floured surface.
Shape in two loaves.
Place in greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double, about 2 hours.
Bake at 375° about 40 minutes.
If crust browns too quickly, cover with foil last half of baking. Makes 2 loaves.

title: strawberry shortcut
directions: Cut cake into 14 slices, about 1/2-inch thick.
Place 7 of the slices on individual dessert plates.
Spoon half of the berries onto the cake slices, allowing about 3 tablespoons for each.
Top with half of the whipping topping, allowing about 4 tablespoons for each.
Repeat layers, ending with a dollop of whipped topping. Makes 7 servings.

title: almond chocolate pie
directions: Fluff up your pies with a silky meringue.
Here's how to whip up one that's a pleasure to serve and eat:

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Boil water.
Remove from stove and add Jell-O to dissolve. Add partially thawed strawberries; stir well.
Add mashed bananas, well drained pineapple and pecans.
Mix well.
Pour 1/2 the mixture into a Jell-O mold.
Chill until set.
Add sour cream on top of that, then the rest of the Jell-O mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and margarine. Add syrup and salt. Beat well. Beat in eggs, one at a time. Add pecans. Pour into shell. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Insert toothpick in the center of pie to check if it is done. If not, cook for 10 minutes longer.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix in a large Tupperware bucket just enough hot water to melt sugar and Kool-Aid.
Add remaining ingredients.
Finish filling container with cold water.
Freezes real good until time to use.

title: apple taffy salad
directions: Heat juice, flour, egg, sugar and vinegar in pan and stir until thick.
Set aside to cool.
Mix apples, half the nuts and Cool Whip.
Then mix with cooled mixture and let set in refrigerator 3 to 4 hours or overnight.
Before putting in refrigerator, sprinkle top with remainder of nuts.

title: beet relish
directions: Put cabbage, beets and red peppers through food chopper. Place in saucepan with vinegar, sugar and salt.
Tie spices loosely in a bag.
Let simmer until beets are tender.
Remove spices and fill hot jars; seal.

title: ambrosia mold
directions: Pour mixture over layers.
Put in refrigerator overnight. Toss when ready to serve.

title: perfect pastry
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Combine all other ingredients.
Sprinkle 4 tablespoons mixture over flour mixture; mix with fork.
Add 4 more tablespoons and continue mixing until pastry holds together.
Gather dough with hands and press into ball.
Wrap in clear plastic.
Wrap; chill 15 minutes. Divide dough into 4 parts.
Roll out between clear plastic wrap. Makes 4 crusts.
Freezes well.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Separate wings; discard tips.
Mix soy sauce, oil, ketchup, honey and garlic.
Place wings in greased baking dish.
Lightly salt and pepper wings.
Pour marinade over.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: chocolate nutty krispies squares
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan (low heat). Add marshmallows; stir until melted. Remove from heat. Stir in Rice Krispies. Fold in chocolate chips and nuts. Place in a lightly greased pan. Let cool; cut into squares.

title: blt chicken salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in
a bowl; mix well. Cover and chill. Combine lettuce, tomatoes and chicken; toss to mix.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in order on low speed, 1/2 minute each. Beat all together on medium speed for 5 minutes.
Pour into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add can of onion rings on top.

title: pistachio salad
directions: In a big mixing bowl, mix all the ingredients together and chill before serving.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients thoroughly in bowl. Sift together in a bowl the flour, soda, cinnamon, ginger, cloves and salt. Mix dry ingredients into first mixture. Chill dough for 2 hours or overnight.

title: basic fish marinade
directions: Stir together oil, juice, garlic, pepper and dill or parsley. Brush on both sides of fish steaks or pour over to marinate.
Let sit on fish 30 minutes at room temperature or refrigerate up to 2 hours.
Grill or broil 4 to 5 minutes on each side or bake in a 350 °oven for 20 minutes or until fish easily flakes when separated with a fork.
Makes enough for 1 to 1 1/2 pounds of fish.

title: asparagus ham roll-ups
directions: Place 3 to 4 spears of asparagus on each ham slice.
Roll up and secure with toothpick. Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Stir in flour and seasonings.
Cook until pasty.
Add milk and stir until thickened.
Add cheese and heat until cheese melts.
Place ham rolls in baking dish.
Pour cheese sauce over top.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: corn dip
directions: Mix all together and serve with crackers.

title: strawberry air delight
directions: Mix. Pour into jelly roll pan. Bake 20 minutes at 300°. Stir every 5 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together.
Makes 8 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Cook chicken; debone and cube.
Mix stuffing mix with butter. Mix each soup with a can of broth.
Layer stuffing, chicken and soup.
Use some stuffing as top layer.
Cook in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hilltop lakes corn dip
directions: Mix all ingredients; cover and refrigerate overnight. Serve with Fritos.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Pour on dressing and dry salad seasoning.
Stir.
Add vegetables and stir.
Chill and serve.

title: kowpot (thai)
directions: Fry bacon.
Saute onion, celery and mushrooms in bacon grease. Place rice in wok or skillet.
Pour in saute mixture and water chestnuts.
Beat 2 eggs.
Add soy sauce, cooked peas and hot peppers.
Serve immediately.

title: nachos
directions: Arrange Doritos on cookie sheets.
Place 1/2 to 1 pepper ring on each.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Broil 2 to 3 minutes, until cheese melts and serve immediately.

title: frozen fruit slush
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze.
Thaw until slushy and serve.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream butter and sugar; add egg and mashed bananas.
Add flour mixture in small amounts.
Mix well each time.
Add oats last.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 11 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Use 1 tablespoon per cup of hot water.

title: low-fat tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: cherokee fry bread
directions: Mix
flour,
baking
powder
and
salt.
Add milk.
Mix well. Working
with
floured
or	greased
hands,
shape into biscuit shapes.
More
flour
may be added to make dough firm. Fry in
hot fat,
enough to cover half the bread as it cooks, turning	once. Bread will be golden brown.
Serve with honey, or
Indian
style with soup, stew or beans.
Around Tahlequah, fry bread
is also the base for "Indian Tacos"; make the dough bigger before
you fry
it
and
top it with traditional taco toppings.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Place dates, orange slices, coconut and pecans in a large bowl.
Coat well with 1/2 cup flour.
Set aside.
Blend shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well.
Mix soda with buttermilk.
Add to shortening mixture.
Blend flour a little at a time.
Add fruit mixture and mix gently.
Pour into greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours or until firm.

title: fudgy pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In saucepan, melt butter or margarine. Add sugar and cocoa; stir until well blended.
Remove from heat; cool.
In medium bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Stir in corn syrup and salt.
Add cocoa mixture; blend well.
Stir in chopped pecans.

title: frozen bread caramel rolls
directions: Don't allow bread to raise, just thaw.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Tear one loaf into pieces and drop into pan.
Bring to boil sugars and margarine.
Cool and pour over dough.
Tear second loaf and throw on top, covering all bare spots.
Raise for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let cool 15 minutes before turning out onto waxed paper.

title: libby's fudge
directions: Bring sugar, evaporated milk and salt to a full boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat and stir constantly for 10 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add butter, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Beat with electric mixer until it loses its gloss.
Add nuts, if desired.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan or dish.

title: walnut-coconut-oatmeal chews
directions: Mix oatmeal, sugar and oil together in large bowl and let stand for several hours in refrigerator.
Add salt, vanilla, beaten eggs, walnuts and coconut.
Mix and drop from a spoon onto baking sheet and pat out with back of spoon.
Bake at 325° until golden brown.

title: potato frosted meat loaf
directions: Combine meat, broth, ketchup, eggs, bread crumbs, celery, onion, parsley, salt and pepper in a large bowl.
Mix well. Press mixture into a lightly greased 6 cup mold or a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour or until loaf shrinks from side of pan.
Remove from oven.
Pour off drippings.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Cut turkey into small pieces.
Prepare stuffing as directed on package.
Put some stuffing on bottom of casserole dish.
Put turkey on top of stuffing.
Pour soups on turkey.
Pour chicken broth on top.
Top with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon ginger flip
directions: Combine the fruit juices and sugar; stir until the sugar is dissolved.
Add ginger ale, lemon rind and ice.
Makes 5 1/2 cups before adding ice.

title: banana crunch bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a medium bowl, combine crushed wafers, sugar, cocoa and vanilla. Stir in 1/2 cup melted butter. Press into bottom of a greased 8-inch square baking pan. Bake for 10 minutes. Cool slightly on a wire rack, about 10 minutes.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Peel and cook potatoes.
Drain.
Beat cream cheese in mixer. Add butter and seasonings.
Add potatoes.
Beat until fluffy.
Add half and half.
When all is mixed, put in casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with parsley and paprika, if desired.
May be frozen.
Keeps well if made ahead of time in fridge.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix and drop batter from small spoon into hot fat.
Turn once. Batter will be thin.
Cook until golden brown.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Mix beans, then add all remaining ingredients.
Drain hamburger before adding.
Mix and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: milky way gems
directions: Combine sugar, brown sugar and ice cream topping in a large skillet.
Cook until sugar dissolves.
Remove from heat and stir in cream cheese until melted. Add vanilla and stir.
Add remaining ingredients. Allow to cool completely.
Roll into balls and then coat with additional nuts or coconut (or mixture of both).

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine and pour over stuffing in bowl.
Stir soup into broth.
Layer 1/3 dressing, 1/2 chicken (deboned), 1/2 broth, continue, ending with stuffing on top.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar in mixing bowl.
Heat butter, cocoa and Coca-Cola to boiling and add to flour and sugar mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda, vanilla and marshmallows. Bake in oblong pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Leave in pan.

title: grandmother's sweet potato pie
directions: Mix sugar with mashed potatoes.
Beat eggs; add soda to buttermilk and mix with eggs.
Add to mashed potatoes and sugar. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells (deep crust).
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then lower to 300° for 60 minutes.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Grease bread loaf pan. In mixing bowl, combine sugar, flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and melted butter. Set aside. Grate the orange rind and add to sugar mixture. Squeeze juice from orange into a measuring cup. Add enough water to make 1 1/4 cups liquid. Add liquid to sugar mixture. Mix well. Add cranberries and nuts until blended. Pour into bread loaf pan. Bake at 350° about 45 to 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: bread sticks
directions: Place bread sticks in shallow pan.
Mix together 1 cup oil and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over bread sticks.
Mix together the remaining seasonings and sprinkle over bread sticks.
Bake at 200° for 1 1/2 hours, turning every 15 minutes.

title: wild rice and chicken salad
directions: Prepare rice as package directs, using 1/2 cup less water. Combine cooled rice and chicken with mayonnaise.
In another bowl, combine artichokes, pimento, celery and peppers with salad dressing.
Mix all ingredients together.
Can be made a day ahead and assembled before serving.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: strawberry torte
directions: Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Add sliced strawberries to mixture.
Slice the pound cake into layers.
Layer the cake with mixture.
Garnish top with additional strawberries.

title: wolf brand chili pie
directions: Layer 2 1/2 cups of corn chips, onion, 1/2 cup cheese and chili in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with remaining corn chips.
Bake for 25 minutes at 375°.
Top with remaining cheese and bake for 5 minutes.
Garnish with sour cream and ripe olives (optional)

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steaks in bite size chunks and brown in skillet.
Once all meat is browned, rinse skillet and add diced peppers and 2 cans soup.
Add 2 cans of water, rinsing soup cans.
Stir in meat.
Add cornstarch to thicken.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Serve over rice or mashed potatoes.

title: picante sauce
directions: Combine and simmer two hours or until desired thickness. Freeze or can.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Mix together and beat well.
Bake in loaf pan at 350°.

title: rum buns
directions: Scald milk and pour into mixing bowl.
Add 1/2 cup sugar, butter and salt.
Mix until butter melts. In a separate bowl, sprinkle the dry yeast into the 1/2 cup warm water.
Add 1/2 teaspoon of sugar and swirl to moisten each granule.
Let rest and proof for 5 minutes.

title: vegetable wedges
directions: Press crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes at 325°.

title: punch
directions: Heat the first 4 ingredients until dissolved. Cool and add remaining ingredients.

title: wonderful cucumber dip
directions: Peel and grate cucumber.
Mash softened cream cheese.
Season to taste.
Serve with Ruffles potato chips.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Mix 1 cup of the flour and salt; add candy and dates into it. Add nuts and coconut.
Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add buttermilk mixture and rest of flour alternately.
Combine with candy mixture.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.
Place pan of water under rack to keep cake moist.

title: prune cake
directions: Beat together first four ingredients.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add butter, milk and dry ingredients to sugar/egg mixture.
Fold in chopped prunes and nuts.
Cook in oven at 350° for 40 minutes in oblong pan.

title: pig-licken cake
directions: Beat cake mix, oil, margarine and eggs for 4 minutes; add juice from oranges.
Mix well.
Cut oranges into small pieces; fold into batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan, well-greased and floured.

title: toffee bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Stir in egg yolk, flour, salt and almond flavor.
Mix well.
Spread in a thin layer on ungreased cookie sheet about thickness of toffee candy.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix sugar and flour; sprinkle sugar and flour mixture over pineapple.
Sprinkle cheese over ingredients.
Mix together butter and crackers.
Place cracker mixture over cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: everything cookies
directions: Mix together oleo, brown sugar, beaten egg, oil and vanilla. Add flour, salt, baking soda and cream of tartar to creamed mixture.
Blend in oatmeal, coconut, Rice Krispies and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: In a very large bowl, crumble cornbread very well. Add remaining ingredients, mixing well. Spray Pam or Wesson oil on the inside of pan. Be careful; will burn easy! Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown and not soupy.

title: sand cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine, beat in remaining ingredients. Make into 3 rolls and place into refrigerator overnight. (May be kept in freezer.)
Slice 1/4 inch thick and bake at 350 degrees approximately 10 minutes.

title: cranberry muffins
directions: Grease the bottoms of muffin pan or use paper baking cups. Sift flour with 1/2 cup of sugar, baking powder and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Put cranberries in another bowl and add remaining 1/2 cup of sugar.

title: easy beef hash
directions: Brown flour in margarine.
Add onion.
Cook a few minutes. Add beef and water.
Cook on low heat about 25 minutes.
Serve over hot biscuits.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Note:
Use 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish or pan.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Bring undiluted cream of shrimp soup to a boil.
Add cream cheese; stir until blended.
Add gelatin.
Let cool until it begins to thicken.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour into mold and refrigerate overnight before serving with crackers.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Melt oleo or butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add 1/2 cup sugar to fruit and heat to boiling.
Mix 1 cup sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk in mixing bowl.
Remove baking dish from oven, pour crust mixture over oleo and top with hot fruit.
Return to 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Good hot or cold.

title: pizza dip(italian hors d'oeuvre)
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients and spread into a quiche pan.
Top with the remaining ingredients.
Either bake 15 minutes at 350° or microwave 3 to 5 minutes on High until the cheese bubbles.
Serve with chips.

title: quick and easy marinated mushrooms
directions: Boil mushrooms until cooked.
Place in glass bowl.
Cover with Italian dressing and marinate for 24 to 48 hours, turning occasionally.

title: bananas foster
directions: On medium heat, melt margarine and brown sugar.
Add sliced bananas and cook, 3 to 4 minutes, stirring gently.
Remove from heat.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Stir gently.
Immediately serve over ice cream.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix and drop in deep fat.
Fry until brown.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs well, then add sugar, salt, vanilla and nutmeg.
Add scalded milk, a little at a time, beating fast.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 28 to 30 minutes.
Pie is done when knife comes out clean.
Makes 2 large or 4 small pies.

title: fudge sundae pie
directions: Put milk, morsels, marshmallows and salt into a heavy, 1-quart saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until chocolate and marshmallows melt completely and mixture thickens.
Take off heat.
Cool to room temperature.
Line bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie pan or 2 (1-quart) ice trays with vanilla wafers.
Spoon half of vanilla ice cream over the vanilla wafers.
Cover with 1/2 of the chocolate mixture.
Repeat with rest of the ice cream and chocolate.
Toast pecan halves and decorate on top.
Freeze 3 to 5 hours.
So rich; it serves 8 to 10.

title: callie's best-ever chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat shortening together until fluffy.
Add both brown & white sugar. Beat until well blended. Beat in eggs and vanilla. Set aside.

In separate bowl, sift together flour, baking soda, salt, instant pudding mix. Gradually add to wet mixture. Stirring well. Stir in chocolate chips. Drop by tablespoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 - 12 minutes. Cool on sheet for 1 minute, then remove to wire rack.

title: claret lemonade
directions: Combine sugar and lemon juice, stirring until sugar dissolves. Add wine and sparkling water.
Serve over ice.
Yields 4 cups.

title: aunt sue's fut nudge
directions: Shook the kugar, the chilk, the mawkolet and the surn-keerup until the mawkolet chelts.
Stoil withoub burring to 234 degees of greet.
Then dairfully crop a little of the mott mixture into a wawt of cold cupper, if little bawft sawly form in the cuttom of the bopp, the dudge is sun.
Remove the hann from the peat-bad the udder let canned until stool and fladd the aivoring.
Speat with a boon until gick and thooey, nopp in the druts, empty into buttered pun and squark in mairs.
You may marshy add mellows if you have a teet swooth.
Serves a gruzzen doan-ups or two bean-aged toys.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix shortening, peanut butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar and egg.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill 1 hour.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Press crushed pretzels, 4 tablespoons sugar and 1 stick melted margarine in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 325°.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except almonds and butter; spread in pie tin.
Melt butter.
Add almonds.
Sprinkle over mixture.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Yield:
2 cups.
Carbohydrate 1 g, protein 1 g, fat 5 g, calories per serving 53.
One tablespoon = 1 fat exchange.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer one at a time in 9 x 13-inch serving dish the spinach, lettuce, bacon, eggs, peas, salt, pepper, sugar, onion and carrots.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until brown, then turn oven to 250° and bake for about 1 hour.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in refrigerator overnight before serving.

title: party turnovers(meat pies)
directions: Cut each package of crescent rolls into 16 triangles.
Brown ground meat with 1 package Lipton onion soup mix.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 package shredded sharp Cheddar cheese and stir together.
Spoon one teaspoon meat mixture onto crescent triangle. Fold over ends (like a diaper).
Pinch the middle down.
Bake at 350° for five to ten minutes, until golden brown.
Serve warm. Yields 48 Party Turnovers.

title: quick spicy shrimp cocktail
directions: In a large saucepan, bring beer and seasoning to a boil.
Add shrimp. Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 3 to 4 minutes, stirring occasionally, until shrimp are opaque.
Remove shrimp with slotted spoon to a 9 x 9-inch metal pan.
Add 1 cup beer mixture. Cover with plastic wrap and place in freezer 5 minutes to cool.

title: custard pie
directions: Cream sugar, flour and butter together.
Beat in eggs 1 at a time.
Add sweet milk, salt and vanilla.
Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°; reduce heat to 350° and finish baking.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.

title: italian zucchini crescent pie
directions: Spread 1 can of crescent rolls on a large pie pan to form crust.
Spread mustard over crust.
Sauce onion in butter for 10 minutes; remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients, mix and pour into pie shell.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes at 375°.
Even better reheated the second day!

title: janice's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients except catsup. Boil for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat. Add catsup.
Mix well. Yields 1 gallon.

title: hot cider
directions: Combine ingredients in large boiler (or crock pot) and heat at low temperature for about 3 hours.
Serve hot.
Makes 12 servings.

title: savory cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Gently press crust in bottom and 1-inch up sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake for 5 minutes; remove from oven.
Reduce oven to 350°.

title: cheesy new potatoes
directions: Cover potatoes with water and bring to a boil; reduce heat and cook 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain potatoes and cool slightly.
Stir in butter and pepper; toss lightly.
Spoon half of potato mixture into a lightly greased 3-quart casserole dish.
Top with half each of the bacon and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Garnish with parsley.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: You will need a 9-inch glass pie plate.

title: bisque a la crab
directions: In saucepan, cook celery with chervil in butter until tender. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat until everything is well blended, stirring now and then.
Do not allow soup to boil.
(Can substitute mushrooms for shrimp or even use canned crab meat instead of frozen.
It's still wonderful!)
Serves 4.

title: fruit salad with honey-wine syrup
directions: Stir wine, orange juice and honey until well blended.
Add canteloup and mix.
Toss gently and refrigerate for 4 hours or overnight.
Before serving, add strawberries, cut in half or quarters.
Serve cold.

title: one hour biscuits
directions: Mix, roll out and cut like any other biscuit.
Turn over in grease.
Let rise about 1/2 hour.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 2 pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: crustless mushroom quiche
directions: Combine milk, melted margarine and bread.
Set aside.
Saute onion and mushrooms.
Cool.
Add eggs, cheese, salt and pepper to cooked mixture.
Combine all ingredients.
Place in pie plate, sprayed with non-oil baking spray.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes, until lightly browned and knife comes out clean.

title: corn dogs
directions: Combine corn meal, flour and salt.
Add milk, egg and oil; mix well.
Insert wooden sticks into hot dogs.
Coat with additional flour; dip into corn meal mixture.
Deep fry a few at a time in deep hot oil (375°) until golden brown.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Put flour, spices, salt and pepper in paper bag.
Pour oil into bottom of baking pan.
Put chicken pieces, 3 or 4 at a time, into bag of flour and spices; shake bag to coat.
Arrange chicken pieces, skin side down, in pan.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes, turn pieces and bake 15 minutes longer, until golden brown and tender.

title: pizza hors d'oeuvres
directions: Fry sausage and drain.
Meanwhile, melt cheese in top of double boiler, then add sausage and stir in rest of ingredients, except rye bread.
Spread mixture on rye bread.
Put on cookie sheet and freeze.
When frozen, put in containers or Baggies and keep frozen.

title: "3 minute lemon pie"
directions: Empty 2 cans of sweetened condensed milk into glass bowl. Stir with whisk.
Add ReaLemon to taste a little at a time (as tart as preferable).
Mixture will thicken somewhat.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Place in refrigerator.
Before serving, generously top with Cool Whip.

title: cheesy corn bake
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: whipped cornmeal with okra
directions: Combine water and okra in a 3-quart saucepan. Bring to boil gently and cook 10 minutes. Remove okra with slotted spoon and set aside. Raise heat until water comes to brisk boil and add cornmeal in thin steady stream, stirring constantly to prevent lumping. Add salt and okra and cook about 10 minutes more. Remove from heat and add butter 1 piece at a time, stirring after each addition until all butter is incorporated. Keep stirring until okra has practically disappeared and cornmeal is light. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Serve hot. Serves 4.

title: ginny's cheesecake
directions: In bowl, combine graham cracker crumbs and 1/3 cup butter; blend, then add cinnamon, pecans and 1 1/4 cups sugar.
Blend again.
Press mixture on bottom and sides of buttered spring-form pan.
Set aside.

title: sourdough starter
directions: To begin your starter, mix the 1 c. sugar, dry yeast, 6 Tbsp. instant potatoes and warm water in a glass jar, cover with paper towel and rubber band.
Let stand at room temperature for 48 hours. Remove desired amount for baking and store remainder in the refrigerator.

title: miniature fruit cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Use food processor to chop fruits and nuts.
Use small cupcake pan.
Spray well with Baker's Joy. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Turn onto wax paper when removed from oven.
Makes approximately 40 small cakes.

title: texas hash
directions: Heat oven to 350°f. 180°c. gas mark 4. In a large skillet, cook and stir meat, onion and green pepper until the meat is brown and the vegetables are tender. Drain off the fat and stir in tomatoes, rice, salt, chili powder and pepper; heat through. Pour into an ungreased 2 qt.
casserole, cover and bake for 1 hour. 4-6 Servings.

title: 7 layer casserole
directions: Put into layers in casserole dish the potatoes, carrots, rice, onion, peas and Spam.
Over these 6 layers, pour tomatoes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook the chopped broccoli and onion together until tender. Drain the broccoli and then mix all the ingredients together. Pour into a baking dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tomato vinaigrette
directions: Stir together and chill.
Slice tomatoes for serving 4 to 6 people.
Pour the mixture over just before serving.

title: anna's beet soup(to my mother)
directions: Peel 3 to 5 medium beets, cover with water and add 1/2 tablespoon salt.
Boil on medium heat until tender (easily poked with fork).
Remove beets from soup, cut into cubes.
Add cubes and sliced beet leaves to the soup and boil until leaves lose green color.
Remove from heat.
At room temperature, add 2 teaspoons lemon concentrate.
Chill.

title: chinese beef casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain excess fat.
Add celery and onions and continue simmering.
Stir in soups and sauce.
Fold in noodles. Pour into casserole dish and bake for 30 to 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: clara's fresh apple cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs.
Set aside.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add to moist mixture.
Stir in nuts and apples.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 glass pan.
Sprinkle with butterscotch morsels.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: salad wraps
directions: Dice cucumber, tomatoes, and pepper.
Mix with peas.
Mince basil and add to mixture.
Spread mixture onto lettuce leaf and roll up.
Secure with toothpicks and serve.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and beat until creamy.
Sift flour and dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with milk. Add vanilla.
Lastly add rhubarb.
Put topping on cake after batter is in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together.
Roll into balls; flatten and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: baked cream corn
directions: Chop up corn; add mixture of whipping cream, 3 unbeaten egg whites, salt and pepper.
Butter a casserole dish; sprinkle with parsley, if you wish.
Pour in corn mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until it sets.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add buttermilk.
In another bowl, add flour, salt, sugar and soda.
To this, add the yeast, buttermilk and shortening.
Knead lightly; shape into biscuits. Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: mississippi mud bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease only bottom of 9 X 13 inch pan.
In a large bowl combine all brownie ingredients.
Beat 50 strokes by hand.
Spread in greased pan.
Bake for 33-35 minutes. DO NOT OVERBAKE!
Cool completely.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion.
Drain off liquid.
Melt margarine and combine with all other ingredients.
Pour into a greased baking dish and bake in a 350° oven 35 minutes.

title: cherry yum-yum
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with margarine.
Save 1/2 cup crumbs for top.
Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Mix Dream Whip with milk and vanilla.
Line pan with cracker mix.
Add cheese mixture, then cherries.
Top with Cool Whip.
Best to let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: old fashion german dressing
directions: Use large mixing container to mix all items.
Add extra water to the mixture so it will be extra moist.
Mix with a potato masher.
Pour in greased roaster and place another stick of butter on top.
Bake at 350° until cooked as you like.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Drop cabbage leaves into boiling hot water and let stand until softened.
Combine ground beef, rice, parsley, salt and pepper. Mix well and form into balls (12).
Roll meatballs into softened cabbage leaves and fasten with toothpicks.

title: stuff cabbage
directions: Remove leaves from cabbage; set aside.
Cook beef, onion, garlic, salt, pepper and 1 cup diced cabbage until brown, about 15 minutes.
Stir in rice and 1 cup sauce; remove from heat.
Fill cabbage leaves with beef.
Roll and cook.

title: fried eggplant - medium spicy(from india)
directions: Cut eggplant into 4 long quarters, then into 1/2-inch slices (pie shaped).
Mix dry ingredients together and sprinkle evenly over slices of eggplant.
Heat oil in frying pan and fry single layer of eggplant until golden-red on each side.
Remove and blot on paper towel.
Do the next batch.
Add oil as needed.
Serve with lemon wedges.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Mix dry onion and wine together; let set for 5 minutes.
Drain. Soften cream cheese; blend with Miracle Whip.
Cut up and mix beef and olives with the cheese mixture.
Put into large butter or Cool Whip container which has been sprayed with Pam.
Put in refrigerator for 12 or more hours.
Serve at room temperature on crackers, chips or large Fritos.

title: german farmer's breakfast
directions: In a large skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon from skillet.
Drain on paper towels.
Reserve 3 Tbsp. drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Cook green onion and green pepper in reserved drippings until tender.
Blend flour, sugar, celery seeds, 1/4 tsp. salt and dash pepper.
Stir in water and vinegar.
Stir constantly over medium-high heat until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Fold in potatoes, bratwurst and pimento. Heat until bubbly.
Reduce heat and keep hot while scrambling eggs.
In a large skillet, melt butter or margarine over medium heat.
Mix eggs with milk, 1/2 tsp. salt and dash pepper.
Add to skillet.
Cook over medium heat, lifting edges of egg mixture so uncooked portion flows underneath.
When eggs are cooked throughout but still glossy and moist, remove from skillet and place on a heated platter.
Top with hot potato mixture.
Garnish with crumbled bacon and snipped parsley, if desired.
Serves 6-8.

title: apple mallow yam bake
directions: Toss apples and nuts with combined brown sugar and cinnamon. Alternate layers (begin with yams) in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Dot with margarine.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Sprinkle marshmallows on top.
Heat until lightly browned.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Blend sugar, butter and flour.
Beat in beaten eggs.
Add buttermilk, coconut and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. (Double recipe for 2 pies.)

title: shrimp terrine seaside
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Line an 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan with enough foil to completely cover the top of the loaf.
Oil the foil.

Place the shrimp in the bowl of a food processor; process until smooth, stopping frequently to scrape the sides of the bowl. Add the egg whites, chives, onions, dill weed, salt and pepper; process until the mixture resembles a thick paste.
With the processor running, gradually add the cream.
Process for 1 minute.

title: spiced peaches
directions: Drain peaches, reserving syrup.
Combine syrup, cornstarch and remaining ingredients in a small Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat; add peaches and simmer 1 minute.
Let cool 30 minutes; chill.

title: tangy pecan-orange cranberry relish
directions: Grind oranges and cranberries in a food grinder, using medium blade, or chop medium fine in a food processor.
Stir in 2 cups of granulated sugar.
Refrigerate several hours or longer.
Makes 2 pints.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Cream milk with beater.
Add blueberries, pineapple and pecans.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust and refrigerate overnight before serving.
Makes 2 pies.

title: clam chowder(soup)
directions: Saute onion, celery and green pepper in oleo or butter.
Add potatoes, boiling water and salt; cover and cook until potatoes are tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
(I add some diced carrots for color.)
Heat to boiling point serve.

title: grapenut pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Pour scalded milk over Grapenuts; let set for 10 minutes in a warm place.
Beat egg and sugar together. Stir into cooled Grapenuts mixture.
Add salt, vanilla and melted shortening.
Bake in a slow 300° oven for about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: linguini salad
directions: Boil linguini for 12 minutes in large kettle.
Drain well.
Cut up all ingredients.
Mix all together well.
Let set overnight.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Melt butter and pour over crushed saltine crackers.
Spread over casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: creamy mocha frozen dessert
directions: In small bowl, dissolve coffee granules in hot water; set aside.
In another bowl, combine the cookie crumbs, 1/2 cup pecans and butter.
Pat into bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
In bowl, beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Blend in coffee, milk and chocolate syrup.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread over crust. Sprinkle remaining pecans on top and freeze until firm.

title: shanty beans
directions: Wash beans, then put in 5-quart kettle.
Add beans and water to top; add bacon that has been cut into 1-inch pieces.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours, then add the brown sugar and cook 1/2 hour longer, or until beans are soft.

title: upper crust chicken
directions: Trim crust from bread; reserve crusts.
Cut bread diagonally into quarters.
Cut crusts into cubes.
Combine bread cubes, chicken, celery and cheese.
Mix well.
Spoon into 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Arrange bread quarters over mixture. Combine mayonnaise, eggs and seasonings.
Mix well.
Add milk. Pour over bread.
Cover.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Heat potatoes.
Add all ingredients, saving 1/2 cup brown sugar and nuts.
Place in baking dish.
Top with brown sugar and chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine all ingredients except corn in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove mixture from heat; pour over popcorn (in roaster pan) and mix well.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, checking and stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven; stir immediately.
Stir occasionally while mixture cools.
Store in airtight container.
Yields 2 quarts.

title: wederah's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine butter, the sugars, vanilla and pudding mix in a large mixer bowl; beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in chips and nuts (batter will be stiff).
Drop by teaspoons about 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Chop cucumbers, onion and peppers.
Sprinkle with salt.
Place in refrigerator 8 hours or overnight.
Wash and drain.
Boil vinegar, sugar and spices.
Add cucumber mixture.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Seal in jars.

title: dobash frosting
directions: Soften cornstarch with a little of the 1 cup water.
In a saucepan, melt
the
chocolate
in the remaining water.
Add sugar and
butter,
stirring
until
dissolved.
Add the cornstarch mixture; boil until it thickens.
Makes enough frosting for a 9 x 13-inch cake.

title: upside-down hot fudge cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Stir in oil and vanilla.
Put in 9-inch square pan.

title: microwave truffles
directions: Bring all to a soft boil.
Remove from heat.
As mixture firms, roll into small balls and roll in favorite topping (1/2 c. chopped roasted nuts, 1/4 c. coconut, instant mocha, etc.).

title: after school cookies
directions: Thoroughly
cream
shortening
and sugars; add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Add oatmeal and nuts; mix well.
Shape in rolls;
wrap in waxed paper and chill overnight.	Slice
inch
thick
and
bake
on	an ungreased cookie sheet in a moderate 350° oven for 10 minutes. Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: pumpkin sheet cake
directions: Mix oil, eggs and pumpkin.
Add dry ingredients and mix well. Bake 20 minutes in 15 x 10-inch pan at 350°.

title: german potato salad
directions: Chop and saute bacon.
Add onion to bacon just before the bacon is done and cook.
Remove from heat.
Drain off excess grease and discard.
In a separate pot, bring to a boil, vinegar, salt and sugar.
Dissolve flour into water and add to dressing. Add bacon and onion to dressing.
Pour over potatoes, which have been cut into bite-size pieces.

title: warm sue bee brownies(honey blonde brownies)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Spread into well-greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, but only until a slight imprint shows when touched with finger. Don't overbake.
Before cooling, cut into bars.

title: nana's crock pot candy
directions: Layer ingredients in a slow cooker in the order listed.
Cook on low for 1 hour then stir.
Cook on low 1 hour more.
Spoon out by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let cool. Makes 5 pounds.

title: zucchini au gratin
directions: Blanch zucchini in boiling salted water for 8 minutes; drain. Cut slice off top, lengthwise.
Scoop out flesh, leaving 1/4-inch rim around edge.
Roughly chop flesh and top slices.
Turn shells upside down to drain.
Fry onion in 1/2 butter until light brown. Add chopped zucchini; cook on high a few minutes.
Add corn; season well.
Place zucchini shells in shallow, ovenproof dish; fill with corn mixture.

title: rhonda's pecan fingers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream margarine/butter and confectioners sugar.
Blend in 1 1/2 cups flour.
Press evenly in bottom of ungreased baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mary's chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening until soft.
Add sugars one at a time.
Cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Sift the flour, salt and baking soda together.
Add the sifted dry ingredients. Add the package of Nestle's after the ingredients are mixed.
Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 7 minutes.

title: pimento peppers
directions: Bring to a boil and pour over cooked pimento peppers.
Seal in jars.

title: bistek (philippine style steak)
directions: Marinate the meat in lemon juice, soy sauce, pepper and salt for 3 hours or more.
Cook onion rings in oil until transparent. Transfer to a serving dish, leaving the oil in the skillet.
Add the meat to the skillet and cook over high heat, stirring often, until tender.
Transfer the meat to a serving dish.
Add marinade and water to the skillet.
Simmer for 10 minutes and pour over the meat and onion rings.
Serves 4.

title: fried oysters
directions: Drain oysters; mix eggs, milk and seasonings.
Dip oysters in egg mixture and roll in crumbs.
Fry in deep fat (375°) about 2 minutes or until brown.
Or fry in shallow fat about 2 minutes on one side; turn and brown on other side.

title: okra creole
directions: Saute onion in bacon drippings; add frozen okra.
Cover and cook 5 minutes or until unfrozen.
Add remaining ingredients except corn.
Stir together and cook on low, 35 to 45 minutes, stirring often.
Add corn last 10 minutes of cooking time.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix all ingredients; bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: super wheat germ cookies
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Combine eggs, oil, molasses and raisins.
Add to dry ingredients and mix.
Spoon cookie size onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.

title: caramels
directions: Combine; stir constantly.
Boil to 248°.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet (with sides).
Cut when cool.
Wrap in waxed paper.

title: chocolate chip pecan waffles
directions: Sift together dry ingredients. Combine egg yolks, butter and milk.
Stir into dry ingredients.
Fold in egg whites leaving a few fluffs.
Sprinkle chips and pecans over batter in waffle maker.
Bake.
Makes 3 (10-inch) waffles.

title: asparagus with water chestnuts
directions: Heat oil in large skillet. Add asparagus and garlic. Cover; stir now and then. Tender in 5 to 7 minutes. Add chestnuts 2 to 3 minutes before removing from fire (just long enough to heat).

title: fruit delight salad
directions: Mix all together and cool in refrigerator.
Add back as much saved juice as necessary.
Can make the night before.

title: beef-zucchini stroganoff
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet until beef loses its pink color.
Add mushroom soup, water, noodles, zucchini and seasoning (basil).
Simmer covered until noodles are done.
Stir in sour cream.
This is a quick meal all in one pan.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain. Chop green onions, cucumber and bell pepper. Mix all ingredients together. Let set overnight in the refrigerator.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Mince and brown the onion in butter.
Add the ground beef and salt. Add more butter, if needed.
Mix together the remaining ingredients.
Skim fat from meat.
Combine to mixture and simmer. Serve on hot dogs.

title: quick banana cake
directions: Combine eggs, oil, and water with mashed bananas.
Add cake mix.
Beat on medium speed for 5 minutes.
Put in two 9-inch round pans or one 9-inch x 13-inch that have been greased with Crisco and sprinkled with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Put chicken in bottom of baking dish sprayed with Pam and add Veg-All.
Mix soup, broth, and onions; pour over chicken.
Add chopped eggs.
Mix flour, milk and melted butter; pour over top. Bake for 1 hour at 375 degrees.

title: cornbread stuffing
directions: Boil whole chicken until done.
Cut chicken up and add with cornbread.

title: meat loaf
directions: Make sauce.
Combine tomato sauce and A.1. sauce.
Mix half of sauce with ground beef and other ingredients.
Put the other half of the sauce on top.
Bake at 400°.

title: momma's pie crust
directions: Sift flour and salt; cut in Crisco.
Beat water, egg and vinegar together.
Stir into flour mixture.
Turn out on floured board.
Roll to fit pan.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes in 425° oven. Makes 2 crusts.

title: corn-zucchini bake
directions: Slice zucchini about 1-inch thick.
Cook until tender; drain and mash with fork.
Cook onion in the first tablespoon butter until tender.
Combine beaten eggs, mashed zucchini, onion, corn, Swiss cheese and salt.
Turn into 1-quart casserole dish.
Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and second tablespoon butter. Sprinkle on top of corn mixture and bake on baking sheet for 40 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving. Garnish with chopped fresh tomatoes.

title: chicken and vegetable bake
directions: In a 1/2-quart casserole dish, mix soup, milk, vegetables, chicken 1/2 cup of cheese, Worcestershire sauce and 1/2 can of fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes; stir.
Sprinkle on top the rest of the French fried onions; bake 5 more minutes.

title: louise's pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Grease and flour tube pan or bundt pan. beat sugar, butter and crisco until fluffy. Add eggs one at a time beating after each one. Add lemon and vanilla. Add milk and flour alternately, beating after each addition ending with flour. Bake one hour and 15 minutes. Cool in pan 15 minutes before inverting.

title: shoepeg corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Pour half in greased 12 x 9 x 2-inch pan, then sprinkle with mixture of brown sugar and cinnamon. Pour remaining cake batter over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
While baking, mix frosting.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place cooked rice on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Saute celery and onion in small amount of butter.
Add soup to celery and onions.
Add broccoli to rice; pour soup mixture on top of broccoli and top with Cheez Whiz.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: debbie's baked chicken
directions: Wash and skin meat.
Melt butter.
Dip chicken in butter. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and Season-All.
Roll in cracker crumbs.
Bake, covered with foil, for 45 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine apple slices and 1 cup sugar in bottom of 2-quart casserole.
Mix butter, oats, flour, brown sugar and walnuts. Sprinkle butter-oat mixture over apple combination.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 1 hour or until topping is browned and apples are tender.
Serve warm, plain or topped with a small spoonful of ice cream.

title: bullfrogs
directions: Whip together in blender.
You can also add 1/2 package of frozen strawberries.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter until soft.
Add salt, toss well. (Onions should be golden brown, not dark.)
Add hot bouillon and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Ladle into heat-proof soup bowls.
Top each with piece of toasted French bread.
Spoon about 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese on top of each.
Bake in preheated oven 10 minutes at 300°.

title: karo pecan pie
directions: Beat together all except pecans and flour which have been combined.
Add pecans and flour last.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° until firm.
If crust starts to brown too quickly, fold foil around edges.

title: mounds cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box in a 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Leave in pan.
When cooled, mix together the creme of coconut and Eagle Brand milk.
Punch holes in cooled cake with handle of wooden spoon.
Pour mixture of coconut creme and milk over cake, then spread bowl of whipped cream over cake.
Then sprinkle coconut all over top of that.

title: dragon dream pops
directions: Puree peaches, undrained pineapple and bananas in blender. Pour into popsicle molds.
Freeze until firm.
Yields 20 servings.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Wash raisins, cover with water.
Add cloves and simmer 10 minutes.
Add orange juice and vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Add brown sugar, cornstarch and butter.
Cook until slightly thickened.
Serve as hot sauce with ham.
Any left over may be frozen.

title: fruit punch bars
directions: Grease and flour bottom of 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan. Beat eggs and sugar in large bowl at high speed until light and fluffy.
Add fruit cocktail, flour, soda, salt and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed until well blended, scraping sides of bowl and bottom of bowl.
Spread in pan.
Sprinkle with coconut and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
While hot, drizzle with glaze.

title: pork supreme
directions: Brown pork pieces in margarine in an electric frying pan. Take pork out and set aside.
Add the soup and 1 can of water to pan; stir.
Return pork to pan; simmer until done.
Serve with yellow rice.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Stir in water and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in gelatin.
Pour over strawberries and mix well.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Refrigerate until set.
When set, spread Cool Whip or whipped cream on top.

title: wild rice
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 6-cup casserole dish.
Place all ingredients except 1 cup broth in the dish and cover tightly. Bake 1 1/2 hours, adding more broth if necessary.
Serves 6 generously.

title: potato and pepper casserole
directions: Melt butter with milk; do not boil.
Grate or grind potatoes, pepper and onion.
Put into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour on milk.

title: dutch meat loaf
directions: Combine.
Pour over meat loaf.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours longer, basting occasionally.
Serve with a hot sauce.
Will serve 6.

title: ladyfingers
directions: Cream butter, sugar, flour, pecans and vanilla; mix well with hands.
Roll into little fingers (don't let them touch in pan). Place in refrigerator for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Blend butter, sugar, flour, salt and eggs, beating well.
Stir in corn and milk.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes, stirring once.

title: posh nosh gazpacho
directions: To peel tomatoes:
Bring a large pot of water to a boil.
Add tomatoes; immerse for 30 seconds.
Remove tomatoes from pot; peel.

title: sweet-and-sour red cabbage and apple salad
directions: In a
large heatproof bowl, combine the cabbage, apple, green pepper and onion and toss well to mix; set aside.

title: miniature cheese cakes
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, vanilla and lemon juice.
Add softened cream cheese; beat with mixer until light and fluffy.
Line muffin pans with paper muffin cups.
Place a vanilla wafer in the bottom of each cup.
Fill cups 2/3 full with cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until set.
Let stand 5 minutes. You can serve as is or top with your favorite jam.

title: chateaubriand with bearnaise sauce
directions: Marinate beef in Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper for at least 2 hours.
Prepare charcoal grill.
Thirty minutes before ready to serve, sear meat for 5 minutes on each side.
Move off coals and cover grill; cook for at least 20 minutes more for medium rare.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients (except cheese) together and pour into pan.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: instant hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix ingredients in large container and seal.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Pour rice mixture into casserole dish.
Pour onion soup and 1 can water over rice and mix it up.
Cover this mixture with chicken pieces.
Pour mushroom soup and 1 can water over chicken and rice.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes to 1 1/2 hours, depending on your oven.

title: coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: sausage and noodle dish
directions: Mix all except noodles and sausage; heat until cheese is melted.
Cook noodles and drain.
Fry pork sausage and drain. Combine mixture and turn into greased casserole.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: red chicken stew
directions: Boil chicken and salt and pepper.
Save stock.
Remove chicken from bones.
Boil stock.
Add onions, catsup, Worcestershire sauce and hot sauce.
Simmer.
Add chicken and continue to simmer until thick enough to serve over rice.
Add more hot sauce if desired. Total cooking time is about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
You can also use 1/2 tomato sauce and 1/2 catsup.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces. Add to 2 quarts water and chicken broth. Bring to boil. Add sausage and vegetables. Mix gumbo mix with 2 quarts cold water. Add to chicken mixture. Simmer 1 hour. Add shrimp when almost done, if desired.

title: marshmallow cream fudge
directions: Combine in pan and bring to boil over moderate heat the first 5 ingredients, stirring occasionally.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate morsels and stir until melted.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
Yields about 2 1/4 pounds.

title: shrimp onion dip
directions: In a small mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill.
Serve with assorted fresh vegetables or potato chips.
Refrigerate.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except chiles and cheese.
Pour half of batter into 9-inch square greased pan.
Spread chiles and cheese on evenly.
Then pour remaining batter on top.

title: jenny's sugar cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in butter as for pie crust with knives.
Add egg and vanilla and mix thoroughly.
Form into balls. Flatten with a small glass dipped in granulated sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet about 10 minutes or until lightly browned at 400°.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Fry sausage; drain.
Mix chopped onions, celery soup mix, hot water, soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Place rice in bottom of 2-quart casserole, then the sausage.
Pour the soup and vegetable mixture over the sausage.
Place finely sliced almonds on top (optional).
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Stir well. Saute some more almonds and place on top.
Return to oven for an additional 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: old-time beef stew
directions: Brown meat in 2 tablespoons hot shortening.
Add 2 cups hot water and next 9 ingredients.
Cover; simmer for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally to keep from sticking.
Remove bay leaves and garlic.
Add vegetables.
Cover and cook 30 to 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: chocolate fruit dip
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients except fruit.
Stir with a wire whisk until smooth.
Cover; refrigerate at least 1 hour or until well chilled.
Serve with assorted fruit for dipping.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: texas cheese log
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except chili powder, and form into a large ball.
Chill until firm.
Roll in chili powder to cover.
Serve with crackers.
This cheese log can be frozen.

title: turkey and broccoli stroganoff
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Saute turkey, mushrooms, onion and pepper until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add chicken broth and nutmeg. Bring to a boil, simmer 5 minutes.
Combine yogurt and flour until smooth.
Stir into turkey mixture.
Boil over medium heat 1 minute.
Stir in broccoli and wine.
Heat through.
Serve over noodles.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Boil
chicken
with just enough water to cover chicken. Debone and
cut
up
in
pieces.
Skim
off fat from broth and return cut up chicken to broth.
Add celery, potatoes, chicken bouillon, carrots
and onion to broth.
Cook until vegetables are tender. Then
add
soup,
sour cream, evaporated milk and egg noodles. Mix together.
Do not boil.

title: avocado soup
directions: Place avocados, cream and broth in a blender and puree them along with all the seasonings except the lemon juice.
Cool for several hours.
Add lemon juice just before serving.

title: peach almond jam
