directions: In 6 to 8-quart pot, combine first 4 ingredients and heat to rolling boil for 1 minute.
Stir constantly and add last 2 ingredients.
Skim the foam off top with metal spoon and ladle into hot jars allowing 1/4-inch head room.
Cover and process 5 minutes in boiling water bath.
Yields 8 jars at 8-ounce size.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Roll in small balls lightly.
Press down with base of glass buttered and dipped in sugar.
Bake 10 minutes, approximately, at 350°.

title: venison chop suey
directions: Cook venison in butter (do not brown). Add onion, celery, molasses and soy sauce. Cook 5 minutes. Drain sprouts.
Reserve juice.
Mix starch and bean juice and slowly add to meat.
Mix and cook until thick.
Add bean sprouts.
Heat and serve over rice or noodles.

title: scampi and pasta
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Cook garlic and green onion 30 seconds.
Add shrimp and cook until shrimp turn pink, 3 to 4 minutes.
Sprinkle with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Add basil, parsley and red pepper.
Meanwhile, cook pasta.
Pour sauce over pasta; toss and serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Combine the consomme and water.
In casserole dish (oblong), pour rice, then the mixture of soup and water.
Salt chops, also black pepper, place on top.
Cover with foil and place in preheated oven of 350° and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
About 15 minutes prior to time of baking, uncover for browning.

title: best pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta; drain and cool.
Mix pasta with all other ingredients.
Chill.
Best if chilled overnight.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sherried rice(side dish)
directions: Grate onion.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Pour into casserole.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Mix one-half way through.

title: cheese twists
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt into a medium sized bowl. Cut in butter with a pastry blender until crumbly.
Sprinkle water over.
Mix lightly with fork just until mixture holds together and leaves sides of bowl.
Roll out on lightly floured pastry cloth or board to a 12 x 10-inch rectangle.
Divide in half lengthwise, then cut each half crosswise into 1/2-inch wide strips.
Lift strips one at a time.
Twist a couple turns and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash the avocados with lemon juice, salt and pepper; set aside.
Combine the sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
For best effect, use a glass bowl with straight sides. To assemble:
spread the bean dip over the bottom of bowl.
Over that, layer the avocado mixture, over that the sour cream mixture. Sprinkle the tomato, black olives and scallions over the top and cover with shredded cheese.
Serve chilled or at room temperature with tortilla chips.

title: fajitas
directions: Marinade whole meat overnight in milk after you sprinkle with unseasoned meat tenderizer.
Drain.
Cut into strips and then cut strips into pieces.
Place oil in skillet or wok.
When it gets hot, add meat.

title: carrot and orange marmalade
directions: Scrape and peel carrots.
Dice and cook until tender in as little water as possible.
Slice oranges very thin.
Add juice and grated rind of lemon.
Combine with carrots.
Measure and add 2/3 cup sugar for every 1 cup of carrot mixture.
Heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Cook rapidly until thick and clear.
Pour into pint jars, leave 1/4 inch headspace and adjust caps.
Process 10 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: best chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa in a large saucepan.
Add half of milk.
Beat egg yolks.
Add eggs.
Then add remaining milk.
Add vanilla. Put on stove.
Add butter.
Stir and cook only until oleo melts.
Pour into two unbaked pie shells and bake at 375° until done, about 45 minutes.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: hamburger hash
directions: Brown beef in large skillet.
Remove from pan; set aside. Add enough oil to drippings in pan to make 3 tablespoons.
Add potatoes, onions and green pepper.
Cook until onions and potatoes are almost tender.
Stir in meat, salt, pepper and sugar.
Heat and cook until vegetables are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: grandma sally's sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, butter and eggs.
Stir in sour cream, then add dry ingredients that have been premixed and the vanilla.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Roll out a small amount at a time on a floured board to which some sugar has also been added.
Sprinkle top of dough with sugar also as roll out.
Cut out with 3-inch round open cookie cutter.
Keep dough cold.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until very slightly browned.
Cool on racks covered with waxed paper.
Store in airtight containers with waxed paper between layers.
Freezes well.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: mock apple rings
directions: Soak the first 3 ingredients for 24 hours.
Rinse and soak in clear water for 3 hours.
Mix 1/2 cup vinegar, food color and alum.
Add cucumbers and cover with water.
Simmer 2 hours and drain well.
Mix 2 cups vinegar, 2 cups water, sugar, cinnamon and candy and heat until candy melts.
Pour over cucumbers.
Let stand overnight.
Reheat and can in boiling water bath.
These are very good.

title: hearty beef-vegetable soup
directions: Heat oil in a large heavy saucepan or Dutch oven over high heat. Crumble in meat.
Add garlic, salt and pepper.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring 2 or 3 times, until meat loses its pink color. Stir in remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 3 minutes until vegetables are hot.
Makes 4 servings. Per Serving:
352 calories, 28 g protein, 33 g carbohydrates, 13 g fat, 59 mg cholesterol and 606 mg sodium.

title: nells' dip
directions: Mix together and chill 12 hours.
Serve with raw veggies or crackers.

title: potato broccoli casserole
directions: Whip cream cheese, milk and butter into hot potatoes and season with salt and pepper.
Fold in half of onions.
Pile potatoes in a greased casserole dish and make a well in the center.
Arrange hot broccoli in well.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350°
until hot and cheese is melted.

title: mimi's christmas wreaths
directions: Melt margarine with marshmallows. Add vanilla and food coloring. Pour over corn flakes and mix. Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper. Put "red hots" or cherry halves in middle to form wreath. Chill about 40 minutes. Makes 2 dozen.

title: fruit freeze cups
directions: Mix all ingredients in a big bowl and put into freezer to thicken.
When mixture starts to thicken, put into individual serving dishes and freeze.
Remove from freezer 20 minutes before serving.

title: fruit dip
directions: In small bowl, combine cream cheese, whipped topping and Marshmallow Creme.
Mix well.
Taste.
Can add more Cool Whip if needed.
Serve with fresh fruit pieces.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in an 8 x 8-inch square or round pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Remove tops and seeds of peppers.
Parboil in salted water about 5 minutes; drain.
Brown beef and cook onion in butter until tender; stir in
1/2 can soup and remaining ingredients.
Spoon meat mixture into peppers.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Heat remaining soup; pour over peppers before serving.

title: martha's meatballs
directions: Mix together eggs, milk, dry onion soup and stuffing mix in a large bowl until well blended.
Add hamburger into mixture and mix well with hands.
Form into desired shape balls.
Place on a jelly roll pan or stove broiler pan and bake at 350° until done.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and squeeze spinach until dry; this is extremely important.
Mix all ingredients and chill in refrigerator overnight.
Add pepper sauce to taste just before serving.

title: microwave garlic penny carrots
directions: Slice carrots and put in microwave dish.
Layer the margarine or Butter Buds and garlic over the carrots.
Cover and microwave 10 to 15 minutes until tender.
Stir occasionally.

title: cheesy-mushroom chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken; dip chicken in melted butter.
Arrange pieces in square baking pan.
Bake in oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Remove from oven; sprinkle cheese over chicken, then sprinkle mushrooms on top of the cheese.
Place back in oven under broiler for just a few seconds until cheese turns a light brown.
Remove and serve.
Serves 4.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Pop popcorn (hot air is best) and divide into 2 large pans. Melt butter.
Stir in brown sugar, Karo syrup and salt.
Boil, without stirring, 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and soda.
Pour over popcorn.
Mix well. Bake in 250° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Cool completely.
Break apart and store in tightly covered container.

title: sugar-free fudge
directions: Mix with a mixer.
Put in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Keep cool or in freezer.

title: low calorie strawberry pie
directions: Boil the water and cornstarch until thick, then add Equal, jello and strawberries.
Stir until mixed.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill.
Cover with Cool Whip.

title: onion-roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a shallow baking or roasting pan, thoroughly blend all ingredients except potatoes.
Add potatoes and turn to coat completely.
Bake, stirring potatoes occasionally, 60 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.

title: pepper steak
directions: Trim fat and bones from meat; cut into 4 to 6 serving pieces. Grease large skillet and brown meat thoroughly on one side.
Turn and season with salt.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk, marshmallows, butter and salt in a heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly over medium heat to a boil (mixture will be bubbling all over top).
When mixture first begins to boil set timer and continue to cook, stirring constantly for 5 more minutes.
Take off heat.
Stir in semi-sweet chocolate until completely melted.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Spread in a slightly buttered tray.
Cut into 30 pieces.

title: slippery slime
directions: Mix 2 quarts of fruit punch and 1 quart of apple juice together.
Add 2 cups of carbonated beverage just before serving.

title: fruity yogurt jello
directions: Prepare Jell-O according to package directions, but instead of adding cold water, add the container of yogurt instead and chill until set.
Serve with lite Cool Whip for garnish.

title: failure cake
directions: In a 9 x 13 x 2 inch baking dish, combine 2 beaten eggs, butter and cake mix.
Mix until crumbly.
Spread out.
Mix separately with electric hand mixer (until smooth), cream cheese, 2 eggs and confectioners sugar.
Pour this mixture over crumb mixture in dish. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: holiday fruit cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in orange juice, over hot water in a double boiler.
Thoroughly blend next 6 ingredients.
Add following 5 ingredients.
Mix well; stir in honey, butter and dissolved gelatin.
Mix thoroughly; press into waxed paper-lined 9 x 5 x 2 3/4-inch loaf pan (firmly).
Cover with aluminum foil. Refrigerate for at least 24 hours before cutting.

title: mexican wedding rings or russian tea cookies
directions: Roll in sticks.
Bake in oven at 250° for 1/2 hour.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: beet salad
directions: Drain beets, reserving liquid.
Add enough water to reserved liquid to equal 2 cups.
In a saucepan, bring beets and liquid to a boil.
Remove from heat; stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Add cold water, onion, horseradish, vinegar and salt.
Chill until partially set.

title: quick curried chicken(makes 4 servings)
directions: In medium-sized bowl combine mayonnaise, curry powder, horseradish, mustard and soy sauce, stirring to mix well.
Dry chicken with paper toweling so sauce will cling.
Dip each quarter in sauce, turning to coat on all sides in large shallow microwave-safe baking dish.
Drizzle any remaining sauce over chicken and cover loosely with waxed paper.
Microwave on High 100% power 20 minutes, rotating dish quarter turn every 5 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
If fork can not be inserted easily in chicken, microwave on High for 3 to 5 minutes longer.
To serve on a large platter arrange chicken on rice.
Drizzle pan drippings over chicken.
Serve with chutney.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: finlandia: a pasties
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour and dash of salt.
With pastry blender or two knives, cut shortening into flour until mixture resembles gravel.
Slowly add water until mixture forms ball.
The pastry will be much stickier than regular pie crust.
With floured hands, shape pastry into ball, cover with plastic wrap and let rest in refrigerator while preparing filling.

title: chicken cheese swirls
directions: Cook green peppers and onions in shortening until tender.
Add 1/4 cup Bisquick, soup and milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Add chicken and peas.
Pour into 7 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix 2 cups Bisquick and water until dough forms.
Knead and roll into 15 x 9-inch rectangle.
Sprinkle with cheese and roll up tightly.
Cut into 12 (1 1/4-inch) slices and arrange on top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: jam cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, sift together flour, spices and soda. Add cake mix, oil, buttermilk and eggs.
Blend until moistened. Beat two minutes at medium speed.
Blend in jam at low speed. Stir in nuts and raisins.
Pour into three floured and paper lined 9-inch cake pans.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool layers in pans 10 to 20 minutes before removing.

title: courtney's cookies
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and oil.
Beat, then add flour, vanilla and cinnamon. Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes. Do not overbake.
These cookies are so easy to make.

title: taste of summer salmon packets
directions: NOTE: You will need 1 salmon fillet per person. This recipe will make 2-8 fillets.

title: almond flan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place milk, sugar, eggs, vanilla, flour, almonds, extract and brown sugar in food processor.
Pulse 5 to 10 seconds at a time, stopping to scrape sides of bowl until mixture is blended but not overprocessed.
Pour batter into a lightly greased 9-inch baking dish or pie plate.
Bake 30 minutes until fluffy and brown.
A knife will come out clean.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and cool slightly before serving.

title: coconut cream pie(microwave)
directions: In a 1 1/2 quart casserole, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add milk gradually, mixing well.
Cook on High for 6 minutes or until thick, stirring at the end of each minute.
Add this hot mixture slowly to beaten egg yolks, stirring well.
Cook 2 minutes or until thick, stirring at the end of each 30 seconds. Add vanilla, butter and coconut and stir well.
Cool filling to room temperature.
Pour into baked pie crust and top with meringue.
Sprinkle 1/3 cup coconut over meringue before browning.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar, syrup, margarine, vanilla, nuts and pinch of salt.
Mix well and pour into unbaked regular (not deep-dish) pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes to an hour.

title: chicken salad croissant
directions: Mix chicken, mayo and sour cream.
Add remaining ingredients. Sprinkle top with chopped walnuts or almonds before serving.
Serve with croissant.

title: chess cake
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients.
Mix well and spread in a long cake pan.
Mixture will be very stiff.

title: church supper chicken
directions: Mince carrot and celery.
Cut up chicken in serving size pieces.
Saute vegetables in butter.
Put rice in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Add onion soup mix and sauteed vegetables with water.
Brown chicken in butter; place on top of rice mixture. Cover with foil and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Note:
If nuts are omitted, use 1 1/2 cups chocolate chips.

title: warm bean salad
directions: In a 1 1/2 quart microwave-safe casserole dish, combine oil, celery and onions.
Cover and microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes or until celery is tender-crisp.

title: ribbon gelatin(eight layers)
directions: To make clear layers in each of four small bowls, dissolve one of the packages of each color gelatin in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.

title: squash medley
directions: Wash and clean all vegetables.
Chop.
Cook in 1/2 cup oil until tender. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix well.
Gradually add 2 cups salad oil.
Beat until fairly thick.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix all together and beat well. Then add 1 cup boiling water with 2 teaspoons soda added and beat again thoroughly. Lastly, add 2 egg whites, beaten stiffly by folding into mix. Bake in two loaves slowly for about 1 hour (or stem pan).

title: broccoli casserole 2
directions: Cut and cook broccoli until tender.
Combine soup, milk and eggs.
Add broccoli, cheese, onion and mushrooms.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Add crackers on top.
Bake (uncovered) at 350° until bubbly (about 45 minutes).

title: ambrosia punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pitcher.
Stir and blend. Chill before serving.
Sweeten lightly, if desired.
Top each glass with mint leaves.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease muffin cups or use paper liners. Measure all ingredients into large mixer bowl.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour into pans.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: holiday waldorf salad
directions: Mix in medium bowl diced cooked turkey.
Drain pineapple well, and mix with diced turkey.
Add chopped celery, walnuts and enough mayonnaise until moistened.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: tony's favorite blue cheese dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients except blue cheese, blend well. Add blue cheese, stir thoroughly. Refrigerate. Makes about 1 1/4 cups. You can add 4 oz softened cream cheese and 1/4 c milk.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and pepper.
Add salt, pepper and a little garlic salt.
Combine all ingredients and pour into crock-pot and cook as long as you want; the longer the better.

title: quick dinner rolls
directions: Add yeast to water.
Stir in sugar, oil, salt and egg until sugar and salt are dissolved.
Stir in one cup of flour until mixture is smooth.
Let rise, covered, on top of a warm pan of water for 15 minutes.
Stir down and add remaining flour.
Turn onto board and knead three minutes.
Roll into 16 balls, quickly. Place in buttered pan and brush butter on tops.
Cover and place in warm place to rise for 25 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: old fashioned butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg.
Beat in flour, baking powder, orange juice and vanilla.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Roll 1/4-inch thick.
Cook 6 to 10 minutes, until golden brown on edges.
Makes 6 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill.

title: no fail - good chili
directions: Brown meat with cut up onion.
Drain off fat except for about 1/4 cup.
Add the rest of the ingredients and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Add water to your desired thickness or thinness.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower into small pieces.
Then mix all other ingredients and add to the cut vegetables.
Let stand in refrigerator 2 to 3 hours or overnight.

title: sweet potato roll
directions: Mix together.
Unroll towel and spread mixture on top.
Roll back up and put in aluminum foil or freeze. Slice as needed

title: never weep meringue
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 1 heaping tablespoon marshmallow fluff for each egg white.
Place on top of pie, sealing edges and bake at 450° for 3-5 minutes.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; add brown sugar.
Boil over low heat for 2 minutes, stirring all the time.
Add milk.
Keep stirring until mixture boils.
Remove from heat.
Cool and add sifted sugar.
Beat well after each addition.
Add pecans, if desired.

title: english trifle
directions: In large glass bowl on bottom lay sponge fingers.
Boil and cool strawberry jelly.
Pour over sponge fingers.
Slice fresh strawberries on top of jelly.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: First Layer:
Melt the oleo and add 2 tablespoons sugar and the pretzels.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: pork chop suey
directions: Brown up cubed pork in oil.
Add onion and celery and cook until soft.
Add the bean sprouts and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add soy sauce.
Thicken with the cornstarch and water mixture by stirring it in.

title: mints
directions: Cut butter into sugar.
Add milk and mint flavor.
Use your favorite food coloring to fit the occasion; form into shapes. Store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: beef and bacon delights
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: pork roast, german style
directions: Place salt and peppered roast in roaster and add onion.
Bake for 2 hours.
During last half of baking, add remaining ingredients.
Finish cooking for 1 hour longer, or more if necessary.
Approximately 3 1/2 to 4 hours at 325°.

title: orange julius
directions: Put orange juice, sugar, water, milk and vanilla in blender with 4 or 5 ice cubes.
Blend 30 seconds or until smooth.
Serve immediately.

title: shrimp dip
directions: With electric mixer, gradually blend soup into cream cheese. Beat just until smooth.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Chill. Serve with chips or crackers.

title: brown sugar fruit cake
directions: Beat
egg
whites
until stiff but not dry.
Slowly add brown sugar
and
vanilla.
Fold
in flour and baking powder. Add pecans.
Bake in tube pan for 45 minutes in 325° oven.

title: cheese broccoli
directions: Heat in large kettle the oil and onion over medium heat 3 minutes.
Add water, broccoli and bouillon cubes.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally, until cubes dissolve.
Gradually add the noodles and salt; cook, uncovered, for 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add cubed cheese, pepper and garlic powder. Continue cooking until cheese melts, then add milk.
Do not let it come to boil as it will curdle.
Freezes well.

title: candied grapefruit peel
directions: Take any amount of grapefruit peeling and cut into strips approximately 3-inches long by 1/2 inch wide.
Wash and be sure to remove all pulp.Soak the peeling in salted cold water for three days.
Drain off this water and cover with fresh cold water and bring to a boil. Drain, and for the second time - cover with fresh cold water and bring to a boil.

Again, drain, and for the third time - cover with fresh cold water and bring to a boil. This procedure eliminates the bitter taste. In a separate saucepan mix 2 parts of granulated sugar with 1 part of water and bring to a boil. Put in any food coloring, such as green or red for Christmas.
Add drained peeling to this syrup and cook until peel strips are transparent.
Drain well and lay on a cookie sheet to cool.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Store in glass jars.

title: chicken casserole
directions: The chicken breasts should be boned, skinned and cut in strips.
The frozen vegetables (broccoli, cauliflower and carrots) should be thawed and drained.
Put the ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch casserole in the order as listed with the cheese sprinkled over the top (layer).
Bake at 300° for 1 3/4 hours.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown meat and drain off fat.
Mix vegetables and meat with gravy, then put mashed potatoes on top.
Then brown the potatoes in oven for about 30 minutes.

title: crab cakes
directions: Pick over crab meat for pieces of shell.
Cook onion in butter until tender.
Combine all ingredients, except bread crumbs. Shape into 6 cakes and roll in bread crumbs.
Place cakes in frypan with 1/8-inch of fat that is hot, but not smoking.
Fry at moderate heat.
When all the cakes are brown on one side, turn and brown other side.
The cooking time will be approximately 5 to 8 minutes.

title: strawberry waffles
directions: Puree strawberries.
Combine with milk to measure 3 cups.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until batter is smooth.
Bake on preheated waffle iron until steaming stops.
Yields 6 large waffles.

title: banana wow! bread
directions: In bowl, cream the sugar and butter together.
Stir in eggs. Then stir in sour cream and the soda.
Stir in the flour and pinch of salt.
Then stir in bananas until all is well mixed.
If desired, add nuts.
Mix and pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate-peanut butter banana lollipops
directions: You will also need 6 to 8 popsicle sticks.

title: creamy broccoli soup
directions: Chop onion.
Trim broccoli and cut stems and florets into 2-inch pieces.
In medium saucepan, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Add onion and cook until tender, but not browned, about 5 minutes.
Stir in flour.
Cook, stirring constantly, 1 minute. Add chicken broth and 2 cups water.
Bring to a boil.
Add broccoli. Reduce heat to medium and simmer until broccoli is tender, about 8 minutes.
Puree vegetable mixture, in batches, in food processor or blender until smooth.
Return mixture to saucepan over low heat.
Stir in evaporated skim milk and nutmeg. Cook, stirring occasionally, until heated through, 5 minutes.
Do not let soup boil.
Garnish with yogurt, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spacheezies
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Sift together the flour, salt and baking powder.
Add the milk, melted margarine and eggs to the sifted ingredients.
Add spinach and cheese.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 375° for 35 minutes

title: garden slaw
directions: Mix shredded cabbage, carrots, pepper and onion. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cold water. Chill. Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water. Mix sugar, vinegar, celery seeds, salt and pepper in a saucepan; bring to a boil. Stir in softened gelatin; cool slightly until thickened. Beat well; gradually beat in salad oil. Drain vegetables; pour over top. Mix lightly until all vegetables are coated. May be served immediately or stored in refrigerator. Stir just before serving. Makes 8 servings.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Combine all in casserole dish and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: quick punch
directions: Scoop sherbet into a punch bowl.
Add the soda, pouring liquid slowly down the sides of the bowl.
Yield: 12 to 15 small servings.

title: biscuit cake
directions: Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Cut each biscuit into fourths. Roll each biscuit in brown sugar, cinnamon and sugar.
Melt 1 stick of butter and roll over biscuits before cooking.
Bake at 300°.
Glaze with 1 cup of powdered sugar and 2 tablespoons of water.
Take out of pan immediately.

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Measure all ingredients
into
large
mixer
bowl; beat on medium speed 1/2 minute.
Pour
into
pan(s).
Bake
to
65 minutes or until wooden
pick
inserted
in center comes out clean.
Remove from pan(s); cool thoroughly before slicing.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Place strawberries in kettle over heat.
Crush as they heat. When berries boil, add sugar and cook quickly until thick (not over 20 minutes), stirring frequently to prevent burning.
Pour into clean, hot jars and seal.
Makes 4 (1/2 pint) jars.

title: crunchy ice cream pie
directions: Stir butter and sugar.
Mix in cornflakes, nuts and coconut. Line bottom and sides of 9-inch pie pan with 2/3 of mixture. Chill.
Fill with ice cream and sprinkle with remaining corn flake mixture on top, pressing lightly into ice cream.
Serve with chocolate topping or any other flavor.
May serve plain.

title: vegetable medley
directions: In a medium saucepan, saute onions in butter.
Add tomatoes, cornstarch, thyme and pepper; stir until cornstarch is dissolved. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and translucent.
Add peas; heat through.
Serve sauce over omelet, hamburger or use as a side dish.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Saute together margarine, onions and broccoli.
Mix together the corn muffin mix, eggs and sour cream.
Pour muffin mixture over sauteed ingredients into a cast-iron skillet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: zucchini, turnips and carrots in butter
directions: Cut ends off zucchini.
Cut into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Stack slices and cut into 1/4-inch wide julienne strips.
Prepare turnips and carrots in same manner.
Put carrots in saucepan; add water to cover.
Bring to boil and simmer 2 minutes.
Add turnips and simmer 1 minute more.
Drain well.
Melt butter in heavy skillet and add zucchini, carrots,
turnips and shallots.
Season to taste.
Cook, tossing and stirring, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Serve hot.
Serves 4.

title: struflers
directions: Fry in deep oil.
When finished, melt honey and pour over cookies.
Add colored beads.

title: raspberry delight
directions: Mix together and put in jelly roll pan.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: never fail meringue
directions: Beat egg whites with cream of tartar.
Beat sugar in gradually.
Beat until mixture is stiff and glossy and sugar is dissolved.
Swirl meringue on pie filling.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
For a crisper meringue bake longer.

title: jellied cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O using less than 2 cups of water as relish is juicy.
When Jell-O is partially jelled, add in remaining ingredients.
This is something a little different for Thanksgiving; great with leftovers!

title: sausage and wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed and set aside.
Brown sausage in skillet, stir and crumble; drain well.
Combine all ingredients. Spoon into lightly greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots and drain.
Marinate 24 hours.

title: fantasy fudge(low-fat)
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and bring to a rolling boil.
Stir constantly.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and cool.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time, alternately with flour.
Add cocoa, vanilla, salt and nuts.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes.
Spread marshmallows over cake; return to oven and melt.

title: perohi casserole
directions: Cook sauerkraut and drain.
Fry bacon and drain on paper towel.
Fry onion and mushrooms in margarine.
Combine bacon that has been cut into small pieces, mushrooms, onion and sauerkraut. Place perohi in casserole.
Cover with combined ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Serve with applesauce or sour cream.

title: quick red velvet cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to instructions on box.
Add cocoa and vinegar.
Also, add red food coloring.
After emptying 1 ounce bottle, fill bottle with water and add to mixture.
Mix well. Pour batter into 2 (9-inch) cake pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 300° until cake leaves side of pan.
Cool on wire rack in pan for 10 minutes, then turn out on rack to cool.

title: skillet dinner
directions: Brown together in hot shortening ground beef, green pepper and onion.
Add remaining ingredients and cook on low heat about 45 minutes.

title: hamburger stroganoff with egg noodles
directions: saute onion and garlic in butter over medium heat.
Stir in meat and brown.
Add flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes.
Combine diluted soup with sour cream.
Stir in meat mixture; add parsley and sherry (optional) and simmer 10 minutes. Serve over hot, drained egg noodles that have been cooked according to directions on the package.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: homemade doughnuts
directions: Scald milk; cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast which has been dissolved in the lukewarm water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let rise until ready to use.
Roll out and cut and let rise again. Fry in deep fat.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Crush Oreos in food processor or blender until crumbs are fine.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and margarine until well blended. Fold in whipped topping until well blended.
Set aside.
Combine pudding, milk and vanilla and set aside.
Using medium plastic flowerpot, layer Oreos, whipped topping, pudding, Oreos, whipped topping and pudding and finish with Oreos.
Place silk flowers in center and chill until served.

title: mexican taco dip
directions: Mix together sour cream and cream cheese.
Spread on the bottom of an 11 inch by 7 inch dish. Spread salsa on cream cheese layer.
Sprinkle onion and tomato on salsa.
Sprinkle taco cheese on top.
Dip with tortilla chips.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix, chill and serve with Parmesan cheese on top.

title: old-fashioned apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry.
Mix sugars, flour, lemon juice, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Stir in apples.
Turn into pastry-lined pie plate.
Dot with butter.
Moisten rim of bottom crust and place top crust, with slits cut in it, over filling. Fold edge of top crust under bottom crust, pressing to seal.
Make a decorative edge.
Cover edge with 3-inch strip of aluminum foil to prevent excessive browning; remove foil during last 15 minutes of baking.
Bake until lightly brown and juice bubbles, 40 to 50 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: green tomato chow-chow
directions: Add all ingredients except spice.
Put spice in a clean cloth and tie up.
Put in mixture and boil for 30 minutes.
Put in pints and seal with hot lids and rings.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix all ingredients in food processor or by hand.
Use a cookie press and shape into straws.
Bake at 350° for approximately 15 minutes or until crisp when cut.

title: banana pudding
directions: Layer bananas.
Layer wafers.
Continue until all gone.
Mix instant pudding with milk; mix with hand mixer.
Pour over banana and wafers.
Top with whipped topping.

title: icing-cooked
directions: Cook sugar, syrup, cream of tartar and water until soft ball state.
Pour syrup in a slow stream over 2 beaten egg whites. Beat for 10 minutes.
Beat in powdered sugar, mandarin peel and mandarin juice.
Beat icing until it is a smooth, spreadable consistency.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Put in baking dish.
Mix 1/2 cup of margarine with corn flake crumbs and sprinkle on top.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 300° to 350°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender and debone.
Place chicken in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Slice boiled eggs and place over chicken.
Mix the broth with the soup and pour over chicken and eggs.
In separate bowl, mix flour, milk and margarine well.
Pour this over the chicken mixture; do not stir.
Cook at 400° for about 45 minutes.

title: crock pot chicken and dressing
directions: Bake cornbread per package directions.
Boil chicken and debone.
Crumble cornbread in crock pot.
Add soups and chopped onion and celery.
Stir well.
Add chicken.
Add broth (I use about 2 cups of the broth from the boiled chicken.
Add more or less as you prefer.)
Cook 4 to 6 hours on low in crock pot.

title: chinese barbecue sauce for spareribs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in refrigerator for about an hour. Brush over pork ribs and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until done. Brush over while they are cooking at least once.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Mix well and roll very thin on a well floured board.
Makes 2 crusts.
Excellent to freeze in larger amounts.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In a double boiler top over direct heat, cook onion in butter until tender.
Stir in flour.

title: chuck wagon casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Mix all ingredients except for biscuits, butter and cornmeal. Place in shallow 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake 10 minutes. Dip biscuits in melted butter and then add cornmeal. Arrange around the casserole dish. Bake an additional 20 to 25 minutes or until biscuits brown.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Place all ingredients into large mixing bowl.
Beat well.
(Do not use electric mixer.)
Pour into a well-greased, floured and paper-lined (bottom) tube pan.
Bake at 325° approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: no knead white bread
directions: Stir the yeast into the lukewarm water.
Set aside.
Put butter, sugar and salt in a medium bowl.
Add boiling water and stir.
When this is lukewarm, stir in the yeast mixture.
Now add the liquid mixture slowly to the flour by hand or mixer.
When everything is combined and mixture is smooth, cover and leave in warm place to rise until double in bulk, about 1 hour.
Stir the dough until it deflates.
Spoon into a regular size loaf pan that has been buttered.
The dough will be soft and spongy.
Pat the top of the log with a floured hand to smooth it out.
Let it rise again, lightly covered, just until edges of loaf reach top of pan, 30 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: rachel's beef stew
directions: In Dutch oven over medium-high heat, fry bacon until crisp. Push bacon bits to side of pan.
To drippings in pan, add stew meat and cook until well browned.
Stir in water, wine and next 6 ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 2 hours or until meat is fork-tender, stirring occasionally.
Later, in covered medium pan over high heat in about 1-inch boiling salted water, cook onions 10 minutes.
Add mushrooms.
Cook 5 more minutes; drain.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch cake pan with Pam.
Sprinkle nuts and coconut on the bottom of cake pan.
Make cake mix according to directions on box and pour over nuts and coconut.
With a mixer, mix powdered sugar, margarine and cream cheese.
Pour this mixture over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.
Serve as is.

title: pudding and sauce cake
directions: Mix together and pour into 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° until done.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: Cook noodles 7 minutes and drain.
Combine butter, cream and cream cheese.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.

title: hearty chicken bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a medium bowl combine potatoes, 1/2 of cheese and 1/2 of onions; mix.
Spoon into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole, spreading across bottom and up the sides to form a shell.
In a large bowl, combine chicken, mixed vegetables, soup, milk and seasonings; pour into potato shell.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onion; bake 3 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes.

title: calico beans
directions: Fry and drain bacon.
In remaining grease put brown sugar, vinegar, mustard and onions.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Mix all ingredients in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken baked over rice(low-fat)
directions: Spread 1/2 can of soup into square baking dish.
Place chicken on top.
Top chicken with cheese.
Dilute remaining soup and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serve over rice.
tags: Healthy Choice cream of chicken soup

title: aunt alice's stone crock cookies
directions: Combine shortening, salt, soda, vanilla and nutmeg.
Add brown sugar gradually; cream well. Add beaten eggs and mix well. Drop from spoon onto a greased cookies sheet.

title: no fool pie
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish in 350° oven.
Combine flour, sugar and 1/2 of milk and stir until moist.
Add remaining milk and stir until smooth.
Pour batter over melted butter.
Do not mix.
Place fruit over mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes, until light brown.

title: daisy's delicious pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour. Stir in melted butter, then eggs. Add syrup; mix well. Stir in pecans. Pour into pie crust. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: chocolate mahogany chiffon cake
directions: Combine hot water and cocoa.
Let cool.
Sift flour, sugar and baking soda into a mixing bowl.
Make a well in the center and add, in order, salad oil, egg yolks, cocoa mixture and vanilla. Beat until smooth.

title: wild rice with vegetables
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan except peppers.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cover.
Simmer 40 minutes.
Stir in pepper.
Simmer covered 10 minutes more.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken breast parmesan
directions: Coat chicken with pancake mix and salt and pepper.
Combine other ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes, covered.
Uncover and bake another 1/2 hour more.

title: fruit bowl supreme
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Chill about 1 hour.
Serve as dessert or salad on crisp salad greens.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and sugar. Mix pudding and milk per package directions. Layer Cool Whip mixture, pudding and Oreos. Chill 1 hour.

title: grama dodd's spinach squares
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan or baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Do Not preheat oven!

title: tallasina
directions: While noodles
are
cooking, saute meat, onions, celery and garlic in
large skillet.
Stir until redness is gone from meat. Add
sauce,
corn
and
half
the
cheese.	Stir
until melted. Add olives.
Mix well with noodles.
Place in greased baking dish and
sprinkle
top with rest of cheese.
Cover and bake one hour at 350°.

title: raspberry jello salad
directions: Add boiling water to jello and pudding, then add raspberries. When a little set, add Cool Whip.
Fold mixture together. Refrigerate.

title: floating island punch
directions: Mix sugar, water, lemon and orange juices.
Before serving, add ginger ale, sparkling water or grape juice and balls of sherbet.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Soak the cut up frying chicken in milk for several hours in refrigerator.
Place flour, salt and pepper in plastic bag.
Dip chicken in egg and then put in flour mixture.
Shake in bag until well coated.
Place chicken on hot oil in a heavy skillet with lid. Turn heat to medium and cover chicken.
Brown well on each side and cook until well done.
Serve with mashed potatoes and white gravy.

title: homemade rolls
directions: In mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, salt and half of flour.
Beat thoroughly for 2 minutes.
Add egg and shortening.
Mix in remaining flour with fork until dough is easy to handle.
Place greased side up in a greased bowl.
Cover bowl. Place in refrigerator.
Punch down occasionally as dough rises. About 2 hours before needed, cut off amount needed and return rest of dough to refrigerator.
Shape while cold into rolls.
Cover. Let rise until doubled in size (1 1/2 to 2 hours).

title: sugar creme cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pat in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix beaten eggs, powdered sugar and cream cheese with electric mixer until smooth.
Pour over crust.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool completely and refrigerate leftovers.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, salt, pepper, onion, celery, pickles and diced eggs.
Blend pickle juice and Miracle Whip with mustard; add to potatoes and mix until all ingredients are well coated with dressing.
Cover salad; refrigerate several hours or overnight so flavors will mingle.

title: garden pizza appetizer
directions: Unroll crescent roll and pat evenly in 15 x 11-inch jelly roll pan. Bake according to package directions.

title: harvest torte
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix thoroughly,
but do not beat.
Turn mixture into a greased 8-inch pan. Bake in a 400° oven for 40 minutes or until apples are tender. Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: baked hush puppies
directions: In medium bowl mix flour, cornmeal, baking powder, salt and sugar; then add
milk, onion, eggs, margarine and corn.
Stir until blended.
Drop by tablespoon 2 inches apart on well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° about 15 minutes.
Serve with butter.

title: potato candy
directions: Smash cooled, boiled potatoes.
Blend in vanilla and butter. Blend in confectioners sugar until mixture is stiff.
Roll out mixture on floured surface leaving mixture about 1/4-inch thick. Spread a thin layer of peanut butter (smooth or crunchy) on top of mixture.
Roll into a log.
Let set in refrigerator for 1 hour. Cut log into 1/4 to 1/2-inch slices.

title: muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400° (moderately hot).
Blend ingredients, then beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Fill well-greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake 15 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: almond brittle
directions: Combine in heavy skillet all of the ingredients.
Cook over medium heat.
Stir in 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Stir constantly until sugar and almonds are golden brown (approximately 15 minutes).
Spread on foil.
Any kind of nuts may be used.

title: appalachian pear relish
directions: Peel and core pears.
Seed both kinds of the peppers.
Coarsely grind pears, peppers and onions.
Place ground mixture in a large pot, adding the vinegar and sugar.
In a muslin bag, combine celery seed, pickling spices and mustard seed.
Tie bag shut and place in the pot.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer 40 minutes. Remove spice bag.
Pour into sterilized canning jars and seal tightly.
Store pear relish in cellar or a cool, dry place.
Yields 8 pints.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: In saucepan, combine flour, sugar and salt.
With a wire whisk, whip egg yolks into milk.
Add milk and egg mixture gradually to the dry ingredients in the saucepan.
Stir constantly.
Cook until very thick.
The mixture should bubble as you cook it.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked 9-inch pie shell and top with meringue, whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Place 2/3 of the Fritos in a casserole dish; set aside.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix margarine and flour in a saucepan.
Add sugars and syrup; boil 5 minutes.
Let cool and add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well. Place pecans in pie shell; pour mixture over pecans.
Bake at 300 degrees about 1 hour.
Let cool before cutting.

title: angel food surprise
directions: Cut the top 1/3 of the cake horizontally.
Lay top aside.
In the remaining cake make a trough approximately 1 inch deep.
Do not cut the sides, just the center.
Pinch out the cake in the trough.
Lay aside.
Prepare the pudding according to the package instructions, using only half of the milk.
Mix pudding with cake crumbs from the center.
Place the pudding mixture in the trough. Put the top back on the cake.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Using a grater or vegetable peeler, make chocolate shavings for the top of cake.

title: frosted ginger ale salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and let set until partially jelled.
Then add the last 3 ingredients.

title: velvet pound cake
directions: Cream butter and
sugar
together.
Add
eggs, one at a time. Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: do nothing cake
directions: Combine ingredients, mixing lightly.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: champagne delite
directions: Cream cheese and sugar and add fruit and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour into a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Refrigerate 12 hours or overnight.

title: chili dip
directions: Melt Velveeta; add Hormel chili, green chilies and chives. Heat until well blended.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: tuna spread
directions: Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise together until smooth. Add drained tuna, onion and celery. Warm tomato soup. Mix gelatine and cold water together quickly and mix with soup.
Immediately put mixture with tuna. Pour into mold that has been sprayed with Pam. Refrigerate overnight or until firm.
Serve on Ritz or Townhouse crackers.

title: dream cheesecake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Butter generously a 9-inch spring form pan.
Mix butter and crumbs well; reserve 1/4 cup of crumb mixture.
Press remainder of crumb mixture in bottom of pan (firmly).
Add cream of tartar to egg whites and beat until foamy.
Gradually add 3 tablespoons sugar and beat until stiff. Set aside.
Beat cheese until soft.
Mix 1 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt.
Gradually beat into cheese.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each one.
Add sour cream and vanilla, mix well.
Fold egg white thoroughly into rest.
Pour into prepared pan.
Sprinkle reserved 1/4 cup crumbs over top.
Bake in preheated oven at 350 for 1 1/4 hours or until firm.
Turn off heat, open oven door and leave cake in oven for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and let stand on cake rack, away from drafts, until cool.
Chill over night or until totally firm.

title: kugelis
directions: Peel and grate the potatoes on fine side of hand grater, grating a bit of onion between each potato.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cut strips of bacon and fry until crisp.
Pour over potato mixture.
Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Pour into square or oblong pan about 2 to 2 1/2 inches deep.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes, lowering heat to 375° for another 40 minutes or until nicely browned.
Serve hot with sour cream or applesauce.

title: haystacks
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter.
Boil 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in marshmallows until dissolved.
Add coconut and graham crackers.
Drop small haystacks on waxed paper to cool.

title: mocha bourbon balls
directions: Combine chocolate, butter and sugar in top of a double boiler. Bring water to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cook until chocolate and butter melt.
Remove from heat; stir in cream, bourbon, coffee granules and one cup of pecans.
Cover and refrigerate until firm.

title: alfredo sauce
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Add the rest of the ingredients and stir until smooth.
Allow to come to a soft boil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour over cooked fettuccini or tortellini.

title: petits pois stuffed tomatoes(microwave recipe)
directions: Cut a thin slice from top of each tomato; scoop out pulp (reserve), leaving a 1/4-inch shell.
Chop pulp.
Combine butter, peas, onion, garlic, basil, pepper and tomato pulp in a 2-quart dish or measuring cup.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook on High for 10 minutes.
Add mushrooms; cover and continue cooking on High for 5 minutes.
Stir in salt and croutons.
Spoon mixture into tomato shells.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese on top.
Place tomatoes in baking dish and, just before serving, microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes.
Do not overcook tomatoes.

title: cheesy crunch macaroni casserole
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Stir in soup and other ingredients except 1 cup cheese.
Layer in baking dish (2-quart).
Top with cheese and bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Top with remaining half of onions and brown 5 minutes.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add cocoa and coffee. Beat these ingredients.
Add soda to buttermilk and vanilla; add to cake flour.
Add all together and beat until mixture is creamy. Place in a greased pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: stuffed date wheel
directions: Shape cream cheese into 8 balls; roll in nuts.
Cut 2 pineapple slices into eighths; stuff into dates.
Place cheese balls in center of remaining pineapple slices; garnish with stuffed dates.
Serve with watercress and lettuce.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cranberry coffee cake
directions: Mix topping together; set aside.
Mix cake mix, pudding, oil, water, eggs and vanilla as you would a cake.
Pour 1/2 of cake mix into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 of sugar mixture and spoon 1/2 of the cranberries on top.
Pour the rest of the cake mix on this and top with the rest of the sugar mixture and cranberries.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: quick shrimp casserole
directions: Cook and drain peas according to directions.
Mix soup and milk; add cheese, onion and seasoning.
Blend well.
Add the peas and shrimp.
Pour half the mixture into a 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle half of the potato chips on the sauce.
Cover with the rest of the shrimp mixture.
Crumble remaining potato chips on top.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour, until bubbly and brown.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: microwave baked apples
directions: Core apples.
Place sugar and butter in cavities. Arrange in rings in baking dish with space in between. Cover tightly. Microwave on High for 4 to 6 1/2 minutes, rotating after 2 minutes. Let stand 2 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In pan, melt butter and add soups and water.
Mix in rice and pour into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Lay chicken over top and cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Remove foil and stir. Sprinkle almonds and cheese on top and bake for another 15 minutes.

title: pecan dreams
directions: Rub flour, confectioners sugar and butter into a paste and spread over 2 cookie pans, 8 x 15-inch.
Bake or chill until firm. Beat eggs slightly.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well. Spread over bottom crust.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 20 minutes.

title: granny's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and add butter, sugar, syrup and vanilla.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell; sprinkle pecans over filling.
Bake in a 350° oven approximately 40 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Mix
together
potatoes, cheese, mayonnaise, onions and half of bacon.
Top with olives and remainder of bacon.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter and flour 12-cup Bundt cake pan. Cream butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar; cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add flour and beat on medium speed.
Add flavor.
Pour batter evenly into prepared pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours or until pick inserted comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes in pan.
Turn upside down on cake plate.

title: vanilla icebox cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream oleo and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in half of flour. Then add the remaining flour to form a stiff dough.
Add nuts. Roll out on floured board in 2 rolls.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
May be left 10 days.
Slice and bake at 375°.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Soak oatmeal in buttermilk or sour milk for 1 hour.
Mix shortening, brown sugar and egg together.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Stir mixtures into oatmeal and buttermilk.
Put into muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Good with a casserole and a salad.

title: lasagne
directions: Sauce:
Brown ground beef and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and simmer for 15 minutes.
Cook lasagne noodles until done.
Drain.

title: vegetable creole
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and spoon over casserole.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix butter, milk, sugar and cocoa and boil 4 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add oats and vanilla.
Stir and drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: spicy lamb
directions: Cut lamb into 1-inch cubes.
In large saucepan, brown 1/2 of the meat in hot margarine/butter.
Remove meat.
Brown remaining meat with onion, celery and garlic until vegetables are tender. Drain fat.
Return all meat to pan and stir in tomato sauce, water, curry powder, ginger, cumin, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for about 1 hour or until lamb is tender.
Combine yogurt and flour; add to meat.
Cook and stir until bubbly; cook about 1 minute more.
Serve sprinkled with cilantro or parsley over rice or with pita bread.
Serves 4.

title: top of the range beans
directions: Melt shortening in large saucepan, add green pepper and onion. Saute for 5 minutes or until tender.
Stir in beans, pineapple, catsup, molasses and brown sugar.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes, or until mixture comes just to boiling.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together eggs, sugars, melted butter, peanut butter, vanilla, corn syrup and the baking soda.
Mix well, then add oatmeal, chocolate chips, nuts, M&M's and raisins.
Mix well; spray pan with cooking spray.
Drop onto cookie sheet with ice cream scoop.
Flatten for cow-chip cookies.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Combine peaches, sugar, butter or oleo and cornstarch in a saucepan, stirring well.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Stir.

title: overnight cinnamon buns
directions: Grease a Bundt or other fluted cake pan well and coat with some of the chopped nuts.
Break frozen rolls apart and arrange 12 over the nuts.
Sprinkle 1/2 the dry pudding mix on top, then sprinkle with cinnamon.
Arrange the remaining 12 rolls in the pan and sprinkle with remaining pudding mix and cinnamon.
Scatter remaining nuts on top.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash and drain cucumbers.
Cut in half, quarters or leave whole, if small.
Put cucumbers in a half gallon jar; add 1/4 cup vinegar.
Add 2 heaping tablespoons salt.
(I use the coarse salt you can buy at the country stores.)
Fill the jar with cold water; put the top on the jar and shake it until the salt and vinegar is thoroughly mixed with the water.
Let the pickles set on the cabinet overnight.
They are now ready to be eaten.
They are best kept in the refrigerator as they will stay crisp and fresh.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Combine
tuna
fish,
bread
crumbs,
celery and onion; blend mayonnaise,
chili	sauce and lemon juice and stir into tuna mixture.
Form patties and cook on grill.

title: giant soap bubbles
directions: Bend a coat hanger into a loop.
Mix detergent with water. Measure carefully, it makes a big difference.
Stir slowly.
Add glycerin.
Pour solution into frying pan, dip hanger loop and wave into the air.
The longer the solution sits, the better it gets.

title: lemon pie
directions: Cook sugar, water and cornstarch until thick.
Beat egg yolks slightly.
Add a bit of the cooked mixture to egg yolks and continue on so the egg yolks don't cook and get stringy.
Add fresh lemon juice and grated lemon rind.
Cook 1 minute.
Pour into a cooled, baked pastry shell.

title: pineapple over baked ham
directions: Pour melted butter over bread crumbs, saving some to put on top.
Mix pineapple, sugar and cinnamon and pour over buttered bread crumbs that have been placed in a baking dish.

title: cream cheese nut drops
directions: Cream margarine and cream cheese; add sugar and flour, blending well.
Form into small balls and flatten on greased cookie sheet by placing nut half in center.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 1/2 to 10 dozen, depending on size formed.
Let cookies cool before removing from cookie sheet or they will crumble.

title: apricot pork chops
directions: Brown chops; remove.
Combine ingredients.
Put on top of chops.
Simmer covered in pan for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate coca-cola cake
directions: Bring margarine, cocoa and cola to a boil.
Sift together flour, sugar and vanilla.
Pour hot mixture over flour and sugar. Mix well and add eggs.
Beat buttermilk, soda and marshmallows. Cook in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat sweetened condensed milk, peanut butter, egg and vanilla until smooth.
Add biscuit mix; mix well. Chill at least 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Shape into 1-inch balls; roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Flatten with fork.
Bake for 6 to 8 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool; store, tightly covered, at room temperature.

title: beef and broccoli stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in wok or large frying pan. Stir-fry beef until it loses its pink coloring.
Add vegetables and cover. Cook until tender-crisp.
Remove ingredients.
Mix cornstarch and water and add to wok.
Add soy sauce. Toss in vegetable-meat mixture.
Heat thoroughly. Serve over rice.

title: sourdough for hot cakes
directions: The Night Before:
Mix flour, milk and sourdough starter in a bowl.
Cover and set on countertop overnight.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Combine brown sugar, margarine, syrup and salt in a 2-quart dish.
Place in microwave and bring to a boil; cook on high for 2 minutes.
Remove from microwave and stir in baking soda.
Mix well. Put popped corn into heavy brown grocery bag.
Pour syrup over corn.
Close bag and shake to mix and coat corn.
Close bag by turning top down.
Cook in bag in microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake and cook another 1 1/2 minutes; shake.
Cook another 1 1/2 minutes.
Pour in pan; cool and break apart.
Store in closed container.

title: four bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Best if left overnight or several hours.
Refrigerate; stir occasionally.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Salt and pepper to taste.
Brown ground beef with onions and salt and pepper.
Put in a crock-pot or Dutch oven.
Add all the ingredients and cook all day on low in crock-pot or simmer until done in dutch oven.

title: turnip greens casserole
directions: Blend all ingredients together except crumbs and cheese. Spoon into casserole, cover top with bread crumbs and cheese. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: magic noodles
directions: Brown meat.
Add tomato juice, onion, green pepper, salt, sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Add noodles and cook in covered skillet for 20 minutes.
Add cheese the last 5 minutes.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Use 2 heaping tablespoons to 1 cup of hot water.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine apples, marshmallows, celery and walnuts.
Add enough salad dressing to moisten.
Toss lightly and chill.
Add additional dressing and garnish with apple slices before serving.

title: hot cider
directions: Add cinnamon sticks and allspice to apple juice in a saucepan. Heat until hot, not boiling on a low temperature.

title: best gingerbread ever
directions: Cream shortening and butter
with
sugar.
Add	egg and molasses; beat well.
Sift	together
the
dry ingredients and stir in.
Add the hot water
last;	mix
well.
This
makes
a very fluid batter.	Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan and bake in a 350° oven for
to
minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.
When
cool,
cut in squares and serve with whipped cream or nutmeg sauce.
Makes 18 to 20 servings.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Mix together cake mix and yeast.
Then add water and mix. Mix in flour.
Mix with hands.
Cover with waxed paper and let rise 1 hour.
After 1 hour divide dough in half and roll in a circle (takes a lot of flour) and cut into 8 pie shaped pieces. Roll into crescents starting at the large end.
Bake at 350° for 10-12 minutes.
Butter while hot.
Each box makes 16 rolls.

title: lima beans (butter beans) or field peas
directions: Wash and clean peas or butter beans.
Add peas or beans to medium size cook pot and cover with water.
Cook about 20 to 30 minutes until almost tender.
Add bacon drippings.
Cook for a few minutes longer until peas or beans are done (tender).
Add salt to taste.
Tastes better when not overcooked.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: red hot wings
directions: Split wings at each joint and discard tips.
Pat dry.
Deep fry at 400° for 12 minutes until completely cooked and skin is crispy.
Drain.
Combine butter, hot sauce and Worcestershire. Dip wings in sauce to coat completely.
Serve with celery and cheese dip.
Yields 24 to 30 pieces.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Sift together the flour, salt, soda and sugar.
Beat egg with half the buttermilk.
Add to the dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Slowly add the remaining buttermilk to make a thin batter, stirring constantly.
Mix in the melted shortening.

title: asparagus baked in foil
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
Place the asparagus in the center of a large sheet of aluminum foil in a baking pan with the edges folded up to keep the liquid inside.
Season with salt and pepper. Sprinkle with lemon juice and pour the broth over all.
Fold the sides over and seal.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes or until the asparagus are al dente, just cooked.
Place the asparagus on a platter and pour the juice over.
Serve immediately, garnished with parsley and lemon rind.
Serves 4.

title: wild rice-beef casserole supreme
directions: Prepare dish a day ahead so meat and spices marinate, but do not bake until ready to serve.
Pour boiling water over rice;
let stand, covered, for 15 minutes.
Drain off water.
Place rice in a large oven-to-table casserole dish.
Add soup, mushrooms with liquid, water, and seasonings.
Let stand.
Saute onion in oil until tender; add to rice.
Saute meat until brown and crumbly; add to casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake dish in 325° oven for 2 hours before serving.
This is very good with green beans and a tossed salad for a buffet dinner.
Yields:
8 servings.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain off fat.
Add taco mix and water.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add tomato sauce and continue simmering until sauce thickens.
In a separate bowl, beat egg and add sour cream.
Cover the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with a small amount of meat sauce. Place 4 tortillas on bottom of the pan.
Layer 1/2 of the meat sauce, 1/2 of the sour cream mixture and 1/3 of the combined cheeses.
Repeat layers and top with the chilies, the salsa, the remaining tortillas
and the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Allow to rest for a few minutes before serving.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, stir together apples and sugar.
Add dry ingredients; stir well.
In separate bowl, beat eggs, oil and vanilla.
Stir egg mixture into apple mixture, blending until thoroughly moistened.
Stir in pecans.

title: house fried rice
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
While rice is cooking, heat a wok or large skillet over medium-high heat.
Pour in sesame oil and stir onion.
Fry until golden, then add garlic. When garlic is lightly browned, mix in shrimp, ham and chicken. Fry until shrimp is pink.
Lower heat to medium and stir in celery, carrot, green pepper and peas.
Fry until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Stir in beaten egg and cook just until egg is scrambled and firm.
When rice is done, mix thoroughly with the vegetables and stir in soy sauce.
Adjust seasoning to your preference and serve immediately.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown rice in the oil in a skillet.
Add the green onions, pepper, garlic powder, salt and cumin to the rice.
Add the chicken broth and tomato sauce to the mixture.
Cook until tender, covered, for about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serves 6.

title: easy cheese cakes
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese together until smooth. Whip cream until stiff peaks. Fold whip cream into cream cheese mixture. Pour into shells. Refrigerate. Top with your choice of topping.

title: fried bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Add sugar and salt. Add 3 cups flour and beat until smooth. Add melted shortening and remaining flour. Mix well. Roll onto floured board to 1/4 inch thick, cut in 3-inch squares, and fry.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Wash and boil sweet potatoes until tender.
Pare and cut into slices and place in a greased baking dish.
Combine butter, sugar and water; stir well.
Then pour over sweet potatoes.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve hot.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Make cornbread as directed on package; add corn.
Pour half of the mixture into a greased baking dish.
Brown ground beef, onion and bell pepper together.
Drain.
Add tomatoes.
Pour over cornbread mixture in baking dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan and Mozzarella cheese.
Add remaining cornbread mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Test for doneness with toothpick.

title: potato cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and pout in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Put dough the size of a marble on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: buttermilk pecan pralines
directions: In a large saucepan, combine sugar, soda and salt.
Stir in buttermilk and syrup. Bring to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly. Cook and stir to soft ball stage (234°).
Remove from heat. Add butter. Stir in pecans.
Beat until mixture is thick enough to drop from spoon (5 or 6 minutes). Quickly drop from tablespoon onto waxed paper.
If candy becomes too stiff, add 1 teaspoon hot water.
Makes about 45 pralines.

title: chocolate nut drops
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together thoroughly.
Blend in chocolate (if using cocoa, use 1/4 cup).
Stir in milk.
Sift together and stir in the remaining ingredients (if using self-rising flour, omit soda and salt).
Stir in nuts.
Chill dough.
Drop by teaspoonful about 2 inches apart onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in moderately hot oven (400°). Frost with butter icing.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen cookies.

title: frozen banana pops
directions: Peel bananas; cut in half crosswise.
Insert a wooden stick into each banana half; place on waxed paper.
Cover; freeze 2 hours.
Combine chocolate morsels, evaporated milk and peanut butter in a small saucepan.
Cook, stirring occasionally until chocolate morsels are melted and sauce is smooth.
Dip frozen bananas into sauce; roll in nuts.
Serve immediately or freeze for later.

title: diet chili
directions: Mix together all ingredients; simmer until done.
Makes 1/2 kettle of chili, 574 calories for all.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots and diced onions.
Use 1/2 cup water from carrots and add horseradish, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Pour over carrots.
Combine butter with crumbs and add half to carrot mixture.
Put other half on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Peel zucchini and cut in quarters; remove seed and slice. Cook with other ingredients about 10 minutes.
(Pieces will look almost clear.)
Put into casserole or glass loaf dish with small amount of cooking water.
Mix together the margarine, flour, brown sugar, salt and baking powder until crumbly.
Sprinkle over top of zucchini mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: german baked beans
directions: Brown hamburg and onion in butter.
Combine with the remaining ingredients in large casserole.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
May be topped with strips of bacon before baking.

title: shrimp pilaff
directions: Partly cook and clean shrimps.
Remove bacon from pan and drain.
Add other ingredients to bacon fat.
Place in double boiler and steam over hot water for 45 minutes.
Stir in peeled, cooked shrimp and a pinch of chervil.
Turn into a casserole. Bake in a moderate oven for 15 minutes.
Serve with Mornay Sauce. Serves 6.

title: chocolate peanut clusters
directions: Combine pudding mix, sugar, milk and butter in a saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a full boil.
Boil 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in peanuts.
Beat 4 minutes, or until mixture begins to thicken.
Working rapidly, drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper. Let stand until firm.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: bonnie's favorite indonesian pork roast
directions: Brown roast on all sides in hot oil in a large Dutch oven. Drain off excess oil.
Combine next 6 ingredients; add to roast. Cover and simmer 2 1/2 hours.
Add carrots.
Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Add potatoes and onions.
Cover and cook 20 minutes or until all vegetables are tender.
(Can thicken juices with cornstarch mixed with a little water, if preferred.
Serve juices over roast and vegetables.) Serves 6.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Stir pistachio instant mix and pineapple well.
Add marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Stir well and chill.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Sift together the flour, soda, cocoa and sugar.
Add oil, then add the rest of the ingredients.
Drop by tablespoonful on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350°
oven for about 8 minutes.

title: fruited yogurt dip
directions: Beat cream cheese at medium speed until fluffy.
Add next 3 ingredients and blend well.
Stir in pineapple and coconut. Chill.
Serve as a dip with fresh fruit pieces and different kinds of melon cubes.

title: sauce pe qua
directions: Brown chicken in cooking oil; take out and add chopped onion, garlic, celery and pepper.
Fry until slightly brown, then add flour, mustard, tomato paste, chicken and sausage.
Season; let simmer about 1 hour.
Serve on rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Add the corn.
Stir in eggs and green onion dip.
Last, add cornmeal mix and taco seasoning.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken salad a l'orange
directions: Combine bite size pieces of greens with chicken, oranges, celery, olives, almonds and anise seed (optional) in a large bowl. Toss with prepared salad dressing to taste.
Serves 6.

title: homemade white bread
directions: Scald milk; stir in shortening, sugar and salt.
Put 5 1/2 cups flour in mixing bowl.
In center, place egg.
Add yeast which has been dissolved in lukewarm water.
Stir in the milk mixture and stir until smooth; this will make a stiff batter. Cover with a damp cloth.
Set in a warm place and let rise for 2 hours or until double in bulk.
Punch down.
Using the rest of the flour, turn onto a floured board and knead until firm, smooth and elastic.
Shape into 3 loaves or buns.
Cover; let rise for 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 350° for around 40 minutes.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water plus 1/2 teaspoon sugar.
Set aside and beat 1 egg slightly.
Add 3/4 cup sugar, oleo and salt. Add boiling water.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast and about 5 cups flour.
Let stand 30 minutes at room temperature.
Cover and put in refrigerator overnight or for a few hours.
Melt 1 stick oleo in pan.
Roll out dough about the thickness of biscuits. With biscuit cutter, cut out and dip in melted oleo.
Give a twist with a pull or stretch.
Let rise in pan about 2 hours at room temperature.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Mix all, except oil.
Add oil slowly and beat on high for 10 minutes.
Can be stored.
Shake well before using if stored.

title: berry punch
directions: Mix well in blender.
Makes 2 tall glasses.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Layer asparagus, peas, soup and water chestnuts.
Dip bread strips in melted butter.
Place on top and cover with cheese. Cook for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar cheese; mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients except nuts.
Mix well; chill and shape into ball.
Roll in nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: african rice
directions: Saute onion in olive oil.
Add ground chuck.
Cook until browned.
Add cabbage and saute for a few minutes, then add tomatoes (diced).
Add soy sauce and peanut butter.
Simmer until cabbage is tender.
Add cayenne pepper (to taste).
Remove from heat and stir in yogurt.
Serve over cooked white rice.

title: easy pineapple dessert
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with cookies (save 4 cookies to crumble on top of dessert).
Mix all ingredients.
Pour over cookies. Sprinkle cookie crumbs over filling.
Refrigerate overnight or until solid.
Cut into squares.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat.
Add ingredients and let simmer for 30 minutes.

title: grandmama cobb's fried apples
directions: Peel and core 3 large apples.
Cut them in slices 1/2-inch thick.
Dip each slice in cold milk, then in flour.
Put enough Crisco in frying pan to entirely cover the bottom; when hot, put in apples.
Fry on both sides to an even brown, about 2 minutes for each side.
Remove from fat; drain on soft paper.
Dust with powdered sugar; serve.

title: chocolate peanut butter rice krispies
directions: Melt butter, marshmallows and chocolate chips in microwave; stir until blended.
Add Rice Krispies; stir.
Add peanut butter chips; stir.
Blob by teaspoonful onto a greased cookie sheet and let harden.

title: hot cheese dip(for nachos, etc.)
directions: Brown bacon, add onion and saute; drain.
Melt cheese and combine all ingredients.
Put in crock-pot to keep hot.

title: sukiyaki sauce
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil.
Keep in refrigerator to use for Hekka, Sukiyaki or marinade for other meat dishes.

title: sausage and rice mix
directions: In skillet, cook sausage, cumin and garlic powder. Stir often; drain. Add onions and green peppers.
Saut until crisp and tender. Dissolve bouillon cubes in water and add to skillet. Stir in jalapeno, rice and rice seasoning and bring to a boil. Simmer uncovered for 5 to 10 minutes.
tags: long grain wild Uncle Ben's fast

title: velvet almond fudge cake
directions: Chop almonds and toast at 350° for 3 to 5 minutes.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup almonds on bottom of well-greased 10-inch tube (or two 9-inch pans).
Set aside the remainder of the almonds and the chocolate chips.
Measure remaining ingredients into a mixing bowl and blend.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Stir in chocolate chips and almonds.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes (50 to 60 for 9-inch pans) or until cake begins to pull away from the pan.
Do not underbake.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes and remove.
Finish cooling on cake rack.

title: david's picadillo
directions: Dice potatoes.
Brown and crumble ground chuck with chopped onion and garlic to taste.
When almost browned, add potatoes. Brown lightly.
Drain any grease that remains.
Add tomatoes and enough water to cover potatoes.
Cover and cook until potatoes are tender.
Add the jalapeno pepper before you cook.
Just drop it on top of potatoes.
Serve with corn bread or corn tortillas.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix and let stand overnight to blend ingredients.

title: daddy's chocolate pie
directions: Cream the butter, then slowly add the sugar while continuing to beat.
Melt chocolate and blend it in along with the vanilla. Add 1 egg and beat for 5 minutes.
Add 2nd egg and beat another 5 minutes.
Pour into a cooled, baked 8-inch crust or crumb crust. Refrigerate and cover when set up.

title: laurie's refrigerator mashed potatoes
directions: Cook peeled potatoes until tender; drain and mash (add milk sparingly).
Add remaining ingredients; beat until light and fluffy.
Cool.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: crabmeat (shrimp) appetizer
directions: Place in a bowl that can be put in a microwave the softened cream cheese and salsa; then top with Cheddar cheese, shredded. Put in microwave for 5 minutes, uncovered.

title: raisin pumpkin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, pumpkin pie spice and salt.
In another large bowl, mix together the beaten eggs, pumpkin, vegetable oil and cereal.
Add the flour mixture to the pumpkin mixture, mixing just until moistened.
Stir in the raisins and nuts.

title: sweet potato pone
directions: Mix and bake in a greased casserole or pan for 1 1/2 hours at 350° until set and brown.
More nutmeg or cinnamon may be added.

title: beef goulash
directions: Cut the meat into strips 2 inches long and 1/4 inch wide. Sprinkle the strips with pepper and paprika.
Heat the oil in a large skillet and add half the meat, cooking and stirring over high heat until meat is browned, about 3 minutes.
Using a slotted spoon, transfer the meat to another skillet.
Add the remaining beef and cook rapidly over high heat until browned.
Transfer this meat to the other skillet.
Pour off any fat remaining in the skillet.
Add the butter and onion to the skillet and cook until wilted.
Sprinkle with flour and stir.
Add the wine and tomatoes, stirring.
Cook for about 4 minutes.
Add the yogurt, stirring rapidly.
