Add any juices that have accumulated around the meat. Add the thyme.

Cook for about 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Place a strainer over the meat and strain the sauce, stirring with a wooden spoon or spatula to push through as much of the solids in the sauce as possible.
Heat thoroughly and serve with noodles or rice.
Serves 4.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Place rhubarb in pie shell.
Mix all ingredients and pour over rhubarb.
Bake in 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger, onions, salt and pepper; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until of sandwich filling consistency.

title: crab, shrimp and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and turn into a greased casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour.
Also delicious unbaked, as a salad.

title: apple pudding cake
directions: Combine ingredients; blend well.
Pat evenly into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with topping.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix and pat into a 9 x 13 pan.

title: key lime pie
directions: Allow cream cheese to come to softened stage.
Add juice and sweetened milk (coloring if used).
Use mixer until well blended. Pour on pie shell.
Let set for 6 hours or overnight.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Sift 1 cup flour over the fruit; cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and whiskey.
Mix in fruit and nuts.
Drop small bits (about 1/2 teaspoon) on cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes many; keeps well in tin or covered container.

title: meat loaf(filling for stuffed peppers)
directions: Mix all ingredients together except beef, soup mix and tomato sauce.
After mixing well, then mix in beef.
Place in sprayed loaf pan and pour tomato sauce on top.
Sprinkle with soup mix (onion flavor).
Cover with plastic wrap, leaving a vent at one corner.
Cook at 70% for 15 minutes.
Doesn't require standing time.

title: filet mignon with peppers and onions
directions: Roast peppers over gas flame or under broiler until blackened on all sides.
Place peppers in paper bag; let cool 15 minutes. Peel, stem and seed peppers.
Cut peppers into thin strips.
Heat oil in heavy large skillet over high heat.
Season steaks with salt and pepper.
Add steaks to skillet; saute to desired doneness, about 4 minutes per side for rare.
Transfer steaks to plates and tent with foil to keep warm.
Add roasted peppers and garlic to same skillet; cook for 30 seconds.
Add broth, olives and vinegar; boil until liquid is reduced to glaze, scraping up browned bits, about 8 minutes.
Mix in oregano; remove from heat.
Add butter; whisk to melt.
Season sauce to taste with salt and pepper.
Spoon sauce over and around filets and serve.

title: marshmallow salad
directions: Cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Add crushed pineapple, undrained. Stir in marshmallows.

title: mincemeat cake
directions: Mix and pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: friend of a friend's pizza
directions: Take out the 2 loaves frozen bread dough at 9:30 to 10:00 a.m.; let thaw.
Preheat oven to 390°.
Fry ground beef and ground chicken; drain fat.
Add minced onion, minced garlic and 1 teaspoon pepper; let cool.
Grease pizza pans; roll out dough 1 hour before time to eat.
(Roll dough out with flour so it doesn't stick,) Spread spaghetti sauce over dough; add meat mixture.
Add olives and pepper or whatever you like, then add cheese (half Mozzarella and half Jack).
Then add pepperoni.
Bake for approximately 20 minutes or until bottom of dough is lightly brown and top is melted.

title: easy, delicious no-bake cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese with electric mixer until fluffy.
Add Eagle Brand milk; beat until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla. Pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Chill for 3 hours.
Top with strawberry or blueberry glaze, if desired.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and 1/2 cup sugar. Combine eggs, milk and oil.
Add all at once to flour mixture. Stir until dry ingredients are moist but still lumpy.
Fold in blueberries.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in hot oven (400°) about 25 minutes.

title: ice box cookies
directions: In a large bowl, combine sugar, margarine, vanilla and eggs; blend well.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt; blend well. Stir in nuts.
Divide dough into thirds on 3 sheets of waxed paper; shape each into a roll 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Wrap; refrigerate overnight or freeze at least 2 hours or until firm. When ready to bake, heat oven to 350°.
Slice dough into 1/4 inch slices and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: venison meat loaf
directions: Combine ground venison and pork shoulder.
Add seasoned bread crumbs and egg.
Mix thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients, except bacon slices.
Mix thoroughly and pat into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Spread bacon slices over top.
Bake at 350° until done, about 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; add brown sugar, corn syrup and salt. Bring to a boil; stir constantly.
Remove from heat and add baking soda and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
Put popped corn in a large pan or bowl.
Pour syrup over popped corn and toss lightly until well coated.

title: texas cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Bring to boil the remaining ingredients.
Add at once to flour mixture and mix well.
Pour into a greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: cole slaw(diet)
directions: Combine vinegar, liquid sweetener, water, celery seed, mustard seed, salt and turmeric.
Bring to a boil.
Let cool and pour over cabbage.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown beef in saucepan.
Drain.
Add beans, pepper, tomatoes, seasoning and coating mixture, water, vinegar, and chili powder. Bring to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: lemon chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine, egg and lemon flavoring.
Spread this mixture in 9 x 12-inch pan (dampen hands to spread easier).

title: fruit cocktail parfait pie
directions: Drain fruit; save syrup.
Add enough water to syrup to make 1 cup; heat to boiling.
Add gelatin; dissolve.
Add the 1/2 cup cold water.
Cut ice cream into 6 pieces; add to hot mixture.
Stir until melted.
Chill until mixture thickens, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Fold in fruit.
Pour into vanilla crust.
Chill.

title: chocolate icebox cake
directions: Melt chocolate in top of double boiler over boiling water. Add water and blend. Remove from fire and add egg yolks, one at a time, beating vigorously after each addition until thoroughly blended.
Add sugar and nuts and mix well. Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold into chocolate mixture with whipped cream.
Line a 1 1/2-quart dish or bread loaf pan with ladyfingers.
Pour in mixture. Refrigerate 12 to 24 hours. Serve with additional whipped cream, if desired.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: shanty creek's hot crab dip
directions: Melt in double boiler the cream cheese and mayonnaise; then add other ingredients.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and pineapple. Sprinkle pudding mix over mixture and mix well. Add nuts. Refrigerate.

title: hungry jack casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown meat with onions.
Drain if necessary.
Stir in remaining ingredients, heat until bubbly.
Pour into 2 quart casserole.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix coconut and pecans.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix cake mix according to directions and pour over coconut and nut mixture.
In saucepan, heat margarine and cream cheese until mixture is warm enough to stir in sugar.
Spoon on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Do not cut until cold.

title: rumaki
directions: Cut bacon slices in half crosswise.
Wrap 1/2 slice bacon around piece of chicken liver and water chestnut slice.
Secure with wooden pick.
Arrange on broiler pan.
Combine soy sauce, brown sugar and mustard in small bowl.
Brush over bacon rolls.

title: sprite salad
directions: Mix Sprite, cream cheese, marshmallows and Jell-O on stove until melted (low heat).
Stir to blend.
Cool in refrigerator. Add other ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Cook zucchini halves until tender (15 minutes).
Lay halved zucchini in greased pan.
Spoon out insides and drain in colander. Saute hamburger; add onion, garlic and salt.
Mash bread with milk and beaten eggs.
Add hamburger mixture and zucchini from colander, plus Parmesan cheese and oregano.
Mix together and stuff halved zucchini.
May sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 325° approximately 35 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add next 4 ingredients.
After measuring, sift dry ingredients together.
Mix well.
Roll into balls.
Roll the ball in sugar and mash down with fork.
Bake 10 minutes or until lightly browned at 350°.

title: "m&m's" fudge jumbles
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Stir together brownie mix (dry), flour, oil, water and eggs in large bowl.
Stir in candies.
Drop by scant 1/4 cupfuls, 3 inches apart, onto cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or just until set and tops are dry. Let stand 2 to 3 minutes before removing from cookie sheet.
Cool completely.
Makes about 15 large cookies.

title: chunky applesauce
directions: Put all ingredients into a large pan cover and cook on medium heat for 30 to 40 minutes or until apples are tender.
Remove from heat and mash apples until sauce is desired consistency.
Serve warm or cold.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Add remaining ingredients and mix together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or place in crock-pot.

title: peppermint fudge cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake mix as directed on package.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pans.
Cool completely on wire racks.
Crush 8 mints; set aside remaining for garnish.
Spread 1 cup of the whipped topping on 1 cake layer.
Sprinkle with crushed mints. Top with second cake layer.
Frost entire cake with remaining whipped topping.
Store cake in refrigerator.
Garnish with remaining mints just before serving.

title: cherry nut pie
directions: Combine juice and milk. Fold in cherries, nuts and Cool Whip. Pour into two 8-inch crust.
Chill overnight.
Serve.

title: maple-bacon oven pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease and flour a rectangular 13 x 9-inch dish.
Beat baking mix, sugar, eggs, milk, syrup and 1/2 cup of the cheese with hand beater until smooth.
Pour into dish. Bake, uncovered, until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 10 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle pancake with remaining cheese and the bacon.
Bake, uncovered, until cheese melts, 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve with syrup.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion together; drain well.
Add soup and season; put into a buttered casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli and cheese
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Put into a 9 x 13 inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Cover with dry bread crumbs before baking.

title: pizza snacks
directions: Mix all ingredients (except bread). Spread on bread. Place on cookie sheets and bake at 400° until cheese browns, about 5 to 8 minutes.

title: blueberry-lemon loaf cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Mix in walnuts and lemon peel.
Fold in fresh blueberries.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans, bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown flour in oil, stirring to make a smooth paste.
Add meat, salt, pepper, water and tomato sauce.
Simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add vegetables and simmer until tender.
This cooks well in a crock-pot.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Put all of the ingredients in a bowl and mix together. Moisten to proper consistency with hot coffee.
Beat until creamy.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, lightly folding in bing cherries last.
Spoon into 12 paper muffin cups placed in muffin tins and freeze.
When frozen, place in plastic freezer bags.
Before serving peel off paper cups.

title: herb vinegar
directions: *Try chives, basil, tarragon, pepper, nasturtiums, fennel or garlic.

title: peach mousse(makes 2 quarts)
directions: Mix milk, sugar and peach pulp.
Add gelatin which has been soaked a few minutes in the cold water and dissolved over boiling water.
Fold in cream, whipped stiff.
Freeze.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: In large heavy saucepan, melt butter over medium-high heat. Add chicken thighs, turning until browned on all sides.
As thighs are browned, transfer to plate.
Add celery and onion to drippings in pan and cook, stirring occasionally until softened, about 5 minutes.
Stir in soup, water, and pepper; bring to a boil.
Return thighs to pan and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until chicken is cooked through, about 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in rice, peas and carrots.
Cover and let stand 5 to 8 minutes until rice is tender.

title: hobo bread
directions: Bring coffee to a boil.
Pour coffee over baking soda and raisins; let stand overnight.
Add to this mixture the sugar, brown sugar, nuts, flour and salt; mix well.
Divide batter into 3 well-greased (1-pound size) coffee cans.
Bake at 325° for 65 minutes.
Let cool in cans.
Slice; spread with cream cheese between slices.
Yields 3 loaves.

title: tuna fish cakes
directions: In bowl, combine all ingredients, except oil.
Shape into cakes.
Brown in oil in frying pan, about 12 minutes, on each side.
Serve with buttered noodles and green salad.

title: country ham barbecue
directions: Heat until sugar bubbles.
Add enough water until it is as thin as maple syrup.
Lay trimmed country ham slices in this 30 minutes or until charcoal is gray.
(Don't use hot coals.)
Watch closely and turn, then pour rest of syrup over first side.
Cook only until ham starts to brown, but not burn.
Cooks quickly. It's delicious.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Blend flour, Crisco and salt.
Combine egg, water and vinegar. Pour this into flour mixture. Mix well until flour is moistened and handles to roll out.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: turkey chili
directions: Brown turkey with onion, green pepper, chili powder and garlic.
Drain off any grease.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer.

title: date balls
directions: Combine flour and salt; sift twice.
Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, then milk and vanilla.
Stir in flour.
Blend in dates.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes or until light brown. While still warm, roll in confectioners sugar.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Boil broccoli until tender; drain and place in casserole dish. Mix soup and sour cream with broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese over mixture.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 325°.
Cover dish with foil while baking.

title: 5 cup dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Chill a few hours before serving.

title: chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Boil chicken breasts.
Let cool.
Strip into little pieces.
Place in bottom of baking dish.
Mix soup and sour cream together.
Place on top of chicken.
Crumble crackers on top of mixture.
Put butter on top of crackers. Bake until crackers are slightly brown.

title: tuna a la king
directions: Combine ingredients in skillet until bubbly.
Serve on top of cornbread.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Combine flour, soda and sugar; cut in shortening.
Add yeast mixture and buttermilk; mix with hands until dough is formed.
May be made into biscuits immediately or kept in refrigerator as long as two weeks (if air is worked out everyday), then make into biscuits as needed.
Bake fifteen minutes at 375°.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen biscuits.

title: pork balls with rice
directions: Mix meat; chop onion and add to meat.
Add washed rice. Combine crumbs, beaten egg, salt, pepper and milk and mix with rice and meat.
Mix well.
Form in balls.
Put in roasting pan. Pour tomato soup over meat balls.
Cover pan and bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Baste and add water if necessary so balls won't be dry.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Drain spinach; press between paper towels to remove excess moisture.
Combine spinach, cottage cheese and egg substitute in a medium bowl; stir well and set aside.

title: "any night" casserole
directions: In skillet, brown beef in butter.
Add carrots and celery; cook slowly until nearly tender.
Stir in soup mix and water.
Transfer to 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until meat is tender.
Stir in rice.
Cover and bake an additional 15 minutes. Serve with Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Serves 4.

title: nate newton's easy corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish in 400° oven.
Add remaining ingredients to melted butter.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 to 40 minutes, or until golden.
You can also add chopped green chiles and/or grated cheese to casserole if you like.

title: quick and easy butterscotch fudge
directions: Cook to soft ball stage, stirring all the time.
Beat until creamy.
Pour in buttered pan.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Cream butter flavored Wesson oil with sugar, vanilla and eggs. Stir together flour, cinnamon, salt and soda.
Beat into first mixture.
Fold in undrained pineapple, diced bananas, pecans and coconut.
Bake at 350° for about 55 minutes in a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Let stand for ten minutes and glaze.

title: 4-layer dessert(low-fat)
directions: First Layer: Melt stick of butter and mix with flour and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Spread into nonstick pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: cocoa apple cake
directions: Cream together until fluffy eggs, sugar, margarine and water. Sift together flour, cocoa, baking soda, cinnamon and allspice. Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Fold in walnuts, semi-sweet chocolate bits, grated apples and vanilla; mix well.
Spoon into greased and floured 10-inch loose bottom tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and milk.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Add nuts, bananas and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: braised shrimp with vegetables
directions: Combine cornstarch, broth, oyster sauce, ginger, sugar and pepper in small bowl; mix well.
Set aside.
Remove stems from broccoli.
Discard.
Chop head of broccoli and remaining stems; set aside.
Peel shells from shrimp.
Remove veins with knife.
Heat oil in wok or large skillet over high heat.
Add shrimp; stir-fry until shrimp turn pink, about 3 minutes.
Add broccoli to wok; stir-fry 1 minute.
Add mushrooms and bamboo shoots; stir-fry 1 minute.
Stir cornstarch mixture.
Add to wok.
Cook and stir until sauce boils and thickens, about 2 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hawaiian cranberry float punch
directions: Combine cranberry and pineapple juices and soda in bowl.
Add sherbet by small scoopfuls.
Makes 8 servings.

title: four fold delight
directions: Mix and press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake until light brown.

title: chicken paprika
directions: In a large Ziploc bag, shake chicken pieces in salt, pepper, paprika and flour until well coated.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend with a whip (this makes it creamier).

title: fruit cake
directions: Bring to a boil the water, raisins, sugar and shortening. Add to mixture while still hot the fruit and nuts.
Sift and add to cooled mixture the soda, salt, cinnamon, allspice, cloves, nutmeg and flour.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Take out of pans when cool.
Makes about 3 loaves.

title: super simple sheet cake
directions: Place the 1/4 cup oil in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Tilt to cover bottom.
Add cake mix and 2 eggs and 1 1/3 cups water.
Stir with fork until blended.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: Dredge meat in flour after cutting meat in 1 to 2-inch cubes. Brown in 2 to 3 tablespoons hot oil in large cooking pot.
Saute garlic with meat.
Brown meat on all sides.
Add tomatoes, water and spices.
Bring to low simmer.
Cook 1 1/2 hours until meat is tender.
Add diced vegetables (other vegetables may be added according to taste).
Cook 45 minutes or longer until tender.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs.
Cream well.
Add pineapple and juice.
Add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Add nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken jambalaya
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and garlic in hot oil in a skillet, stirring frequently, until tender. Stir in meats and cook 5 minutes. Add all remaining ingredients and place in a greased casserole dish. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 8.

title: wild  rice soup
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Brown beef and drain.
Add all ingredients together and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: frijoles a la charra
directions: Soak dry beans overnight.
Rinse and place in 10-quart pot full of hot water.
Cook with salt for 2 hours over medium flame. In skillet, place salt bacon and the rest of the ingredients and saute.
Add all to beans and cook until beans are tender and Yum Yum Buenos!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli and drain, then mix cream of broccoli, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
In casserole dish, layer broccoli, then soup mixture, then stir in 1/2 can of dried onions.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
At last 5 minutes of cooking, add remaining onions and cook until lightly browned (check often).

title: yum yum cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together until light and fluffy. Stir in pineapple, add flour which has been sifted with baking powder. Mix well and spread batter into well greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Add topping.

title: grandmas molasses creams
directions: Add baking soda last.
Cream sugar, shortening and egg.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by tablespoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mock sirloin tips
directions: Cut round steak into bite-sized pieces.
Heat cooking oil in a heavy skillet (will need a tightly fitting lid) and brown meat evenly.
Add seasonings and Worcestershire sauce and stir to mix. Add water and bring all just to a boil, reduce heat to lowest setting and put lid on pan.
Cook 1 hour.
Do not remove lid.
In saucepan, melt 1/2 stick margarine and add flour, stirring with fork over medium heat until nicely browned.
Remove from heat. When done, remove meat with slotted spoon to inverted lid.
Measure pan liquid for 2 cups (add water if needed to make 2 cups).
Add liquid to roux in saucepan to make gravy, stirring constantly over medium heat until bubbly.
If too thick, may add up to 1/2 cup water.
Reduce heat.
In the skillet, melt 2 tablespoons margarine and saute onions.
Add drained mushrooms and lightly sprinkle with garlic powder.
Mix well.
Return meat to skillet and toss lightly together to heat and mix.
The gravy is great served over mashed potatoes or rice.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all together and bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Batter rises as it cooks and falls when it is done.
Freezes well.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and boil for 3 minutes.
Let cool and start to thicken.
Add cottage cheese, pineapple and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.
Fits well in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: hamburger roll-ups
directions: Brown crumbled ground beef, onions, pepper and seasonings over medium-high heat until done, about 10 minutes.
Add tomato sauce and mix thoroughly (you may add 1/2 cup shredded cheese at this time, if desired).
Separate uncooked crescent rolls and spoon hamburger mixture onto dough (heaping tablespoonful) and roll as package directs.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Serve with tossed salad or fresh fruit.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and vanilla.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Fold in pecans and apples.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions thin.
Sprinkle salt over the top. Cover with cold water and let stand 1 hour.

title: hunter's stew
directions: Brown
ground
beef;
drain
fat.
In large pan combine ground beef,
potatoes,
peas
and
carrots.
Add just enough water
to cover vegetables.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until potatoes and carrots are tender.
Stir in gravy mix and simmer until slightly thickened.	(Can also be done in a crock-pot.)

title: butter frosting
directions: Let stand in a bowl to soften margarine and sugar.
In a small pan, add milk and flour over low flame.
Stir constantly until it forms a paste; remove from stove and cool completely.
Then add to margarine mixture and beat thoroughly (about 3 minutes) with electric mixer until it looks like butter.
Add Nestle's chocolate or cocoa, if you want chocolate frosting.
Frosts a 9 x 13-inch cake, regular cake or 24 cupcakes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together in a casserole dish. Sprinkle Ritz crackers, crumbled, on top.
Melt butter over top. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: corn-jalapeno casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions; set aside.
Saute onion, green pepper and celery in oleo until vegetables are tender.
Combine rice, sauteed vegetables and next 3 ingredients, stirring well.
Spoon mixture into a slightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Garnish with green pepper rings, cherry tomatoes and parsley, if desired. Yield:
12 servings.

title: fancy salad
directions: Mix ingredients, while chilling can of evaporated milk.
Whip until doubles in size.
Fold in evaporated milk.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Refold.
Put in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Must be refrigerated at least 4 to 6 hours in order to cut.

title: deer steak special
directions: Put deer steaks in a bowl and add all spices.
Cover and let set for several hours in the refrigerator.
Cook on a grill, making sure each piece is done.

title: california wine cake
directions: Mix ingredients for 4 minutes at medium speed.
Fold in pecans after mixing.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes and remove from pan.

Sprinkle top with powdered sugar or mix 1 stick butter, 1 cup sugar and 1/4 cup of same type of wine used in cake; boil them 3 minutes and pour over cake while hot, letting stand in pan at least 30 minutes to cool.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat brown sugar, shortening and eggs together and add remaining ingredients.
Mix together and drop by tablespoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: herbed carrots
directions: Scrub carrots; cut in half lengthwise and crosswise.
Cut onions, including tops, into 1-inch pieces.
Melt butter in a saucepan.
Add carrots, onions, water and herbs, plus a little salt and pepper.
Cover and cook until tender, about 20 minutes. Cut bacon into 1-inch pieces; fry until crisp.
Add to carrots just before serving.
Serves 4.

title: egg pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar well, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked shell.
With metal spoon, remove foam from top of pie.
Bake at 425° for approximately 30 minutes.
Pie will still be shaky, but will finish cooking after being taken from the oven.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies(child snack recipe)
directions: In a medium glass bowl, blend sugar and syrup.
Microwave sugar and syrup on High for 2 1/2 minutes or until mixture comes to a full boil.
Stir in cereal and peanut butter.
Drop by teaspoonful on wax paper.

title: super guacamole
directions: Mash all together.
Serve with tacos or chips.
Serves 10.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Make white sauce out of butter, salt, milk, flour and pepper. Place half of the potatoes in greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover with half of the onion and half of the sauce.
Repeat layers. Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: poppy seed chicken for brian
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove skin and bones; chop chicken into small pieces.
Place in bottom of large casserole dish.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Crush crackers; mix with poppy seed.
Sprinkle on top of soup mixture. Melt butter; pour evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peggy's punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 9 cups water.
Combine sugar in 4 cups water; bring to boil.
Add to Jell-O mixture and cool.
When cool, add lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Mix well; freeze.
Before serving, add ginger ale or 7-Up.

title: sun bakkels
directions: Press in Sun Bakkel tins and bake 15 minutes at 375°.
These come out of the tins easy.

title: bun candy
directions: Melt both kinds of chips and peanut butter in double boiler. Spread half of the mixture in buttered 10 X 15 pan. Chill. Cook butter, milk and pudding mix for 1 minute. Add powdered sugar and mix well. Spread over chip mixture. Refrigerate. Cut into squares. Makes 5 pounds.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and powder and salt.
Cream together shortening, sugar and mix with flour mixture. Add beaten eggs, vanilla, sour cream and nuts.
Mix.
Drop onto cookie sheet.
Flatten with a glass.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add milk and cook, stirring constantly until thick.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Beat egg yolks until creamy and add to hot mixture.
Cook 2 to 3 more minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in rind, juice and butter.

title: brisket (5 to 6 pounds)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on brisket, wrap in heavy-duty foil.
Refrigerate overnight, fat side up.
Bake in 275° oven for 5 hours or until done.
Cool and remove, slice.
To warm up, place in juice or barbecue sauce.

title: campfire stew
directions: In large kettle or saucepan, cook ground beef and onion over medium heat 8 to 10 minutes or until meat is browned and onion is tender.
Drain if necessary.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Cover; simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated, stirring occasionally.
Yields 7 (1 cup) servings.

title: turkey and dressing rolls
directions: Make dressing according to directions on Stove Top box.
For each roll use 2 large pieces of turkey.
Place 2 tablespoons dressing on turkey and roll up.
Place seam-side down in 9 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Spoon gravy across center of rolls. Bake in 325°
oven for 30 minutes until heated through.

title: snack mix
directions: Mix. Let set for several hours and eat!

title: chinese chews
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients as for pie dough. Pat firmly into pan and partially bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip banana bread
directions: Place butter or margarine in large bowl and mix with an electric mixer.
Mix until well blended and creamy.
Add milk, bananas, eggs and vanilla.
Mix until blended.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, salt and soda.
Stir to combine all dry ingredients and add to butter mixture.
Mix until just blended. Stir in chocolate chips and pour into loaf pan which has been sprayed with a nonstick vegetable spray.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 60 minutes or until tester inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool in pan.

title: carnation pumpkin pie
directions: Combine eggs, pumpkin, sugar, salt and spices.
Gradually add evaporated milk.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 15 minutes.
Reduce to moderate heat (350°) and continue baking about 40 minutes or until knife inserted near center of pie comes out clean.
Cool before serving.

title: waffles
directions: Combine all ingredients except egg whites.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.

title: potato and cheese casserole
directions: Cook potatoes with chopped onion until tender; drain.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add diced cheese and mayonnaise; mix well. Place in baking dish and top with the bacon that has been cooked and crumble over top.
Sliced olives may be added.
Bake at 300° for approximately 30 to 35 minutes.

title: gena's blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease 12 muffin pan cups with nonstick cooking spray.
In large bowl, sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sweetener.
Mix well and set aside.
In small bowl, beat together egg, milk and margarine with fork or wire whisk.
Add egg mixture and blueberries to flour mixture.
Stir just until flour is moistened.
Spoon batter in muffin cups.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 1/2 cup of cheese and tomatoes.
Layer half of vegetable mixture and tomatoes in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with remaining vegetable mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and tomato wedges; continue baking for 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: winter fruit bowl
directions: Pare and section grapefruit, reserving juice.
Set grapefruit sections aside.
Add enough water to juice to measure 1 cup; combine with sugar and marmalade.
Heat to boiling, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Add cranberries; cook and stir until skins pop (5 to 8 minutes).
Remove from heat; cool.
Add grapefruit.
Cover and chill.
Just before serving, slice bananas into chilled grapefruit mixture.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Chill.
Roll out on floured board and cut how you want.
Bake at 350°.

title: ham and cheese snacks
directions: Combine 3/4 cup of each cheese, chopped ham, light cream and the spices in top of a double boiler.
Heat until the cheeses melt.
Spread the warm mixture on the cocktail bread slices. Sprinkle with the remaining cheese and broil lightly.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Beat and bake in uncooked pie crust at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: lemon salad supreme
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Chill until mixture begins to thicken.
Beat well and add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 2-quart mold.
Chill until set.
Unmold and serve on salad greens.

title: kentucky caramel dumplings
directions: Brown sugar in large skillet.
Add hot water, oleo and sugar. Let simmer until all is dissolved.
This may be transferred to large baking dish.

title: jo ann's divinity
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water until mixture reaches 255° on candy thermometer.
Pour slowly over stiffly beaten egg whites. Add vanilla and nuts. Drop on waxed paper.

title: thai shrimp and sesame noodles
directions: About 1 hour and 20 minutes before serving:
In medium bowl, mix shrimp with 1/3 cup salad dressing.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.

title: bran muffin mix
directions: Combine boiling water and bran.
Let set.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, bran and buttermilk.
Add flour with salt and soda.
Store, covered, in refrigerator.
Will keep for 2 months.
Use as needed.
Grease muffin tins or use cupcake papers. Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 48 to 50 muffins.
Recipe may be halved.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, lay in mushrooms.
Fill with ingredients, combined.
Add small amount of water.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cover with foil.
Remove foil last 15 to 20 minutes.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Chop
up
lettuce
and green onions.
Pour bacon grease over it.
Put in microwave oven and wilt.
Add vinegar, if you like. Reheat leftovers in microwave.

title: pecan pie squares
directions: Beat flour, sugar, margarine and salt in large bowl until crumbly (mixture will be dry).
Press firmly into greased pan. Bake about 20 minutes until light golden brown.

title: linguine salad
directions: Break linguine into 1-inch pieces.
Cook using package directions; drain well.
Combine cauliflower, onion, broccoli and olives in bowl; toss to mix.
Add linguine, salad dressing and seasoning mix; mix well.
Chill before serving.
Yield:
24 servings.

title: chocolate crunch pie
directions: Melt butter; mix together and press down into baking pan. Bake for 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Stir 2 or 3 times.
Save 1/2 cup for topping.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice lengthwise 3/8 to 1/2-inch thick.
Melt butter in large, heavy skillet.
Add potatoes, lightly browning all on both sides.
Sprinkle sugar, cinnamon and salt over potatoes, then drizzle with syrup.
Add water; gently fold all ingredients together.
Cover skillet and simmer over low heat for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken in large kettle or Dutch oven with bouillon cubes, onion, celery and seasonings.
When done, remove chicken from pot.
Cover chicken and place in oven to keep warm.

title: bar cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Beat in egg yolk, add flour and cinnamon;
press into a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan.
Brush top with slightly beaten egg white, sprinkle nuts on top and press into dough.
Cook 1 hour at 275°.
Drizzle top with melted chocolate.

title: strawberry mousse
directions: Mix jello and milk together by hand; then add other ingredients.
Mix and then refrigerate 1 1/2 hours.
Also good frozen.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Beat cheese and milk until well blended.
Add Cool Whip and sugar.
Stir in pineapple, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into pie shells.
Sprinkle chopped pecans on top of pie.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: creamy icing
directions: Mix egg and 10x sugar thoroughly.
Boil water and 1/4 cup granulated sugar for 1 minute, then add to sugar and egg.
Blend well and add Crisco and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Roll into balls (about the size of large marbles).
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes or until brown. Keep warm in a chafing dish.
Makes about 190 appetizers.
These may be made ahead and frozen.

title: lentils with lemon dressing (adas mtabbal)
directions: Boil the lentils in water for 40 minutes or until tender. Crush garlic with salt and add lemon juice and oil.
Drain lentils and put them in a shallow bowl.
Pour on the dressing and garnish with chopped parsley and hot pepper.
Serve one hour later. Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: small pudding
directions: Cook mixture in double boiler.
If you like you can use coconut, crushed pineapple or any kind of fruit.
Line dish with vanilla wafers, Ritz crackers and graham crackers and pour mixture in, then brown beaten whites of eggs with 2 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla flavoring.

title: mini meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Form round in a teaspoon; cook until brown.

title: lemon-coconut pudding cake
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar in a 1 1/2-quart bowl until stiff peaks form; set aside.
Beat egg yolks slightly.
Beat in lemon peel, lemon juice and milk.
Add sugar, flour and salt; beat until smooth.
Fold into beaten egg whites.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole; sprinkle with coconut.

title: mushroom barley pilaf
directions: Wash, dry and slice mushrooms.
Saute onions and mushrooms in the margarine in a large skillet for 4 to 5 minutes.
Transfer to a large casserole.
Add barley and pimento.
Stir in broth and pepper.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until barley is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Additional water may be needed during cooking if mixture seems dry.
This pilaf can also be cooked on stove top in a large kettle.
Cook on low heat for 45 minutes.

title: bobbie andy pie
directions: In a medium bowl, mix together sugars, flour, cinnamon, cloves and salt.
In another bowl, mix together eggs, milk, butter and vanilla.
Combine both mixtures together.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat, slowly and drain off excess grease.
Add garlic, (1 Tbsp.) parsley, basil, 1 1/2 tsp. salt, tomatoes and tomato paste. Simmer uncovered until thickened - about 45 minutes.
Cook noodles in boiling salted water until tender (10 -12 minutes).
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Combine eggs, pepper, parsley, and parmesan cheese.
Spoon 1/2 noodles into buttered 13 x 9 x 2 baking pan. Spoon 1/2 of egg mixture over noodles.
Layer 1/2 of Mozzarella cheese slices over mixture.
Spread 1/2 of meat mixture over cheese.
Repeat layers once.
Bake at 375 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together until crumbly.
Press half of the crumbs into a greased 9-inch baking pan.
Cover with rhubarb.
Take the next 4 ingredients and combine and cook them until thick and clear.
Pour over rhubarb in baking dish.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until rhubarb is tender.
Can put ice cream or whipped cream topping.

title: peanut butter crisscross
directions: In a large bowl, mix thoroughly the shortening, peanut butter, both sugars and the egg.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda and salt in a separate bowl, then stir it into the first bowl.
Chill dough for 1/2 to 1 hour.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Let cucumbers, onions and salt stand in ice water 3 hours, then drain.
Combine vinegar, sugar and spices; bring to boil for 5 minutes.
Add cucumbers and onions.
Bring to simmering point. Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: burger bundles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix meat, soup mix, egg, pepper, water and bread crumbs.
Press into bottom of 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. Prick meat mixture with fork.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes, or to desired cooking time.
Drain.
Place Velveeta slices over meat.
Bake one minute or until cheese begins to melt.
Cut into 24 squares.
Layer dinner roll, burger square, pickle slice and dinner roll.
Makes 24.

title: pickled beets and eggs
directions: Boil beets until tender.
Remove skins.
Tie spices in cheesecloth.
Heat vinegar, water and spices to boiling point. Add beets and boil 5 minutes.
Cool.
Add shelled hard-boiled eggs to spicy liquid with beets.
Refrigerate 1 or more days.
Eggs take on a beautiful red color and spicy flavor.
Serve whole or halved with sliced or whole beets as side dish or relish.

title: dump pound cake
directions: Put all ingredients in one large bowl.	Beat about 5 to 10 minutes.
Bake
in a greased and floured tube pan in a 325° oven for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Grease 12-cup muffin pans.
Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately to creamed mixture with milk and vanilla.
Crush 1/2 cup berries and add to batter.
Fold remaining berries into batter and spoon into muffin pan.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan 5 minutes and turn out onto wire rack.
Makes about 18 muffins.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Blend mix.
To use, put 1/3 cup mix to 1 mug of hot water.

title: homemade chicken soup
directions: Boil chicken until done; remove skin, fat and bones.
Chunk into broth.
Add potatoes, onion and carrots.
Simmer until tender.
If using fresh okra, add with carrots.
If frozen, add with all canned vegetables after carrots are tender.
Season with salt and pepper and simmer.
Add rice and simmer until rice is done.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by teaspoon in hot vegetable oil.

title: done been buttered bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon mixture into (12) cupcake pan.
Bake in preheated oven (450° to 475°) for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and eggs together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Use 9 x 9-inch pan for thick and 9 x 13-inch for thin.

title: elmer's white cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Add flour mixture to butter and sugar mixture, alternating with vanilla which has been added to milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix ingredients and spread in oblong cake pan.

title: nacho dip
directions: Fry beef; add taco mix.
Mix beans and 1/2-quart sour cream together.
Spread in bottom of baking dish.
Put beef mixture on top of beans.
Then sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.
Take out of oven and spread remaining sour cream on top, then sprinkle olives on.
Dip with your favorite chips.

title: chili pie
directions: Layer 2 1/2 cups corn chips, onion, 3/4 cup cheese and chili in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with remaining corn chips.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 25 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: apricot jello
directions: Put fruit cocktail along with syrup in a 1-quart bowl.
Put fruit cocktail in a microwave for 3 minutes.
Stir in jello and refrigerate until it begins to thicken.
Mix Dream Whip packet as directed, omitting vanilla.
Blend cream cheese into already whipped topping.
Add the whipped topping into already thickened jello mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: flank steak with mustard-caper sauce
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon of butter with oil in a wide frying pan over medium-high heat.
Place meat in pan and cook, uncovered, until meat is browned on both sides but still pink in center (5 to 6 minutes total).
Transfer meat to a carving board.
Cover loosely to keep warm.
Over low heat, melt remaining 3 tablespoons of butter in pan drippings.
Mix in wine, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and capers.
Stir briskly to blend.
Cut meat across the grain into slanting slices.
Spoon sauce over meat.
Serves 4.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add salsa, garlic salt and chili powder; mix well.
Spread a heaping tablespoonful of mixture on each tortilla.
Roll up each tortilla tightly (jelly roll style).
Place seam side down on baking sheet.
Cover and chill for 2 hours.
Slice each roll into four pieces.
Top each piece with guacamole (optional).

title: death by chocolate
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool cake, then poke holes in top with a 2-pronged fork. Pour 1 cup Kahlua over cake and let it sit overnight.

title: tuna patties(serves 6)
directions: Combine all ingredients except 3 tablespoons potato flakes and butter.
Form mixture into 6 patties.
Coat both sides of patties with remaining flakes.
Melt butter.
Fry tuna patties until golden brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels before serving.

title: fannie mae mint cake
directions: Cream 1/2 cup margarine, sugar, eggs, vanilla, Hershey syrup and flour.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: crabbies
directions: Combine ingredients.
Spread onto uncooked muffins.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then lightly brown under broiler.

title: beef with peppers and paprika cream sauce
directions: Cut meat into about 2-inch long strips.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika, blending well with fingers to coat meat.
Heat half of butter in heavy skillet.
Add onions and bell peppers. Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Cook about 5 minutes, stirring.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add eggs and vanilla. Add flour and soda.
Mix well; then add your pecans and chips. Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Cook at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until cookies begin to turn brown.

title: favorite pork chop dinner
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large skillet, brown pork chops.
Place pork chops in ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan; drain liquid. Arrange sweet potatoes around pork chops.
Pour syrup over pork chops and sweet potatoes and in bottom of pan.
Arrange biscuits next to chops and potatoes.
Return to oven.
Bake, uncovered, 17 to 25 minutes or until biscuits are brown and pork chops are tender.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Mix yeast in warm water.
Beat eggs; add sugar, oil and salt. Mix all together.
Mix in flour until smooth.
Let sit until double.
Divide dough in half, roll out in circle.
Cut in triangle shaped pieces, roll each from large end to small end.
Put in greased pan, let rise.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: nanny craig's fudge
directions: Combine chocolate, sugar, milk, butter and salt in medium saucepan.
Bring to boil on high, stirring constantly.
Continue to boil on low or until mixture forms a soft ball in cold water. Add vanilla and nuts.
Beat until mixture will just hold its shape.
Immediately pour into buttered pan.
Let cool.

title: heavenly carrots(serves 6)
directions: Place cooked, drained carrots in a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Stir in croutons and cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over carrots. Bake, uncovered, in a hot oven at 400° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: fried apples
directions: Slice apples into 1/2 inch thick slices. Melt butter in large skillet and add apples.
Sprinkle sugar and seasonings over apples.
Cook over medium heat until apples are tender but not mushy. stirring frequently.
Apples will brown slightly.
Serve while still warm.
Excellent with ham or pork.

title: coca-cola congealed salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and hot water.
Stir 2 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients and refrigerate.

title: dump cake(quick and easy)
directions: Dump the filling, pineapple, cake mix and walnuts in a bowl and mix.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and dot top with the margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Very moist; no need for icing.

title: mexican salad
directions: Bake cornbread at 350° until brown.
Let cool.
Crumble cornbread and mix other ingredients.

title: shake pickles
directions: Fill gallon jar with sliced cucumbers and onions.
Heat remaining ingredients until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over cucumbers and onions.
Shake once each day for 7 days.
Ready to eat.
Omit onions if you want.

title: chocolate syrup for ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients but vanilla.
Boil for 3 minutes. Remove and add vanilla.
If too thick when cool, add a little milk.
Keeps well in refrigerator.
Heat for hot syrup.

title: stroganoff casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Stir in mushroom soup and sour cream. In 9 x 13 pan, roll out crescent rolls in bottom of the pan (just like they come out of the can). Pour meat mixture on top of crescent rolls. Top with shredded cheese. Bake at 350° until bubbly and rolls are brown.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Mix flour and 2 tablespoons of brown sugar.
Work in the 1/2 cup margarine.
Press into a 9-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: justin wilson's hush puppies
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Add the buttermilk and oil. Drop by large spoon into hot cooking oil.
Makes approximately 2 dozen.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Mix lemon, sugar, flour, salt, egg yolks and butter together. Add milk and beaten egg whites.
Stir well and put in unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: lee's caramel sauce
directions: Bring sugar, syrup and butter to soft ball stage (235° to 240°).
Partially cool.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly.

title: congo squares
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Melt shortening. Add brown sugar and stir until mixed.
Cool.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients, nuts and chocolate bits. Pour into baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook and mash potatoes as usual with small amount of milk. Add all rest of ingredients; blend into potatoes.
May be made day before using.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 450° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Mix
shortening, egg, cocoa and sugar. Stir in the milk and remaining dry ingredients. Add nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: onion-hominy bake
directions: Drain hominy, reserving 1/4 cup of liquid.
Chop half the French fried onions.
Combine hominy, reserved liquid, chopped onions, green beans, soup, cheese and Worcestershire sauce.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Uncover; top with remaining onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes more.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon and remove from pan.
Saute onion in bacon drippings.
Add vinegar, sugar and water.
Thicken with cornstarch.
Slice potatoes into mixture.
Add salt and bacon. Keep warm until served.

title: brown sugar frosting
directions: Combine the first four ingredients.
Boil on low for about 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Do not let it reach soft ball stage.
Remove from heat to cool.
Add powdered sugar to desired thickness.
Add maple flavoring.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Saute chopped onion in large skillet.
Add 1/2 cup of Cheddar, 1/2 cup of Jack, green onion, olives, green chilies, sour cream, cream of chicken soup, Minute rice and half of the enchilada sauce.
Layer mixture with the tortillas.
(Layer tortilla, then 1/3 of mixture, tortillas, 1/3 mixture, etc.).
On top of the casserole, pour remaining canned sauce and sprinkle on rest of the cheeses.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let set for 15 minutes.
Cut and serve.
(Layer in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass or metal pan.)

title: coffee can bread
directions: Mix 2 cups flour with yeast.
Stir in water, milk, butter, sugar and salt over low heat until butter melts.
Cool 5 minutes and pour over flour-yeast mixture.
Stir; add remaining flour and eggs.
Dough will be stiff.
Knead on floured board until dough is smooth and elastic.
Coat the inside of cans or pan with grease. Divide dough in half.
Place in cans (upright).
Cover with plastic lids (if made into rolls, cover with towel).
Let rise in warm place until dough reaches 1-inch from top of can.
Remove lids.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes, until top sounds hollow when tapped and cake tester comes out clean.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Cream together shortening and 1-cup sugar.
Add egg and molasses; beat on low speed until well mixed. Stir together all remaining dry ingredients except 1/2 cup sugar. Add to molasses mixture and mix well.
Form dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in remaining sugar.
Place 2-3-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheets until firm.
Remove carefully with spatula.

title: cucumber dip
directions: On a paper towel, cut and remove seeds from the cucumber. Finely chop the cucumber and drain.
Stir together the yogurt, soup mix and dill.
Put in a covered container and refrigerate for 2 hours or more.
Stir in the sour cream and cucumber.
Serve. Makes approximately 3 cups.

title: seven-layer salad
directions: Prepare approximately 12 hours before serving.
Layer in the order given:
broccoli, cauliflower, onion, mayonnaise, bacon, Parmesan and sugar.
Spread layers evenly in a large, covered container.
After several hours; stir to coat.
Let set, then stir several more times.
Salad gets creamier each time it is stirred.

title: orange glazed fruit
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix Tang with pineapple juice.
Add vanilla pudding to the Tang/pineapple mixture.
Mix well.
Slice bananas and stir into the pudding mixture.
Add Mandarin oranges and pineapple chunks.
Mix.

title: four bean salad
directions: Mix all drained beans in large bowl.
Pour rest of ingredients over beans; cover.
Marinate several hours or overnight.
Stir twice.

title: creamy eggs and cheese
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add cheese and water; cook slowly, stirring, until cheese melts.
Add eggs, salt and pepper. Cook slowly until eggs are set, scraping mixture frequently during cooking.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients (except eggs) in order given, then fold in eggs.
(Eggs can be omitted, if desired.)
Cook 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: pasta fagioli
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together, then add all spices.
Then add beans and tomatoes to the burger.
When boiling ditalini, cook the celery with it.
Then add everything together.
Simmer about 1 hour.
Very good.
Spices are all added to taste.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a rapid boil.
Pour over flour and sugar.
Blend well with mixer.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into greased and floured oblong pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Leave in pan.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Place margarine in a bowl.
Once melted, add flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in half and half, water and bouillon until thickened.
Stir in chicken and mushrooms.
Heat for 5 to 8 minutes, continually stirring.
Serve over pastry shells.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake mix in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Prepare pudding.
Crumble 1/3 of cake in bottom of punch bowl.
Add cut up bananas, peaches and pineapple.
Top with 1/3 of pudding.
Crumble rest of cake on top of this.
Add pears, then pie filling and then mandarin orange sections.
Scatter cherries throughout.
Top with rest of pudding, then Cool Whip.

title: white mountain frosting
directions: Put sugar, water and
corn
syrup
over slow fire; stir until sugar is dissolved	and
mixture
begins to boil.
Cover for 2 to 3 minutes
to wash down crystals.
While syrup cooks, beat egg whites and cream
of
tartar
until whites are stiff. Allow syrup to boil vigorously	until
it spins a thread.
Add marshmallows and remove from
fire.
Pour
syrup
very
slowly over egg whites, beating
constantly.
Be sure that syrup goes into egg whites and not on the side of bowl.
Beat until cool, frosting should hold its shape when dropped from spoon.

title: pineapple mush(fast and easy!  a terrific side dish)
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl and pour into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Goes great with ham!

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and lay on a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make crust, closing all perforations. Bake as directed on package.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Toss all ingredients and refrigerate 1 hour.

title: baked apple wedges
directions: *McIntosh apples have the best texture for this dessert because they become soft without falling apart.

title: pennies from heaven
directions: Mix all with hands and make into small balls. Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° approximately 10 minutes or until color you like.
Keep in tins.
Freezes well.

title: broccoli or cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook veggies 5 to 7 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients to drained veggies.
Butter casserole dish and add vegetables. Sprinkle with crumbs on top and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: bum burgers
directions: Mix together meat, 1/4 cup barbecue sauce and seasonings. Shape into four patties.
Place patties on greased grill over hot coals.
Grill, uncovered, to desired doneness, brushing frequently with remaining barbecue sauce.
For each sandwich, fill bun with patty.

title: chicken with pasta
directions: Pour olive oil in pan.
Saute onion and garlic for 5 minutes. Add chicken; sprinkle with pepper.
After the chicken is browned, add the rest of the ingredients (except pasta); simmer for 20 minutes, or until vegetables are done to your taste.
Cook pasta. Toss everything with Parmesan cheese in a large bowl.
Serve hot.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and garlic.
Add tomatoes (break up with fork).
Stir in tomato sauce.
Add
1 1/2 tablespoons
parsley flakes, sugar, 1 teaspoon
salt, basil and 1 teaspoon
oregano.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: yummy crunch peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In mixing bowl, cream the butter and sugar.
Beat in egg, vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir in the rest of the ingredients until all mixed together.
Drop by rounded spoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, or until brown.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill overnight.

title: apricot spiced tea
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together in a bowl.
Store in containers with lids.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Butter a large casserole dish.
Sprinkle onion soup evenly on bottom.
Sprinkle rice over soup.
Place chicken pieces on rice. Mix mushroom soup and water; pour over chicken.
Dot with butter. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cook and bone chicken breasts.
Tear tortillas and line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine all other ingredients and pour in pan.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: spinach or broccoli casserole(club member: ben steadman)
directions: Cook broccoli or spinach until tender; drain. Mix with all other ingredients. Sprinkle top with Cheese Nip crackers.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together and pour in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Crumble Ritz crackers and mix with margarine; pour on top of vegetables. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift flour; measure.
Add baking powder, salt and sugar.
Sift again and add corn meal.
Mix thoroughly.
Combine egg, milk and melted shortening; pour into flour mixture and stir just enough to moisten the dry ingredients.
Do not beat.
Turn into a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan and bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cut into squares and serve hot.

title: pig picking cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in 3 cake pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt butter.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in broccoli.
Add jalapeno peppers and cottage cheese; mix into Jiffy cornbread mix. Blend well.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Mix eggs, butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and milk to flour. Knead dough enough to roll out.
Roll dough thin and cut out.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: any color punch
directions: In a gallon jug, mix together all ingredients.
Fill remaining gallon jug with water; mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Wash cranberries and grind in blender; add sugar and refrigerate overnight.

title: shrimply chick-enchanting
directions: Combine sour cream, gravy mix and salt.
Divide in half and refrigerate one half.
Coat chicken with remaining sour cream mixture, then roll in the cornflake crumbs.
Melt butter in a shallow baking pan.
Arrange chicken in pan, skin side down.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Turn and bake 20 minutes longer, or until tender and brown.
Add shrimp, olives and pimientos to refrigerated half of sour cream.
Heat it slowly in a saucepan, do not boil.
Serve sauce over chicken.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cornflakes and oleo.
Spray one casserole (8 x 12-inch) with nonstick cooking spray.
Spread mix to all corners evenly. Top with cornflakes mixed with oleo. Preheat oven to 350° and bake 35 to 45 minutes.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Beat sugar and butter together until smooth.
Add beaten eggs; beat until fluffy.
Add and mix remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased, floured large pan.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except pie shells.
Pour into pie shells. Bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: frozen strawberry dessert
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool.
Break up into fine crumbles.

title: chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Melt semi-sweet chocolate morsels over hot (not boiling) water. Remove from heat and add condensed milk, water and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
Line bottom and sides of 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish with double thickness of heavy aluminum foil.
Pour in chocolate mixture.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Pour gently over chocolate in baking pan.
Bake according to package directions until cake tests done.
Invert cake on rack.
Lift off pan.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Peel off foil.
Sprinkle nuts on top. Cut in squares.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Drain peaches and place in dish.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream margarine.
Add 3/4 cup sugar and dry ingredients, slowly, with milk.
Pour over peaches.
Sift 1/2 cup sugar and cornstarch; sprinkle over batter.
Pour 1 cup boiling water over mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix.
Drop mixture over batter in pan by spoonfuls.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
(I test with a toothpick and find that it usually requires close to 40 minutes.)

title: all day chili
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Place on low setting and cook 8 hours or until you get home from work.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease a Bundt or tube pan.
Place pecans in bottom.
Cut each biscuit into quarters.
Mix together sugar and cinnamon; shake biscuit pieces in mixture.
Toss in pan.
Add remaining sugar/cinnamon mixture to top of biscuits and pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling water.
Chill slightly.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well and chill.
Save one egg for decoration if desired.
Serves 10.

title: amy's meatless burgers(282 calories per serving)
directions: Boil together water,
soy
sauce,
oil,
garlic,
onion, Italian seasoning and yeast.
Mix
oats and nuts together, then sprinkle gradually into boiling broth.
Let stand until most of the liquid is absorbed.
Then
stir
lightly
until just mixed. Drop by spoonfuls on oiled
cookie sheet.
Press flat.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain (do not add salt).
Spray a 2-quart dish with nonstick spray.
Arrange broccoli in dish.
Pour 1 cup uncooked Minute rice over broccoli.
In saucepan, heat margarine, soup and Cheez Whiz.
Stir often.
Pour over broccoli and rice. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until it begins to bubble.

title: veal with peppers, italian style(makes 4 servings)
directions: In skillet, heat 3 tablespoons of the oil.
Add the peppers, onion and garlic; saute until tender, stirring often.
Transfer to a bowl.
Add the olives, capers, anchovies, salt and pepper.
Keep warm.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package.
Drain corn.
Mix rice, corn and cream of chicken soup.
Layer with cheese.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° until lightly browned, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms, remove stems, chop stems and combine with garlic, bread crumbs, cheese, eggs, salt, pepper and oil. Stuff mushrooms with above filling. Sprinkle with
parsley, dot with butter. Place in shallow baking dish. Pour wine over all. Bake at 400°F. for 15 minutes.

title: creamed chicken over rice
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Add soups.
Heat in a slow cooker for 4 to 6 hours.
Melt bouillon in water for rice.
Cook rice.
Serve chicken over rice.

title: "willie pearl's" beef stew
directions: Flour and brown meat in hot oil; add water, lemon juice, chopped onion, bay leaves and seasonings.
Cover and let simmer 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Take out bay leaves and add carrots, potatoes and can of tomato juice and cook until tender, about 45 minutes.
Everyone loves it!

title: deer steak marinade
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and pour over steaks.
Marinate at room temperature 1 to 3 hours, turning occasionally.
Drain steaks.
Broil over charcoal or under oven broiler.
Baste frequently.

title: snow ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until thick.
Add vanilla, sugar and salt.
Beat in whipping cream.
Fold in fresh snow.
Wet, dense snow doesn't work as well as light, fluffy snow.

title: favorite coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease an 8 x
x
2-inch, 9 x 9 x 2-inch or 9 x 9 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Blend all of the ingredients except topping.
Beat vigorously
minute.
Spread
in pan. Sprinkle topping over batter.
Bake
to 30 minutes or until pick comes clean.
Serve warm.

title: christmas salad
directions: Melt red hots in boiling water.
Add gelatin and stir in applesauce.
Chill until firm in a ringed mold (8-inch).
Serve with sour cream.
Unmold on plate.
Fill center hole with sour cream and decorate around with holly.
This salad is especially good served with turkey or baked chicken.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Combine orange juice, pineapple juice, sugar, egg and flour (mix flour with sugar before adding to liquid); cook over low heat until thick.
Add marshmallows; stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add to marshmallow mixture with fruits.
Chill; fold in whipping cream.
Chill until set.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: 9-inch oil crust
directions: Put flour in middle of 9-inch pie pan.
Mix milk and oil. Pour over flour at once.
Stir until blended.
Pat dough into crust with fingers.
Shape around sides and bottom of pan. Prebake at 350° or bake with favorite filling and directions.

title: cheesy potato slices
directions: Slice potatoes into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Brush all sides of each potato slice with melted butter.
Place potato slices in baking pan and broil for 15 minutes or until tender.
Sprinkle potatoes with salt to taste.
Combine cheese, onion powder and paprika.
Sprinkle evenly over potatoes.
Broil about 2 minutes more.
Serves 2.

title: chicken divan
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer broccoli and chicken; pour sauce over top.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: apple orange syrup
directions: Cook all ingredients in one quart saucepan over medium heat just until mixture thickens slightly and boils.
Stir constantly.

title: golden coins
directions: Mix all well and pour over hot carrots.
Keep well.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine sugar and oil; add eggs.
Sift flour and other dry ingredients.
Add to sugar and oil; beat well.
Add vanilla, grated carrots, nuts and raisins.
Bake in an oblong pan or three 8-inch layer cake pans which have been well-greased.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
When cool, ice with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Mix corn, eggs and most of milk and pour in baking dish.
Dissolve cornstarch in remainder of milk.
Add sugar, salt and pepper.
Add to contents in baking dish.
Mix all together and put in casserole.
I had to bake mine at 350° for 1 hour.
A little longer would be better.

title: english muffin pizza
directions: Split muffin and spoon 2 tablespoons of sauce on each muffin half. Add the cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese melts. Serves 1.

title: cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Cream together cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add jello and blend well.
Fold in stiffly whipped Milnot.
Mix graham cracker crumbs and melted margarine.
Pack 2/3 of mixture on bottom and sides of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan (or larger).
Add filling and sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Chill several hours.
Cut in squares and serve plain or garnish with fruit.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: In blender, combine milk, sugar, biscuit mix, eggs, butter and vanilla.
Cover and blend on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan. Let stand about 5 minutes; then sprinkle with the coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Will make its own crust.
Can be made without a blender.

title: vanilla butternut cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour, milk and flavoring.
Makes three 9-inch layers.
Bake at 350°.

title: dixie corn bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.	Add buttermilk, egg, and drippings, mixing just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour into a greased, hot skillet.
Cook in 450 degree oven 20-25 minutes.
Serve warm with butter.
Yields 4-6 serving.

title: hamburger noodle bake
directions: Brown ground beef in butter; drain.
Add garlic, salt, pepper, sugar, corn and tomato sauce.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Cook noodles.
Mix onions, cream cheese and sour cream.
Layer in a square baking pan 1/2 the noodles, 1/2 the cheese/sour cream mix and 1/2 meat mixture.
Repeat.
Sprinkle with Cheddar, Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll and cut in 7-inch squares.

title: pizza loaf
directions: Let loaf of thawed bread dough rise following label directions.
Prepare filling and cook pork or hamburger with mushrooms (if using), onions, salt and pepper in a large skillet until no pink remains; drain off excess
fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, paprika, oregano and garlic salt.
Bring to boiling; lower heat and cover.
Simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally; cool.
Punch dough down and roll out on floured surface to 15 x 12-inch rectangle.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Combine ingredients; beat well by hand.
Beat egg whites. Pour first mixture into bucket.
Add 1 1/2 quarts milk or until bucket is 3/4 full.
Pour egg whites on top and stir.
Turn by hand or use electric ice cream freezer until firm.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into prepared pie shell and cover with top crust.
Pierce top crust. Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
This is even better warmed over the next day.

title: escalloped potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients, except corn flakes mixture.
Sprinkle buttered corn flakes on top.
Use a 3-quart casserole or large flat glass baking dish.
Bake for one hour.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Bake in 3 lined 9-inch layer pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: whole wheat muffins
directions: Add flour with baking powder and salt.
Add whole wheat flour, brown sugar and dates; mix thoroughly.
Combine and add milk, beaten eggs and melted fat; mix quickly until dry ingredients are just dampened.
Stir 3 or 4 times.
Spoon into buttered muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes or until nicely browned.
Dates may be omitted.
Recipe makes 12 medium sized muffins.

title: mexicorn casserole
directions: Drain corn; save juice.
Mix flour in juice.
Add melted butter, onions and sliced chestnuts to corn.
Add juice and flour mixture; mix well.
Cook in covered buttered casserole dish for about 45 minutes at 350°, until thick.
While cooking, stir occasionally to prevent sticking.
Cook the last 5 to 10 minutes uncovered to allow the mixture to cook down.

title: fat man's salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill at least 1 hour.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend in milk and egg with hand mixer.
add corn, stirring by hand.
In large frying pan with oil, drop in tablespoon size portions and fry until golden brown on both sides.

title: candy cake roll
directions: Brush cookies with milk.
Spread with whipped topping (use 2 cups).
Stack in 4 or 5. Place stacks on plastic wrap to form a roll by pressing together lightly.
Wrap and refrigerate 6 hours, until firm.
Unwrap.
Place on a platter.
Frost with remaining whipped topping.
Garnish with chocolate candy bars.

title: date hors d'oeuvres
directions: Fill date with nut.
Marinate several hours in dressing.
Wrap in 1/2 strip bacon; microwave until bacon is cooked.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve immediately.

title: rhonda's cabbage casserole
directions: Saute cabbage in bacon fat on low heat.
Add mixture of sugar, vinegar and water.
Cover and cook over low heat until cabbage is tender.
Add cooked noodles and crumbled bacon.
Serve hot.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix together sugar, flour and cocoa.
Mix with scalded milk in top of double boiler.
Cook until thickens.
Add beaten egg yolks. Cook for a few minutes longer until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell, that is already cooked.
Beat egg whites with 4 tablespoons of sugar and a little vanilla until stiff.
Put on top of pie and bake until lightly browned at 350°.

title: magnolia house broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crackers, and blend well. Pour into casserole dish and top with crackers.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until bubbling.
Melt butter and mix with crackers before topping.

title: goat cheese and green onion scones
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix first 4 ingredients in large bowl. Add cheese and green onions and toss with fork.
In small bowl, blend egg and half and half and stir into dry ingredients.
Mix gently until dough forms.
Divide dough in half.
On lightly floured surface, flatten each piece into 3/4-inch thick rounds. Cut each round into 6 wedges.
Transfer wedges to baking sheet, spacing evenly.
Bake scones until tops are brown, about 25 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: hanky pankies
directions: Fry sausage and drain off fat.	Place sausage on paper towel. When cool, crumble and put back in skillet after you clean it from all fat with paper towel.
Put cut up cubes of Velveeta cheese in with sausage and melt the cheese.
Stir well.
Sprinkle a little oregano and mix; spread on small rye cocktail bread slices and freeze.	Keep frozen until ready to use.
Take out as many as you want
and do not thaw.	Bake at 350° until thawed and bubbly, about 10 minutes.
Check bread and make sure it doesn't burn on bottom.

title: venison tenderloins
directions: Combine all ingredients except tenderloins.
Mix well.
Add tenderloins.
Marinate in refrigerator 4 to 8 hours.
Drain tenderloins.
Grill over medium-hot coals to desired doneness.

title: chocolate bourbon balls
directions: In a large bowl, beat confectioners sugar and margarine until fluffy.
Add bourbon and chocolate.
Beat 2 minutes.
Stir in nuts.
Dampen hands and form mixture into 3/4-inch balls.
Place on waxed paper lined pan.
Chill until firm.
Roll half in cocoa and half in confectioners sugar.
Refrigerate.
Makes 36 balls.

title: ranch-style chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, thoroughly combine soup mix, buttermilk, flour and garlic; set aside.
In lightly greased 2-quart shallow casserole, arrange chicken breasts and vegetables; add soup mixture.
Bake, uncovered, 20 minutes.
Remove cover and top with bread crumbs combined with melted butter.
Continue baking, uncovered, 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.

title: cocoa brownies
directions: Blend margarine, sugar and vanilla. Add eggs and beat well with spoon. Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt. Add to egg mixture until well blended. Stir in nuts. Spread in greased 9-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool in pan.

title: popovers
directions: Spread popover pans with oil and heat them for 10 minutes in a hot oven (450°).
Sift flour and salt together.
In a separate bowl, beat the eggs until frothy.
Add milk and melted butter. Stir the liquid slowly into the dry ingredients.
Beat until well blended, but not longer, then pour the batter into the oiled and heated pans, filling them only 1/3 full.
Bake in a 450° oven for 20 minutes, then reduce heat and dry them in a moderate oven, about 350°, for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove popovers at once from the pans and puncture them to let the steam escape.

title: golden beef casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and peppers in a small amount of oil.
Mix all remaining ingredients.
Pour into 1 3/4 quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6. Serve over rice.

title: country vanilla ice cream
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Slowly add sugar; beat well.
Add cream, vanilla and salt.
Add milk to the fill line on the freezer container.
