title: taco salad
directions: Mix taco seasoning with 1/4 cup water to with drained beef. While browning beef, cut up lettuce, tomatoes and grated cheese. Toss together in glass bowl. Add beef and broken chips and toss. Put desired amount in salad bowls and pour in dressing.
Enjoy.

title: yellow nectar pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a Bundt pan sprayed with nonstick spray.
Bake at 350° until cake begins to brown, then turn oven to 250° and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour, or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: delicious chicken
directions: Boil and bone chicken and place in bottom of large casserole dish.
Mix soup and milk well; pour over chicken.
Spread dry dressing mix over this mixture.
Melt margarine and add to broth. Pour over the preceding mixture and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Mix together the flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir, but do not beat, until mixed.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: baked macaroni and cheese(home economics class of 1946)
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water until tender; drain and wash. Make white sauce of flour, margarine, milk and seasoning.
Add 2/3 of cheese to sauce; stir until melted.
Pour over macaroni in a greased baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and bread crumbs over top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream shortening with the sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend the dry ingredients.
Mix in oatmeal by hand.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes for chewy, 15 minutes for crisp.

title: baked nacho-taco dip
directions: Spread ingredients into a 9 x 13-inch pan in the order given. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.
Serve warm with plain tortilla chips.

title: flower pot dessert
directions: Use large plastic flower pot with no drainage holes.
Layer ice cream and topping of your choice.
Add nuts, broken up candy bars or whatever you choose.
At the top of your flower pot, spread crumbled cookies.
They will look like dirt.
Pop in freezer.
At time of serving, push into ice cream a bunch of artificial flowers and serve with a small garden spade.
Nice for everyone ... men and children think it's super.

title: final exam brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Add sugar and beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, vanilla, marshmallows, nuts and chips.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Spread 1/2 cup chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: holly dolly bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt caramels and milk in double boiler.
Mix dry ingredients together and mix in butter.
Pat 3/4 of mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 10 minutes at 350°. Take out of oven and spread the chocolate chips over crust, then pour melted caramel mixture over chips.
Then crumble rest of reserved mixture over caramel.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: no crust apple pie
directions: Turn
pie
filling
into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
In
a bowl, mix together flour, sugar, baking powder and
salt
with
a	fork.
Stir
in egg mixture (eggs, vanilla and butter) until crumbly.
Sprinkle over pie filling. Pour
melted butter over top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until top is brown and crisp.

title: bean dip
directions: Spread the following evenly in a dish or platter: refried beans, sour cream and salsa.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Layer cut up tomatoes, avocados, green onions and olives.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cherry salad
directions: Drain cherries; heat the juice and dissolve the jello in it. Add a little water and the sugar to the cherries and boil for 4 minutes. Add to jello. When cool, add the nuts and chill to set.

title: fried bow ties(quanti)
directions: Beat eggs; add baking powder and mix in flour enough to make smooth dough, like pasta dough.
Let dough rest (even overnight). Roll dough out thin and cut in 6-inch strips x 2 inches wide. Make slit in middle.
Fold one end through slit to make twist. Place in hot oil; fry to golden.
Place on paper towel to absorb oil.
Serve plain or sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: blackberry delight
directions: Crush vanilla wafers and mix with butter.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and mixed Dream Whip.
Pour into crust.
Add blueberries.

title: corn meal muffins
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Combine rest of ingredients. Add gradually to flour, stirring in lightly.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Makes 8.

title: nan's turkey dressing
directions: Mix all together; stuff both ends of the bird.
Bake as directed by manufacturer.
Remove stock from the pan as the turkey bakes.
Set aside.
Will be used for giblet gravy and to moisten uncooked dressing.
When the turkey is almost done, pack the rest of the dressing around the bird.
Moisten with 2 to 3 cups of the stock.
Bake until all is cooked.
When everything is cooked, remove all of the dressing from around and inside the turkey.

title: bread pudding
directions: Butter the toast.
Place in a 10x6-inch cake pan.
Place raisins on the toast.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender. Drain and cool. Blend all ingredients together, bring to a boil and pour over carrots. Cover and refrigerate overnight
or several hours. Will keep for two weeks.

title: steak casserole
directions: Cut steak into small pieces and brown in the oil (flour steak).
Place steak in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Put onion slice over steak.
Add sliced potatoes.
Pour soup and water, mixed together, over all.
Bake for 1 hour, or until potatoes are done.

title: smoked salmon ball
directions: Mix ingredients together thoroughly.
Chill several hours. Serve as a spread or form into a large ball and roll in a combination of chopped nuts and parsley.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Wash sauerkraut good with hot water, then cold water.
Dice green pepper, onion, celery and pimento.
Mix ingredients well and pour sauce over sauerkraut.
Chill and serve.

title: earthquake cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spray with Pam.
Mix together coconut and pecan pieces.
Pour in pan.
Mix cake mix as directed on box. Pour over coconut and pecans.

title: pretzel jello salad
directions: Cream 3 tablespoons sugar and margarine; add pretzels.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Use wok.
Cook vegetables in 1/2 cup oil until crisp.
Push to the side of wok, leaving a hole in center of vegetables.
Place shrimp in the center of wok.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and Old Bay onto shrimp.
Cook until shrimp are thawed and done.
Pour off excess liquid.
Mix in cooked rice.
Toss until thoroughly mixed.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling, salted water until tender.
Drain. Add corned beef, cut up cheese, soup, milk and onion, diced very small.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Cook, covered, at 350°
for 35 to 40 minutes.
Using 3 slices of bread make buttered bread cubes.
Place these on top of casserole and bake for additional 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli according to package and drain.
In a large bowl mix cooked broccoli and other ingredients except chips.
Pour into uncovered casserole dish and sprinkle chips on top; lightly press chips down.
Cook 30 minutes and let cool.

title: mom and dad's poor man's cake
directions: Cover raisins with hot water and cook for 15 minutes.
Mix all other ingredients and add raisins.
Put in Bundt pan or 2 loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: edna's cheese ball
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together; chill. Form into a ball. Roll in pecans. Refrigerate.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add oil, zucchini, pineapple and raisins.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Add nuts.
Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 3/4-inch) at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
Bread freezes well wrapped in foil and put into plastic bag.

title: golden cream of potato soup
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in a Dutch oven. Bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 7 to 8 minutes.
Gradually stir 1/4 cup milk into flour, making a smooth paste. Stir into soup.
Add remaining 2 3/4 cups milk and cheese. Cook over medium heat until soup is thickened.

title: unbaked fruitcake
directions: Toast pecans at 250° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Crumble crackers and add all other ingredients.
Pack in lined loaf pans and store in refrigerator.
Make a week after Thanksgiving to taste good for Christmas.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve 1 cup juice.
Combine fruit and pecans; toss gently.
Combine pudding and 1 cup pineapple juice; beat 1 minute.
Pour over fruit; toss gently.
Fresh blueberries and/or strawberries can be added.

title: easy potatoes
directions: Use as little water as possible for potatoes not to stick. Mix all ingredients with potatoes and cook on top of the stove until done. Quick and easy to make.

title: glazed almond cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, then add nuts, flour and salt.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet; flatten dough.
Brush tops with egg white.
Place 1/2 of an almond in center of each cookie.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 45 cookies.
From my mother-in-law.

title: rhubarb 'n dumplings
directions: In a 2-quart microwave-safe casserole, combine 1 1/4 cups water, brown sugar and the first 1/4 cup sugar, cornstarch and 3 tablespoons margarine.
Add sliced rhubarb.
Microcook, uncovered, on 100% (High) for 7 to 9 minutes or until mixture is thickened and bubbly, stirring every minute.
Cover casserole to keep warm.

title: tostado casserole
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Combine hamburger, 1 1/2 cups tomato sauce and taco seasoning mix.
Line a flat 2-quart baking dish with 2 cups corn chips; add meat mixture.
Combine remaining tomato sauce and refried beans.
Spread over meat mixture.
Cover and bake 25 minutes at 375°.
Remove, cover, sprinkle with remaining corn chips and cheese.
Bake 5 minutes.
Serve 6.

title: biscuit topped italian casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 12 x 8-inch (2-quart) baking dish. In large skillet, brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Stir in water, pepper, tomato sauce and paste; simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vegetables and 1 1/2 cups of the cheese.
Spoon mixture into greased baking pan.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Wash chicken pieces.
Place in large pan with cup of water. Cover chicken pieces with garlic, salt, pepper, onion and barbecue sauce.
Cook in oven at 450° until chicken is done, about 1 hour. May have to add a little water.
Serve hot with salad.

title: kasha au gratin
directions: Bring salt and water to boil.
Add Kasha.
Reduce heat, cover and
simmer
minutes.
Saute
onion in 2 tablespoons water. Steam
cauliflower
in
1 inch water.
(If frozen, run under hot water 15 seconds.) Combine all ingredients and stir well.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: butternut squash casserole
directions: In large saucepan, cook vegetables, covered, with chicken broth until tender.
Drain vegetables and transfer to food processor.
Add cream, butter and seasonings and process a few seconds until combined, but not pureed.

title: navy beans or soup
directions: Quick soak: Rinse and sort beans in a large pot.
To 1 lb of beans add 6 to 8 cups hot water.
Bring to a rapid boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat, cover and let stand 1 hour. Drain soak water from beans, rinse and drain again.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Mix Knox gelatine with cold water.
Bring tomato soup, undiluted, to boiling.
Stir in gelatine until dissolved.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes.
In bowl, mix together the cream cheese, mayonnaise, Tabasco and garlic salt.
Add tomato mixture to this, blending well.
Mix in chopped onion, celery and shrimp.
Spoon into a 6-cup mold and chill.
Serve surrounded by crackers.
Serves 35 to 40.
This will freeze.

title: tasty chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix dressing, flour, bouillon, pepper and milk.
Heat until hot.
Add the chicken and vegetables until bubbly hot.
Unroll dough into 2 triangles; pinch together and cut into 1-inch strips.
Place on top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.

title: barbecue bean bake
directions: Brown ground round, bacon and onion.
Drain excess fat. Combine and add all other ingredients except beans.
Stir well. Add beans and mix thoroughly.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
For more servings, double mustard, molasses and all three beans.

title: cheese ring
directions: Mix ingredients together. Form a ring.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Cut rhubarb in small pieces and arrange in unbaked shell. Combine sugar and flour.
Add egg yolks and lemon juice.
Stir into a smooth paste.
Pour this mixture over rhubarb.
Cover with meringue made from egg whites.
Bake in hot oven at 425° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° and bake for 30 minutes.

title: coconut cream dessert
directions: Mix together flour, butter, and chopped nuts.
Mixture will be thick.
Pat in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Then, using a fork, crush and cover entire bottom of pan.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar well.
Then fold in one large size
Cool Whip. Spread evenly over first layer.
Cook boxes of coconut cream pudding with milk.
Cool and spread on second layer.

title: quick and easy dessert
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding together.
Add pecans; then marshmallows.
Fold in Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: braciola(crock-pot)
directions: Cut meat into strips.
Blend Ricotta and Mozzarella cheeses, onion, egg, parsley and spices.
Spread over strips of meat.
Roll strips up and secure with toothpicks.
Place meat in crock-pot and cover with sauce and wine.
Cook on low 10 to 12 hours.

title: larson's 3-bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thoroughly brown hamburger.
Fry bacon to crisp stage.
Break into pieces.
Combine pork and beans, partially drained lima beans and partially drained kidney beans in a small roaster or large casserole.
Add ketchup, brown sugar and vinegar to bean mixture.
Add cooked meats and stir.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: corny dogs
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Coat wieners with batter and fry in hot grease until golden brown.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, eggs, vanilla and sugar. Pour into graham cracker crust. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until set. Cool and pour pie filling on top. Chill.

title: *fruit salad
directions: Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and whipped cream together. Fold in crushed pineapple, marshmallows, green cherries and red cherries.
Combine all ingredients and chill in a large pan until firm.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sprinkle sugar over the apples and let stand 10 minutes.
Add oil and egg.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Add nuts.
Pour into a small greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° about 50 minutes.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, salt, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, apples, vanilla and nuts.
Mix and pour in well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in microwave for about 5 minutes to soften. Put all ingredients together in large pot and cook on medium heat for 45 minutes.
Stir often.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Make white sauce by combining margarine, flour, water and bouillon.
Add broccoli and cheese; spice to taste.
Excellent and filling meal.
(250 calories per 1 c. serving.)

title: polish mistakes
directions: Brown meat and drain well.
Combine all other ingredients; stir until cheese melts.
Spread on party rye.
Place on cookie sheet and put in freezer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Store in plastic bags.
When ready to serve, place on cookie sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.

title: breakfast cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add egg and beat well. Stir in milk, then dry ingredients.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle topping over.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll or pat on floured surface. Cut with biscuit cutter or glass.
Place in lightly greased baking dish and bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: beet cake
directions: Blend and mix well the Crisco, eggs and sugar.
Sift together flour, salt, cinnamon and baking soda, then add to first mixture. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
May be served plain or with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: dreamy apricot salad
directions: Combine sugar, water and jello in a saucepan. Bring to a boil. Remove from heat and add fruits. Set aside to cool. Beat chilled Cool Whip and add softened cream cheese. Combine with gelatin mixture and nuts. Pour into a mold and chill.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix cocoa into melted butter.
Add cocoa and butter mixture to sugar, flour and eggs.
Mix well.
Stir in chopped nuts, vanilla, coconut and salt.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
When cake is done, remove from oven and spread 1 package miniature marshmallows on top.
Place back in oven and melt marshmallows.
Remove and let cool 1 hour.

title: grilled scallops(appetizer)
directions: Wrap each scallop in a strip of bacon and fix with a toothpick. Put scallops on skewers.
Grill over hot charcoal until bacon is crisp; turn frequently.

title: 2 x 2 soup
directions: Brown ground beef.
Combine all ingredients and simmer for at least 30 minutes to allow flavors to blend.

title: my shrimp dish
directions: Saute shrimp in butter in frying pan for 8 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and cook another 8 minutes.
Serve over cooked white rice.
Serves 4.

title: clam fritters
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Add clam liquor, milk and eggs. Stir until well blended.
Add clams and butter; mix.
Drop from spoon into deep, hot fat.
Brown.
Serve with tartar sauce. Serves 4.

title: corn pudding
directions: Grease bottom of baking dish with butter.
Beat 2 eggs (not too well).
Add about 2 tablespoons flour, sugar, salt, pepper, corn and enough milk until well mixed (not soupy).
Dot with butter and bake in moderate oven (350°) for 45 minutes or fast oven (400°) for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pan brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt 1 cup chocolate chips and butter together.
Stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Add flour, sugar, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Stir until blended.
Add 1/2 cup chips.
Stir.
Spread into pan.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup chips.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate bonbons
directions: Mix together in 1-inch balls.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Dip in melted chocolate.
Place on waxed paper until dry.

title: ham and potato salad
directions: Sprinkle cubed potatoes with Italian dressing.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients to potatoes, except mayonnaise. Chill thoroughly.
Before serving, gently fold in mayonnaise. Makes 5 servings.

title: cinnamon oranges
directions: Boil sugar, water and cinnamon sticks with cream of tartar for 5 minutes. Pour over peeled and sliced oranges.
Marinate for 3 days in refrigerator.
Delicious.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Moisten berries
with enough water so sugar will stick. Put berries in	unbaked
pie
shell
and sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar. Mix flour,	brown and white sugars, salt and margarine until crumbly.
Put
on
top of berries.	This will be mounded over the top.
Set
pie
on a cookie sheet as juices sometimes boil out. Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: dutch meat loaf
directions: Lightly mix ground meat, bread, onion, 1/2 can tomato sauce, egg and seasonings.
Shape into loaf in shallow pan.
Combine remaining tomato sauce with rest of ingredients; pour over meat. Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°.
Baste loaf several times.
Serve with hot noodles, if desired.

title: kraut chocolate cake
directions: Thoroughly cream butter and sugar.
Beat in the eggs and vanilla.
Sift together the dry ingredients; add alternately with the water to the creamed mixture.
Fold in the sauerkraut.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 8-inch square or round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool layers and then frost with the Mocha Frosting.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Fry bacon.
Saute onion in small amount of bacon drippings, and add crumbled corn bread and bacon to pan and stir.
Add enough water to make very moist.
Parboil peppers until tender, place on pan and fill with cornbread filling.
Place under broiler until brown on top.

title: barbecue sauce by mama
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan. Add lemon juice, vinegar, catsup, Worcestershire sauce and spices. Bring to boil and pour over meat to be barbecued.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Blend sugar and butter together.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, to sugar and butter mixture, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour and soda together, then add to mixture, alternating with sour cream.
Beat egg whites slightly and add them with vanilla to mixture.
Blend thoroughly.
Bake in floured and greased tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes before removing.

title: crab and shrimp casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl. Pour into greased casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit pudding cake
directions: Drain fruit cocktail,
Mix egg with sugar.
Add fruit juice, then fruit.
Add flour, allspice, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and vanilla.
Mix together and put into greased 13 x 8-inch pan. Sprinkle over top of batter:
1/2 cup brown sugar mixed with 3/4 cup pecans.
Bake at 350°.

title: marshmallowed sweet potatoes
directions: Arrange potatoes in a single layer on bottom of buttered, shallow baking pan.
Dot with butter and drizzle with honey.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In a deep saucepan, saute the onion and garlic in the melted butter for 3 to 4 minutes. Add the remaining ingredients and 1/2 cup water.
Bring to a boil.
Lower the heat and simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour, stirring frequently to prevent scorching. Strain through a fine sieve.

title: pig cake
directions: Beat for 5 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool before frosting.

title: italian roast beef
directions: Bake meat for 2 1/2 hours at 350°.
Pour all ingredients over meat.
Bake 3 hours.
Take meat out and shred with fork. Pour meat back in sauce and bake 2 hours.
Serve on hard rolls.

title: ritz chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender.
Bone and cut in small pieces.
Spread over buttered casserole dish.
Mix the 2 cans soup and sour cream.
Spread over chicken.
Crush tube of Ritz crackers.
Mix with celery seed and spread over soup.
Melt the margarine and sprinkle over casserole evenly.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: mushroom supreme
directions: Saute mushrooms in margarine.
In separate pot, heat and dissolve bouillon cubes in water and set aside.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine and sprinkle flour over.
Add cream to butter/flour mixture.
Add bouillon mix to this and add mushrooms.
Place everything in buttered casserole (large enough to leave mushrooms in a single layer).
Top with mixture of bread crumbs and cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can do ahead.
Serves 6. To double recipe, just double mushrooms.

title: beef and peppers
directions: Cut beef across the grain into slices about 2 inches long and 1/4 inch thick.
Combine cornstarch, sugar and Accent; blend with soy sauce and sherry.
Mix with beef; set aside.
Cut green pepper into 1 1/2-inch slices.
Pour 2 tablespoons oil into skillet.
Set over high heat; add salt, then peppers.
Stir constantly until peppers turn darker green, about 1 minute. Remove peppers, leaving oil in skillet.
Add remaining oil to skillet with crushed garlic; stir in beef mixture and cook, turning constantly, about 2 minutes.
Add green pepper; mix well. Serve with fried rice or plain rice.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Cut up and brown pork.
Add 1/4 cup water.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Drain pineapple; save liquid.
Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add pineapple syrup, vinegar, soy sauce and salt. Cook until thick.
Pour over pork and let stand 10 minutes.
Add pineapple, bell pepper and onion.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Garnish with noodles.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Put water, oil, margarine and cocoa in a sauce pan.
Bring to a boil and pour over flour and sugar.
Beat well and add buttermilk, baking soda and eggs.
Mix well and pour into a 13 x 9 inch pan. Bake at 325° until done, approximately 30 to 35 minutes.

title: p f t cheese ball(perfect, fast, tasty)
directions: Leave cream cheese at room temperature for 1 hour.
Cut dried beef into small pieces.
Cut only green tops of onions into very small pieces.
Mix all 3 ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: lamb chops with minted fruits
directions: Set oven control at broil and/or 550°.
Broil chops 3 inches from heat about 7 minutes or until brown.
Cut cheese to fit chops.
Set aside.
Turn chops; broil 5 to 7 minutes longer. Place onions and cheese slice on each chop; broil 2 minutes or until cheese begins to melt.
Serve with Minted Fruits.
Makes 4 servings.

title: steak parmesan
directions: Combine bread crumbs and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese; set aside. Combine egg, water and pepper in a small bowl.
Dip steaks in egg mixture; dredge in bread crumb mixture.
Brown steaks in hot oil in a large skillet over medium heat for 3 minutes on each side. Arrange in an 8-inch square baking dish.
Top with pizza sauce. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.

title: mexican taco casserole(microwave)
directions: Crumble ground beef and onion in a microwave-safe dish. Microwave on High power, uncovered, 5 to 6 minutes, or until no longer pink, stirring once to break meat apart.
Drain.
Layer 1 cup crushed taco chips in bottom of 1 1/2-quart microwave casserole dish.
Cover with cooked beef, dry taco seasoning mix, tomato sauce, sour cream and cheese.
Top with rest of chips. Microwave on High, uncovered, 5 to 6 minutes or until cheese melts and is heated through.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Set aside.
Mix sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add to flour mixture.
Fold in apples and pecans.
Grease and flour Bundt pan or 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes, until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift all ingredients together and add fruit cocktail and eggs. Put in baking dish.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: holiday mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and cook potatoes.
While hot, mash potatoes in a large bowl until all lumps are gone.
Chop the cream cheese into small pieces and add to potatoes along with butter.
Beat well until butter and cheese are melted and completely mixed.
Add sour cream. Combine milk and eggs.
Add to potatoes with salt and pepper.
Beat well until fluffy.
Put in greased 9-inch round casserole and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° until lightly browned.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: blue ribbon pretzel fruit salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and sugar.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 400° for 8 minutes. Cool.

title: coconut orange jumbles
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Beat in coconut. Sift flour, salt and baking soda together and add alternately with orange juice to cream mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Drop by teaspoons on ungreased baking sheet.
Sprinkle with additional coconut and orange peel.
Bake in hot oven, 425°, for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Combine soup, broth and tomatoes with chilies; blend until smooth.
Place a layer of chicken in a casserole dish; add layers of tortillas, onion, cheese and sauce.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: country rye bread
directions: In large bowl, combine 2 cups all-purpose flour or bread flour, sugar, undissolved yeast, caraway seed and salt.
Gradually add water and oil; beat for 2 minutes on medium speed.
Scrape bowl occasionally.
Add 1/2 cup flour; beat 2 minutes on high, scraping bowl.
Stir in rye flour and enough all-purpose flour to make soft dough.
Knead on a floured surface until smooth and elastic (6 to 8 minutes).

title: artichoke squares
directions: With juice from artichokes, saute chopped onion and garlic; drain and add chopped artichokes.
Beat eggs and add bread crumbs, Tabasco and seasonings. Stir in artichoke mixture and grated cheese.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan or baking dish at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: portuguese bean soup
directions: Combine ham hocks and sausage in heavy large saucepan over medium-high heat and saute for 4 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients with enough water to cover.
Bring to a boil, skimming foam from surface.
Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer about 2 hours.
Remove ham hocks from soup; discard bones and cut
meat into bite-size pieces.
Blend into soup.
Ladle into bowls and serve hot.
Makes 8 servings.

title: greek spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti (break in half before cooking).
Drain and squeeze excess water from spinach.
Bake chicken breasts.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese; add Accent and garlic salt.
Mix 3/4 of green onions and beef with
cheese.
Form ball.
Spread rest of green onion and beef on waxed paper and roll cheese ball on it. Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: chili dip
directions: Brown meat and onion in skillet.
Stir in catsup, chili powder and salt.
Mash in beans.
Heat through.
Top with 1/2 cup of sharp cheese and 1/4 cup chopped onion.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together first three ingredients.
Add vanilla, egg and work in flour. When well mixed, shape into 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet (allow spreading room).
Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.
May change flavoring to change taste.

title: hawaiian rumaki appetizer
directions: Wrap pineapple chunks and water chestnuts with bacon and secure with wooden picks.
Place wrapped rumaki in bowl and pour dressing over. Toss to coat.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Place on broiler pan and broil (or) bake at high temperature until bacon is crispy. Serve hot with extra dressing.

title: lettie's irish stew
directions: Put all
of
the ingredients in a large soup kettle and simmer over low
heat
for at least 6 hours or all day. Remove soup bone and
bay
leaves.
This should be thick; add more or less water accordingly.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Grind together zucchini, onions and all peppers. Sprinkle 5 tablespoons salt on top. Cover and let set overnight.
Rinse 2 times in cold water.
Take the vinegar, sugar, dry mustard, turmeric, cornstarch, celery seed and pepper and bring to a boil. Dump zucchini in.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal. Makes 7 pints.

title: oreo delight
directions: Crush Oreo cookies and combine with melted butter.
Place half of cookie mix in a flat dish, pressing on the bottom.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Make layer of corn chips, layer of chicken and layer of onion (lightly sprinkled).
Make layer of cheese.
Continue layering until ingredients are used up.
Let soup and milk cream together and warm until no longer lumpy.
Pour over completed layers.
Top with remaining cheese.
Cook in convection oven at 350° for 30 minutes or microwave 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cajun beans
directions: Brown beef, bell pepper and onion.
Drain grease.
Put in crock-pot with other ingredients and cook 4 hours on low.

title: chicken and artichoke casserole
directions: Remove chicken skin. Sprinkle with paprika and salt. Brown in 2 tablespoons olive oil. Place in casserole. Arrange artichoke hearts and black olives around them. Add broth. Brown mushrooms in 2 tablespoons oil. Sprinkle with flour. Add sherry. Bring to boil; simmer 1 minute. Pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Cream sugar, eggs, oil and water.
Add dry ingredients, putting potatoes last.
Put in 2 or 3 greased and floured loaf pans.
Fill 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Mix Karo syrup and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Mix in peanut butter and cornflakes.
Put in sheet pan and cut when cooked.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix with dry Hidden Valley dressing mix. Roll into ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix brown sugar, cinnamon and softened butter in a pan on low heat.
Put biscuits in a pan and pour mixture over biscuits.
Bake biscuits in preheated oven for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle nuts over the baked biscuits and serve.

title: "no bake fruit cake"
directions: Chop nuts, candy and fruit.
Mix with graham crackers.
Heat butter to melt. Add marshmallows a few at a time until
melted. Pour over fruit mixture.
Mix well.
Spoon into loaf pan. Store for several days before serving.
It is best to use both candied cherries and pineapple.

title: coffee cake
directions: Crumb the first 6 ingredients together and take out 1/2 cup for the topping.
Add cinnamon and nuts to topping mix.
To the remaining mixture, add the rest of the ingredients.
Beat the ingredients together with mixer.
Pour into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle the topping mixture over the top of batter. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Marinate overnight or for 1 hour.
Drain.
Cook in shallow pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and cook rice according to directions.
Saute 1/2 stick butter with onion and celery.
Then mix all ingredients together and pour into greased casserole dish.
Put grated Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt in saucepan.
Pour in hot water and cook over high heat stirring constantly, until mixture is thick and translucent, about 4-6 minutes.
Remove from heat and add beaten egg yolks.
Return to heat and cook on low heat, stirring constantly for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in butter until melted.
Add lemon juice and stir until mixed thoroughly.

title: baked quesadilla with barbecued chicken
directions: In a large bowl, mix lime juice, water, orange juice, garlic, pepper and salt.
Place chicken breasts in a bowl.
Cover and marinate overnight.

title: fluffy orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Refrigerate until slightly thickened and then whip with electric mixer.
Add softened sherbet by tablespoon to Jell-O and beat.
When mixture is frothy, fold in Cool Whip and mandarin oranges (drained).
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Mix peppers, vinegar and Sure-Jell.
Bring to hard boil.
Add sugar and bring to a rolling boil for 1 minute.
Pour into hot sterilized 1/2-pint jars and seal.

title: creamy shrimp fettuccine
directions: Bring 2 cups water to a boil in a large saucepan over medium heat. Add shrimp and boil 1 minute or until shrimp turns pink. Remove shrimp with slotted spoon, continue boiling shrimp liquid. Add broth and garlic to saucepan. Boil until liquid is reduced to 1/2 cup, about 12 minutes. Add mushrooms, whipping cream, basil and salt. Simmer sauce over medium heat for 6 minutes, stirring occasionally. Place fettucine in a large bowl. Add shrimp to saucepan and heat 1 minute. Spoon shrimp/sauce mixture over pasta. Sprinkle with parmesan and toss lightly. Serve immediately. Serves four.

title: aunt wanda's cranberry salad
directions: Mix ingredients according to directions on boxes of jello. Place in a bowl or jello mold.

title: creamy cucumber salad
directions: Mix dressing and pepper in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients, mix and refrigerate.

title: clam chowder(new england)
directions: Put all ingredients in a large crock and heat in microwave just a few minutes.
If heated on stove, be careful.
Burns easily.
Serve with crumpled bacon on top.

title: ritz cracker cake
directions: Mix crackers, coconut, nuts and butter together.
Make crust. Mix ice cream, milk and pudding; pour over crust.
Refrigerate until filling is chilled.
Top with Cool Whip.
Keep in freezer until one hour before serving; then place in bottom of refrigerator.
Use a glass pan.

title: russian tea
directions: Put all ingredients in 1/2-gallon jar and shake; keep covered. Large package of Twist lemonade is the equivalent of any lemonade mix to make 2 quarts of lemonade.

title: apple zing
directions: Use a hand blender on food processor to blend pears and apple juice until smooth.
Pour into 4 tall glasses.
Spoon in crushed ice.
Top glasses with chilled ginger ale.
Put slice of apple on side of glass.
Makes 4 large glasses or 8 juice size glasses.

title: apricot bread
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients, then blend next 4 ingredients. Add remaining ingredients.
Coat nuts and dried fruit with a little flour.
Pour into loaf pan or 2 small loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Keeps well in freezer.

title: savory grilled potatoes in foil
directions: Mix mayonnaise and seasonings in a large bowl until well blended.
Stir in potatoes and onion to coat.
Divide potato mixture evenly among 6 (12-inch) square pieces of heavy-duty foil. Seal each to form a packet.
Place foil packets on grill over medium-hot coals.
Grill, covered, 25 to 30 minutes or until tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Parboil chicken, cut into pieces.
Spray a 13x9 cooking dish and arrange chicken on bottom.
Add corn.
Put soup in bowl, dilute with water and stir.
pour soup mixture over top.
Prepare stuffing as directed on box and place over soup mixture.
Cover with foil and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Combine with sugar, flour, salt and spices; mix well with apples.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Dot with butter and add top crust.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pierogi dough(very light and easily digestible dough)
directions: Beat eggs.
Add cream cheese, then water and finally flour. Knead until smooth, adding flour until no longer sticky.
Place in refrigerator and let set for a few hours.

title: southern hush puppies
directions: Combine dry ingredients; add buttermilk, egg and onion, stirring well.
Carefully drop batter by tablespoon into deep hot oil (370°), cook only a few at a time, turning once.
Fry until hush puppies are golden brown (3 to 5 minutes).
Drain well on paper towels.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add the soup, peas and cooked noodles.
Place in a baking dish and top with grated cheese.
Bake long enough for cheese to melt.

title: tasty barbecue sauce
directions: Combine in a quart jar, shake well.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and flour together.
Stir in the rhubarb. Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
